    ('15', 'QA Goals for 2019', 'We have below QA goals for 2019. To track work against all these goals created this Epic.聽|Goal|Measure|Value||Merging of dev/QA/SRE (Squad Level)|# of Teams where Dev resources are responsible for positive functional testing|5 squads (at least 1 outside of the U.S.)||Test Coverage, lower level test (backend, unit)|Partner with Dev to hook up Sonar to be able to measure unit and dev integration tests|% of teams that have measurable unit and dev integration, and API tests by end of 2019||Familiarity of dev work|QA resources completing dev tasks|20% of QA resources have completed 12+ dev tasks thoughout the year.聽||Smarter Regression Strategy (timing / risk / defects found/missed)|1. Earliest Detected field is driving behaviour changes on squads2. Regular review of test suites|1. By end of year, 80% of teams are using earliest detected field in JIRA during each retrospective to determine where to focus efforts2. Test suite reviewed every quarter||Upskilling of existing resources|# of manual only testers|SZ - 26 current product QA, reduce in half to 13All other regions, 0 manual testers outside of data collections||Test Transparency - team understands - measured through TestRail|1. #/percentage of cases in Test Rail2. Percentage of product testing which has backup globably|1. 100% of test cases in testrail2. 100% of globabl (Dev/QA/LOB) teams can run each other''s cases and generate test report.||Non-functional testing (Non functional positive) - Performance/Load/Security/Accessibility/Negative|#/% of test cases in TestRail that are non-functional#/% of non-functional bugs|Each team should strive to have 10% of their test cases be non-functional||Business Acumen / Customer focus|Interactions with users / business including side by sides, user forums, customer visits|At least 1 customer interaction per quarter for every employee||QA Innovation|Identify problems - for example within Data Quality|1 major problem identified per quarter|', -