    ('21', 'New Fixed Income stats for portfolio objects', 'We recently released a number of fixed income data points at the Fund level. We want to now apply these calculations to portfolio objects (model portfolios, client accounts) so that users can see these same, new and value added data points for their portfolios instead of just the funds that sit within those portfolios. See attached for a priority ordered list (column A) of the data points that should be rolled up to this level.', 588, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, 'Data Services - July-August 2019', '2019-07-01T00:00:00', '2019-08-13T00:00:00', 2, 0, null, null, 'CLP-1028'),
    ('22', 'Design for: Office Cloud - Pop Up Client Reports', '_As an Office user, I want to generate a report and view it without having to switch to the reports page. The report should appear in a separate window or tab once it has finished generating so that I don''t have to leave my current workflow._*Goal:* towards migration efforts & usability improvements*Dependencies:*聽 OC, Design聽*UX Design Link:*聽[https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/Y3NROT9KHUB]聽*Ideal Flow:* * 1. User generates any report for a Client, Account or Prospect, via ad-hoc workflow ** 1a. (from Clients & Accounts or Prospects area) * 2. User is notified that report process has begun ** 2a. We would like to communicate progress with users via a progress indicator * 3. When report process has completed: ** 3a. User is notified that report has completed, via in system notification, and ** 3b. Report automatically opens in a new tab or window, based on user''s browser preferences, and ** 3c. Report is saved to Reports area * 4. If needed, when report fails, provide pop up warning that provides reason why report failed. See Jira OC-3560.*Out of Scope:* * Any reports run via Batch/Run Batch Now*Open Questions:* * Is there something that GAR has worked on with reports that we could use as a starting point? ** EF: I spoke with GAR and that workflow will not satisfy our criteria. Reports do not currently auto-open when complete. * If user leaves Client & Accounts or Prospect page, will that impact our ability to: ** notify them when the report has completed, or ** automatically open the report in a new tab or window? * Are there tech concerns with the ideal flow outlined above? * Are we able to communicate an accurate progress indicator/time estimate for report completion with users? * If the time estimate is longer than 5-10 seconds, are users able to engage in other tasks (like going to another page in Office) while they wait? ** Would users be able to generate a report for a different client? ** What impact, if any, would that have on the first report? ** Would there be additional impact to keep in mind? ** Is there a limit on the number of concurrent reports that could be generated? At what point would performance be greatly impacted? * A likely scenario is that a user may want to run an ad-hoc report for a couple different clients. Instead of going to each client separately to generate the report, could we allow them to select a couple of different clients and run the same report on them ad-hoc? ** What would be the concerns for that approach?聽聽', 95, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, '241', 'Office Cloud - Report Management', 'CLP-1200'),
    ('23', 'Auto-Select Representative Performance Stream setting for import', 'One of the most frequently requested features we get for Cloud import is to support the ''Auto-Select Representative Performance Stream'' security matching option.聽This setting exists in 3x but not in Cloud:!image-2019-04-24-15-33-21-788.png!This setting is especially necessary for EMEA users who will often be working with investments that trade on multiple exchanges and in multiple currencies. Without it, users will see lots of multiple-match errors which are tedious (and sometimes unreasonable) to manually correct.聽Including this setting will greatly reduce friction for users trying to move over from 3x to Cloud. 3x users are used to having this setting available.This setting will apply to the following import file types (in priority order): # Account, model and custom benchmark holdings (for the holding identifier security matching) # Investment list # Investment list with custom datainformation for 3.X: [https://mswiki.morningstar.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=243243181]Spec: [https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/DCT/Security+mapping+options]', 265, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 5, 5, null, null, 'CLP-1183'),
    ('24', 'June-July Billing Projects: Bill by Group and Pershing Custodian Fee File', '聽 # Bill by Group (Bill by Group, Fee data update in client view and group view, generate billing summary/custodian fee file by group) # Generate Pershing Custodian Fee File', 37, 5, 2, null, '2019-05-30T00:00:00', '2019-07-10T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud - Jun-Jul 2019', '2019-05-30T00:00:00', '2019-07-10T00:00:00', 141, 141, '62', 'Office Cloud -  Billing Parity', 'CLP-1196'),
    ('25', 'LIQD - Lists - View', '*Background:*聽It''s the building block of the whole liquid objects project to be able to view and analyze investment lists bi-directionally in 3.x and Cloud.聽', 527, 5, 2, '#1954a0', '2019-07-11T00:00:00', '2019-08-21T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud - Jul-Aug 2019', '2019-07-11T00:00:00', '2019-08-21T00:00:00', 1, 1, null, null, 'CLP-1213'),
    ('26', 'Dev for:Customizing viewed results in the Clients & Accounts Grid', '聽{color:#172b4d}*Definitions:*{color}聽+{color:#205081}Active Flag:{color}+ This is a client who is actively working with the advisor. The advisor is providing services & billing this client.聽 This client would be part of any practice analysis the advisor ran.+Inactive Flag+: This is a client who once did business with the advisor, but has discontinued the business relationship.聽 The advisor no longer actively reports, bills or provides advice to this client, but for compliance reasons, must keep that Client''s data on file for 5-7 years after the relationship has ended. This client would not be included in any current practice analysis, but the advisor would include this data in any audits that included past years.聽*Target:* All Office Cloud Users*Area:* Clients&Accounts grid, Prospects & Accounts*Dependencies:* Office Cloud, DOPA (API work should be complete)聽*Design:**Visual Spec:*聽[https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/EDN181GTCM6#/316926068_ClientAnalysisGrid-Cover]*UX Spec*:聽[https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/KVNROABTR23]聽{color:#172b4d}+*ACs:*+{color}*As an OC user, I would like a way to easily distinguish between inactive & active clients in the Client & Account area, so that I can quickly focus on my active clients when performing daily workflows.* # As a user, I聽 set clients who no longer do business with me to inactive because ## for compliance reasons, I do not want their records and history deleted from OC ## 聽I don''t want these clients in my daily views on my practice, reports, etc. # In most instances, I am only interested in seeing my active client list, as my daily workflow revolves around them. Therefor, I would like the option to default my Client & Account grid view to reflect only active clients. # There may be occasions when i need to see a list of my inactive clients, so i need a way to view all the Clients i have marked as inactive.聽 ## Example of this may be audits or is an old client comes back with a claim/complaint/etc. ## I am also need to find an inactive Client back to active if i start doing business with them again. # Because I may be approached by legal/compliance questions...... # Determine best way to label active/inactive Clients in Office Cloud # User still needs to maintain the ability to view gird as just a list of accounts OR with accounts organized and displayed under Client # As a user, i expect ''export'' to capture the current view in which i am viewing the client & account gird.*As an Admin user of OC, I would like a way to view results聽in Client & Account area, by entire firm or advisor so that I can change between workflows that require firm focus and individual聽advisor focus.* # As an admin, I need to see the list of all clients/accounts across the entire firm # As an admin, I need to see the list of client/accounts for one particular advisor in my firm #  ## as an admin, i would like to see just active clients for a particular advisor ## as an admin, I would like to see jsut inactive clien', 397, 5, 5, '#F0A509', null, null, null, null, null, null, 32, 32, null, null, 'CLP-1108'),
    ('27', 'Support Client Level Report Setting in OC', '*The general requirement is锛?*1锛? *All options available in Global Report Settings should be customizable on the Client level.* # ** *Bond Yield (Stretch in June-July Scope)* # ** *Return Type* # ** *Fee Type* # ** *Display Accrued Interest (TBD If it鈥檚 global level only)* # ** *Include inception to date return on Performance Reports* # ** *Reporting Currency* # ** *Cover Page Disclosure* # ** *Include Logo* # ** *Cover Page* * ** the setting should can be change to use global level as default.Doc from Kristen:[https://morningstaronline-my.sharepoint.com/:w:/r/personal/kristen_carstensen_morningstar_com/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc=%7B9a41e24d-a8f3-494b-bcca-f8eb3b920eef%7D&action=default&wdLOR=c9387F935-D8C0-427C-ADAF-51D74E675CD0&cid=21947a8d-6a42-4e4d-ab2c-5be8cb2eeb8a] [https://morningstaronline-my.sharepoint.com/:w:/r/personal/kristen_carstensen_morningstar_com/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc=%7B9a41e24d-a8f3-494b-bcca-f8eb3b920eef%7D&action=default&wdLOR=c9387F935-D8C0-427C-ADAF-51D74E675CD0&cid=21947a8d-6a42-4e4d-ab2c-5be8cb2eeb8a]**聽*Design:*UX:聽聽[https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/WRNROI5DHP8#/316929208_01_Cover]聽Visual: ?', 58, 5, 2, '#F0A509', '2019-05-30T00:00:00', '2019-07-10T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud - Jun-Jul 2019', '2019-05-30T00:00:00', '2019-07-10T00:00:00', 123, 123, '58', 'Office Cloud - Portfolio Accounting Settings', 'CLP-1175'),
    ('28', 'Portfolio Editor Enhancement Phase II', 'This project aims to upgrade portfolio editor:1) bring multiple usability enhancements for current existing portfolio editor functionalities2) add Auto Allocate functionality, which can help user to construct portfolio against a policy automatically.聽These enhancements will be enabled for both DWM and OC.', 643, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 26, 26, null, null, 'CLP-1202'),
    ('29', 'Interactive portfolio return and custom data import for DWM/DAM', 'One of the largest functionality gaps that we have today between 3x and Cloud import, is that Cloud import does not support interactive import of portfolio returns.聽We can import portfolio returns through batch, but when clients just want to do a small volume one-time return load it is a hassle to setup a batch process.聽This epic is to allow interactive import of returns in DWM and DAM. In addition, along with returns we''d also be able to import other types of custom data (like classifications).This is a frequent ask from CSMs and we''ve gotten communities ideas posted about this as well.Design: [https://morningstaronline-my.sharepoint.com/:w:/g/personal/eileen_bingle_morningstar_com/ERnrx-erD2hIitPOUqv_XlcB2B1zf5hOi5eFtUdCRlivCA?e=wYCIO2]*{color:#de350b}Updated on 6/19:{color}*{color:#de350b}Still keep the second dropdown as below, other wise we can''t distinguish the Model Portfolio & Model Portfolio with custom data import in the "Import status" page.{color} * {color:#de350b}聽Account Custom data{color} * {color:#de350b}Model Portfolio Custom data{color} * {color:#de350b}Custom Benchmark Custom data{color}+Helper text for the info icon for this file type+:"To import a portfolio return or custom data file, structure your file with the column formatting described in <include Chad''s one page document>."Instructions and example Files:PortfolioReturn_Example.xlsPortfolioCustomData_Example.xls**Comments from Eileen: I don''t think we need the columns section; it''s repetitive from what''s in Chad''s file. Example files are attached to this ticket.聽聽', 515, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 19, 19, null, null, 'CLP-1182'),
    ('30', 'LIQD - Lists - Edit', '*Background:*聽For investment lists in Phase 1 of the liquid objects project, users need the ability to edit the lists聽in either system and have the lists be in-sync.聽', 526, 5, 2, '#ff4e4d', '2019-07-11T00:00:00', '2019-08-21T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud - Jul-Aug 2019', '2019-07-11T00:00:00', '2019-08-21T00:00:00', 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-1214'),
    ('35', 'New search results design implementation', '[~mjankow] has created a new standard design for search drop-down results, so that Auto-Complete (security) results are displayed consistently across the product (considerate of space).This epic is to track the dev work to implement the design change in various components of Cloud.Includes Home Search bar, RP search bar, Grid/Screener (list creation, security searches), Portfolio, and Nerts.聽Mar-Apr:AC1: Design mock-ups and MDS documentation from the Design team.AC2: Validate design approach with Cloud Commercial team.AC3: Scope and plan development work for Nerts, Portfolio, GCS, RP Search bar, and Home Search bar.聽Apr-May:AC4: Execute development work planned in AC3.', 136, 2, 5, '#ff4e4d', '2019-11-14T00:00:00', '2019-12-25T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud - Nov-Dec 2019', '2019-11-14T00:00:00', '2019-12-25T00:00:00', 34, 21, '181', 'Search Usability in Cloud', 'CLP-1020'),
    ('36', 'CLP - Workbooks Going Away', 'Design Specs for Workbook Retirement: * Header Hierarchy [https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/SXNRPXJCR6U#/316939410_00_Cover] * Edited State & Tag [https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/QGNRPWG34Y6#/316939226_00_Cover] * Menu [https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/6MNRPQRK5X2#/316937560_00_Cover] * 3 Objects Relationship [https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/GWNRPXLF3YE#/316939415_00_Cover] * Saving Referential Objects [https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/Y3NRPXRSUDC#/316939429_01_Cover] * Analytical view Creation [https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/EQNRPXPATG4#/316939422_00_Cover] * AV File Management [https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/VJNRPXNX8DK#/316939420_00_Cover]聽This work is required before a workbook goes away because a user''s workflow聽for saving a column set and peer analytics will change once workbooks are removed. This is a prerequisite to Framework removing workbooks.聽聽*Feature:* * Save prompt for Saving changes to a modified column set, column set settings and/or peer analytics to support the future state of a WB (going away).聽**聽*Assumptions:* * When we refer to 鈥渃olumn set鈥? we are now referring to 鈥渃olumn set鈥? 鈥渃olumn set settings鈥?and 鈥減eer analytics鈥?*Out of Scope:* * File Management state of column sets * Saving as a future state. We will have a save prompt today like we do with workbook saving * A combined state of Column Set and Peer Analytics. * Removing 鈥渞ead only鈥?column sets for M* saved column sets聽聽*JTBD:* * When I have a saved column set in the grid, I want to ability to update it and save my changes as needed so I can make my column set more applicable to me. * When I鈥檓 looking at different lists, I want a re-usable standard to analyze funds to save time so I don鈥檛 have to recreate the same analysis for different lists. * When I am creating a new column set, I want to use an existing column set as a jumping off point so I can save time when my column sets are similar. * When I鈥檓 doing adhoc analysis, I want to quickly answer my question and then return back to my original workflow so I don鈥檛 lose track of my original analysis. * When I create and save a column set, I want to share it with other Direct users so we can apply the same analysis to our investments.聽聽Outstanding:1) changing data sets in a list聽 * no save prompt * data set as part of name * open recently viewed ** all data sets - selection * show "recently viewed options" for a list that isn''t saved yet - can we remember recently viewed stuff for lists that aren''t saved yet?2) editing data set * active vs passive save * read only聽 * passive save prompt is different *', 134, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 58, 33, '15', 'Cloud Navigation & Information Architecture', 'CLOUDCX-2552'),
    ('37', 'Page Layout - Phase 3', 'The work in this ticket gets us ready to release the full page layout changes by moving column set storage from the workbook to data api v2 and putting the components into a flyover that opens over the grid.', 608, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-642'),
    ('38', 'Registration API for BAA/Pershing User Registration', 'We need an API to create new users in the Office/UIM system when a new client is created in BAA by Pershing.!registration API.png|thumbnail!To create a corresponding Office client when聽Pershing create a client in BAA system, Office might need more details of the client. These will be provided by BAA:聽 # Client鈥檚 BAA ID (investor鈥檚 person ID) # Advisor鈥檚 BAA ID (advisor鈥檚 person ID) # The Albridge ID of the client # Client鈥檚 email (not necessary but preferred) # Client鈥檚 first name and last name.This work has dependencies on Import and PMS teams: # API to output Office Advisor ID 聽through Advisor BAA ID # API to store mapping of Office client and BAA clientSee diagram: [https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/FINPLAN/Pershing+PFM+Components]聽', 672, 2, 5, '#069de2', null, null, null, null, null, null, 4, 4, null, null, 'CLP-939'),
    ('39', 'Impacted Lists - enhance alerts to include list information - part 1 is to display the list name that triggered the alert', '* It聽is not enough聽to just聽alert users that a security has triggered an alert,聽we also need to help them assess impact.聽聽 * Having the API team create this API will help users understand the linkage between the security and a list that triggered the alert for the user聽聽 * Ex: if I set up alerts for category change on my approved list (and聽dodgx聽is in my approved list) when the category change alert triggers for DODGX, we need to be smart enough聽to say that yes聽this triggered for DODGX but DODGX is part of your Approved List and聽with聽expansion聽and over time, we could also let me know where else they "hold" this security聽 * _This would most likely span multiple program planning cycles聽and require work from the API team. NERTS would not be able to complete work until the API was developed._ * *Short Term*聽*GOAL:*聽聽 * associate individual investments to the lists that the user has stored in the system聽 * be able to tell users if an alert about AAPL triggers, that it impacts these two lists they have聽set up * be able to tell user if聽an alert trigger聽about APPL, which list they set it up for (why are they receiving the alert 鈥?if they set it up on the list level)聽聽 * *Teams I anticipate needing to contribute to this epic:*聽 * NERTS聽 * Security API聽 * Content API V2聽聽 * *Long Term Goal: Relevancy Engine*聽聽 * Need to be able to understand any lists聽and other objects聽a specific security is in (regardless if the user signed up to receive alerts on it or not)聽 * We have so much information about what is important to our users just by simply looking at the data they input in our system 鈥?in the future, we could make the alerts process more proactive by pushing relevant alerts to the users instead of the having them sign up聽*Relevancy Engine*聽聽 * Create an聽api聽of securities that a user holds in a list, screen, model portfolio, or client portfolio聽 * Dynamically update with changes to these聽 * Should also include securities that a user has manually chosen to "watch"/be alerted on聽 * Necessary if M* wants to start pushing聽notifications聽to users聽聽', 479, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 22, 22, null, null, 'CLP-649'),
    ('48', 'Display custom security level returns', '*Use Case*: * Certain securities held by the client鈥檚 account will not match to Morningstar securities (e.g. Merrill Lynch hedge funds) * Since Morningstar will not have any returns for these securities, the client would like to import their own custom returns for these securities * Then, when an account is imported that holds one of these securities, they would like to see the return for that security based on what they imported*Security Performance Source Setting*: Since we allow firms to create multiple return streams, we need to introduce a setting that allows users to pick which return stream they want to use as the primary return for their custom securities.When they chose this option, we will use custom returns where available, and fall back to using Morningstar security return data where no custom data exists.*More details about this feature*: [https://morningstaronline-my.sharepoint.com/:w:/g/personal/eileen_bingle_morningstar_com/Ea111TzEfKBGiwJm64MANUAB_yQvQ8A4mkYpNCfD1CoGkw?e=H5r4uT]聽*The following components need to make change for this epic:* * Portfolio components 鈥?target PROD date 6/19 ** Grid, Holdings Analysis, Holdings Correlation, Holdings Plot, Editor ** Proposal creator and quick account creator * Presentation studio 鈥?target PROD date 6/24 * TPA 鈥?target PROD date TBD (but in June/July period)聽 * Investment workbook components 鈥?target PROD date TBD ** All performance related components * Investment workbook main grid 鈥?will be released along with other global settings updates (target date TBD)*Out of scope*: Equity attribution, for these reasons: * Equity attribution is a holdings based analysis component and this project is focused on custom security returns (not holdings) * Users can鈥檛 add custom securities as holdings to existing funds in M*鈥檚 database * Equity attribution is not available in the Portfolio Analysis workbook * Equity attribution in Cloud is still using an underlying 3.x calculation (not a v2 calculation)', 403, 5, 2, null, '2019-07-11T00:00:00', '2019-08-21T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud - Jul-Aug 2019', '2019-07-11T00:00:00', '2019-08-21T00:00:00', 68, 68, null, null, 'CLP-1053'),
