    ('54', 'Custom Funds', '*Background:*聽Custom Funds are used by Asset Managers, Portfolio Managers and Advisors to better access and monitor aggregated characteristics of a fund plus the ability to create/update/delete historical holdings ad-hoc/daily/monthly.To the user, the custom fund behaves the same as a managed product in Morningstar''s public database. This would require a new user created investment type for 鈥淐ustom Funds."(see attached word document for detailed use cases)*Acceptance Criteria:* * Custom funds can be created via import or manually created * Allow proxy selection as a custom fund setting to select an open end, close end, hedge fund, private fund, SMA, ETFs etc. in Morningstar''s database * Custom funds can apply custom database data points: returns, custom classification and other custom fields * Be accessible to use in Investment Analysis workbooks * Be accessible聽in an investment list mixed with securities in M* database * Access custom funds through new or existing data universe ## Be accessible through a new data universe called 鈥淐ustom Funds鈥?within the firm 鈥?the content in the universe is permission controlled, only users belong to the firm can have access.聽 ## Custom Fund data can be added to an existing (public) universe such as Open end, Close end, Hedge Fund, together with M* standard data * Should not show up in the Client Account list grid view, will not be part of any client or household directly * Custom funds can be added as a holding in a Client Account, Model Portfolio, or Custom Benchmark * Allow custom fund to be a holding of another custom fund * Entitlement/Permission at user or group level within the firm', 371, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-1244'),
    ('55', 'Modernizing Cloud Platform: Architecture Swap + Build System Replacement (Pt. 1 - Capitol Removal)', 'Replace the entire capitol architecture and build system, i.e. `secret-service build dev -s` and聽`secret-service build prod -s` by using the vue-cli 3 bootstrap.聽This gives each application team full access to webpack, code splitting, typescript, jest, vue-router, vuex, and nightwatch out of the box.聽The webpack config for each application will need to be supplemented with framework-specific loaders for each framework-specific FE. (This is done in vue.config.js:聽[https://cli.vuejs.org/config/#vue-config-js])聽The webpack configuration (vue.config.js) will also need to account for outputting assets in a similar manner to the capitol build (where it makes sense).The dev build should use webpack-dev-middleware to serve the SPA. It should auto-reload when front-end changes are made. (Bonus: webpack-hot-middleware)聽聽', 130, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 47, 21, '20', 'Modernizing Cloud Platform', 'CLP-1166'),
