    ('68', 'CLP - Referential Column Sets', 'This work is required before a workbook goes away because a user''s workflow聽for saving a column set and peer analytics will change once workbooks are removed. This is a prerequisite to Framework removing workbooks.聽聽*Feature:* * Save prompt for Saving changes to a modified column set, column set settings and/or peer analytics to support the future state of a WB (going away).聽**聽*Assumptions:* * When we refer to 鈥渃olumn set鈥? we are now referring to 鈥渃olumn set鈥? 鈥渃olumn set settings鈥?and 鈥減eer analytics鈥?*Out of Scope:* * File Management state of column sets * Saving as a future state. We will have a save prompt today like we do with workbook saving * A combined state of Column Set and Peer Analytics. * Removing 鈥渞ead only鈥?column sets for M* saved column sets聽聽*JTBD:* * When I have a saved column set in the grid, I want to ability to update it and save my changes as needed so I can make my column set more applicable to me. * When I鈥檓 looking at different lists, I want a re-usable standard to analyze funds to save time so I don鈥檛 have to recreate the same analysis for different lists. * When I am creating a new column set, I want to use an existing column set as a jumping off point so I can save time when my column sets are similar. * When I鈥檓 doing adhoc analysis, I want to quickly answer my question and then return back to my original workflow so I don鈥檛 lose track of my original analysis. * When I create and save a column set, I want to share it with other Direct users so we can apply the same analysis to our investments.', 133, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 3, 3, '15', 'Cloud Navigation & Information Architecture', 'CLP-1089'),
