    ('70', 'AP Work-Grouping in PS for OC', 'As an Office Cloud user, I need to ability to group account holding information by one or more levels when using聽Portfolio Evaluation & Period Performance components so that I can properly customize my reports to share with my clients.聽 # Multi Level Grouping for Portfolio Evaluation & Period Performance components ## 3 Levels of Grouping ### First Level options: #### Security #### Asset Class #### Asset Class or Equity Sector #### Security Type #### Broad Asset Class #### Super Asset Class #### Account ### Second Level options: #### None #### 聽Security #### Asset Class #### Asset Class or Equity Sector #### Broad Asset Class #### Super Asset Class ##### Note: Super Asset Class is not at second level in 3.x, but we need to add that option for the Cloud version.聽聽 ### Third Level options: #### None #### 聽Security #### Asset Class #### Asset Class or Equity Sector!image-2018-09-25-11-11-48-481.png!聽聽These requirements are needed OC client Financial Planning and Info Services & to make PS at parity with the PS in 3.x聽', 91, 5, 2, '#0d2c54', '2019-08-22T00:00:00', '2019-10-02T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud - Aug-Sept 2019', '2019-08-22T00:00:00', '2019-10-02T00:00:00', 116, 114, '87', 'Office Cloud - Presentation Studio', 'DOPAHAK-3294'),
    ('71', 'Holding Settings-Exclude from Performance', '{color:#172b4d}API link: {color}[https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/SWDO/Portfolio+Accounting+-+Office+Portfolio+API+-+User+Manual#PortfolioAccounting-OfficePortfolioAPI-UserManual-GetAccountSecurities]UX Design:聽[https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/SENROM05URT]聽Visual Design:聽聽[https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/Y8NROTH23RS#/screens/316931661]聽High Level Requirement:h2. *+Security Settings+*h3. *Exclude Securities from Performance (by Practice)**_As an advisor, I need the ability to excluded securities from performance calculations in order to properly report client/account returns to my clients._*|*3.X Name*||Settings &gt; Preferences &gt; Exclude Securities 聽||*What does this do?*||Allows the user to control customizations made on securities in the practice & in they are included in the return calculations on the reports they generate for their clients. 聽 For additional information go to [portfolio accounting setting impact|https://morningstaronline-my.sharepoint.com/:x:/g/personal/kristen_carstensen_morningstar_com/EcQ3pvXmYnhEkuma8K6Hp30BL_9xPDGNuEq4lvU_SpCQIQ?e=vfTnb9] 聽**聽||*Why do we have this?*||Allows the user to control customizations made of securities in the practice so that they can set preferences that impact the entire practice. 聽||*What does the user need in OC?*|| - 聽聽聽聽聽聽聽聽 Determine where & how these exclusion preferences should be accessed - 聽聽聽聽聽聽聽聽 *The ability to globally exclude a security from performance calculations when running returns on Clients or Accounts* o聽聽 Anytime any account in my practice hold "security x" it will automatically be excluded from performance calculation when I run performance reports for any of the clients in my practice. o聽聽 This is a blanket rule, setting applies to all, no exceptions o聽聽 As default I would like to see a list of securities held in the account to make my exclusion selection from o聽聽 In cases where I have liquidated a security mid- performance period, I need the option to view liquidated securities in order to make an exclusion election if necessary. 聽|聽h2. *+Holding Settings+*h3. *Exclude Holdings from Performance (by Account)**_As an advisor, I need the ability to excluded holdings from performance calculations in order to properly report client/account performance to my clients._*|*3.X Name*||Settings &gt; Preferences &gt; Exclude Securities 聽||*What does this do?*||Allows the user to control customizations made on securities in the practice & in they are included in the return calculations on the reports they generate for their clients. 聽 For additional information go to [portfolio accounting setting impact|https://morningstaronline-my.sharepoint.com/:x:/g/personal/kristen_carstensen_morningstar_com/EcQ3pvXmYnhEkuma8K6Hp30BL_9xPDGNuEq4lvU_SpCQIQ?e=vfTnb9] 聽**聽||*Why do we have this?*||Allows the user to control customizations made of securities in the practice so that they can set preferences that impact the entire practice. 聽||*What does the user need in O', 54, 5, 2, null, '2019-05-30T00:00:00', '2019-07-10T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud - Jun-Jul 2019', '2019-05-30T00:00:00', '2019-07-10T00:00:00', 64, 64, '58', 'Office Cloud - Portfolio Accounting Settings', 'CLP-1226'),
    ('72', 'Design For: Mass Setting Management (Client & Accounts)', 'h5. *UX*:聽[https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/ZRNROVBV7ND#/screens/316931918]***Visual*:聽[https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/U8NRP52SB4P#/316933832_toolbarChangeSettings-Cover]h1. *Improve Setting Management*h2. *+Client & Account Settings+*_As an Office Cloud user, I need a fast and simple way to review & update settings on all my Clients and Accounts so that I can easily manage applying settings across my practice._聽__聽|*3.X Name*||_Setting Assignments_ 聽__聽||*What does this do?*||Help the user get a big picture view of the settings applied to their practice as well as make changes to saved setting over many clients or accounts at the same time.||*Why do we have this?*||Users may have 50 + clients and 100s of accounts.聽 They need ways to quickly setup & change settings over many objects at once to save time and increase productivity. (Time is very valuable)||*What does the user need in OC?*|| * User needs a place in which they can view all Client settings and Account settings across their practice ** Admin should be able to view & update the entire firm ** Advisor should be able to view & update their own clients or clients they have read/write sharing permissions on. * User needs the ability to apply a single setting across multiple clients/accounts at once ** For example: _As a user I would like to add the S&P 500 as the primary benchmark for 40 of my 100 Clients._ * Default Settings & Setting Hierarchy ** 聽As a default, Client settings should follow Global Settings *** In this case, the following should be communicated to the user: **** Client is set to follow global settings **** What those global settings are (ex. If the global primary benchmark is S&P 500, that should be clear to the user when viewing client level information) ** When setting Client settings, I need the following options: *** Option for client setting to follow global setting elections *** Option to ignore global setting elections & select customized setting choice for client(s) ** As a default, Account Settings should follow Client Settings *** In this case, the following should be communicated to the user: **** Account is set to follow client setting **** What those client settings are (ex. If the client primary benchmark is S&P 500, that should be clear to the user when viewing client level information) ** When setting Account settings, I need the following options: *** Option for account setting to follow client setting elections *** Option to ignore client setting elections & select customized setting choice for account(s) * User needs the ability to view/manage the following settings in mass: ** Client Level Settings *** Report Settings *** Primary Benchmark *** Secondary Benchmark *** Tertiary Benchmark *** Model Portfolio ** Account Level Settings *** Primary Benchmark *** Secondary Benchmark *** Tertiary Benchmark *** Model Portfolio *** Exclude from Client Aggregate (using 3x name since don鈥檛 have new name yet) *** -Exclude from Client Aggregate Re', 53, 5, 2, null, '2019-05-30T00:00:00', '2019-07-10T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud - Jun-Jul 2019', '2019-05-30T00:00:00', '2019-07-10T00:00:00', 9, 9, '58', 'Office Cloud - Portfolio Accounting Settings', 'CLP-1198'),
    ('73', 'Client & Holding Level Settings', '<p>	This epic is a placeholder for client and holding level settings. Requirements are forthcoming per Kristen''s work. Specific features are: -1) Exclude Account from Client Aggregate (Not in June July scope)- 2) Exclude holding from performance calculation 3) Mark holding as unmanaged. 4) Client and default setting relationship. 聽. API link:[https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/SWDO/Portfolio+Accounting+-+Office+Portfolio+API+-+User+Manual#PortfolioAccounting-OfficePortfolioAPI-UserManual-GetAccountSecurities]</p><div>	<br /></div><div>	.</div>', 49, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 5, 5, '58', 'Office Cloud - Portfolio Accounting Settings', 'CLP-1314'),
    ('74', 'OC Cloudy Portfolio Phase 1', '1. Apply to change to following components in this Phase*Client/Account Workbook,*聽*Prospect Workbook:*Account Analysis, Market Value, Allocation, Historical Performance*Model Workbook:*Holding Analysis,聽Market Value, Allocation, Historical Performance聽2. Re-calculate data logic:聽聽3. Apply this change to user in White list{color:#172b4d}Appendix: {color}Phase 1 Requirement from :聽[https://morningstaronline-my.sharepoint.com/:w:/r/personal/andrew_franger_morningstar_com/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc=%7B1fe2c5ff-ae20-4d82-bb33-ab856359cd60%7D&action=default&wdLOR=c2654744A-C626-4C55-ACB7-6DAFE62601BD&cid=f329c375-3ce9-4f0a-8559-ea1610b1a926]聽Data Set List:聽[https://morningstaronline.sharepoint.com/:x:/r/sites/Office2019/Shared%20Documents/Spec/Cloudy%20Portfolio/Batch%20Data%20Sets.xlsx?d=wd6a1faaa7147458d897dd6c8eb171f5f&csf=1&e=YQRpPG]聽Action List which need trigger batch data update[https://morningstaronline.sharepoint.com/:x:/r/sites/Office2019/Shared%20Documents/Spec/Cloudy%20Portfolio/AWS%20Action%20vs%20Request.xlsx?d=we078169a2fc04700ac4ce119a1d530cc&csf=1&e=a8Qgys]聽聽聽聽聽聽', 81, 5, 2, null, '2019-05-30T00:00:00', '2019-07-10T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud - Jun-Jul 2019', '2019-05-30T00:00:00', '2019-07-10T00:00:00', 12, 12, '17', 'Office Cloud - AWS Batch (Cloudy)', 'CLP-934'),
    ('75', 'Separate Research & amp; Research Notification Services', 'Currently the research & research notification services are deployed/run on same infrastructure as other Cloud Platform shared services (Data Service, Global Setting Service, Setting Service, etc).聽 To handle聽expected/increased聽future load we want to move the Research Services to separate hardware so it can be scaled independently.聽聽', 749, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-788'),
    ('76', 'Upgrade Account Editor in OC', 'As an Office user, I would like to see the upgraded portfolio editor to enhance my accounts/model/custom benchmark creation workflow.1# User can select Mstar security, user created portfolio, portfolio primary benchmark or portfolio attached modal to be its benchmark.2# When creating a new account, user can add holding from manually search or load the holdings from investment/modal holding list.聽When creating a new modal/custom benchmark, user can add holding from manually search or load the holdings from investment list.3# Add allocation component to show current vs benchmark data.4# In grid view, user can see the asset allocation for current portfolio, benchmark & securities data.*This updated version of portfolio editor for Office Cloud (OC) will not use all the functionality available in Portfolio Editor 3.0. This is a list of the necessary functionality for Office Cloud:** OC does not currently support policies** remove Policy selection from step 1** we will display benchmark instead of policy for table and allocation component** remove policy section under portfolio settings * only the Asset allocation column set will be available in OC for this version* we will not use the growth component at this time, only the asset allocation bar chart* we will need the apply equal weight functionality** we will not use Auto-allocate functionality at this time* we need to support the following ways to add holdings:** by searching** from investments lists** from user created portfolios** from model portfolios* we need to support entering weights for models* we need to support entering weights, shares and market value for accounts* support the updated add holdings search experience** bucketed results** smart search', 13, 5, 2, '#6EBDAB', '2019-08-22T00:00:00', '2019-10-02T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud - Aug-Sept 2019', '2019-08-22T00:00:00', '2019-10-02T00:00:00', 79, 76, '152', 'Portfolio Editor 3.0', 'CLP-824'),
    ('77', 'Portfolio Editor Enhancement Phase III', 'This project aims to upgrade portfolio editor:1) bring multiple usability enhancements for current existing portfolio editor functionalities2) add Auto Allocate functionality, which can help user to construct portfolio against a policy automatically.This epic represents the first phase to enable this new editor for model portfolio in DWM.聽This new editor will be enabled for other portfolio types in DWM and in OC in following phases.聽聽聽', 644, 5, 5, '#ff9867', null, null, null, null, null, null, 81, 77, null, null, 'CLP-1212'),
    ('78', 'Link Investment Detail Report Generation', 'As an Office user, I would like to generate an Investment Detail report to better analyze a security. The options to generate the report should be 1) via the security drop down menu in a account holdings grid view, model holdings grid view, investment list grid view, or screen grid view and 2) via a link in the Morningstar Report.', 89, 5, 5, null, '2019-10-03T00:00:00', '2019-10-23T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud - Oct - Nov 2019', '2019-10-03T00:00:00', '2019-11-13T00:00:00', 29, 29, '279', 'Office Cloud - Investment Research', 'CLP-1187'),
    ('79', 'Retire Security Master ETL batch process', 'The DWM import system is comprised of three technical pipelines: * ETL batch import 鈥?this was built back when we were trying to deliver the UST deal. However, there are severe limitations with this pipeline: ** No parallel processing ** Configuration setup does not support multiple clients running on the same client database ** Morningstar as a company is moving away from ETL/Informatica technology, so there is very little technical expertise/support for this technology * Backend batch import 鈥?updated batch process, supports parallel processing. There are limitations in the volume we can handle in this pipeline, but we will enhance that * Interactive import 鈥?this is for the UI; technology is the same as backend batchDue to the limitation listed above for the ETL batch import process, we need to retire the ETL.This includes: * Moving the remaining ETL file loads onto backend batch, this includes: ** Merrill Lynch account files (this should already be done in April/May planning period) ** Merrill Lynch monthly security master file ** MIM daily performance file * Shutting down all code and technical infrastructure related to the ETL data flowRetiring the ETL process reduces technical risk and simplifies our system.', 713, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, 'Cloud - Nov-Dec 2019', '2019-11-14T00:00:00', '2019-12-25T00:00:00', 41, 14, null, null, 'CLP-1181'),
    ('80', 'Update investment types IDs in custom data services to be consistent with portfolio and security services', 'Currently, /v2/custom-content/ services and all associated kafka flows use the following two types: * CLIENTSECURITY * CLIENTACCOUNTHowever, /portfolio and /securities API services use these types: * DWMAccounts * OFCAccounts * DWMTempAccounts * CUSIP * SECID * PerformanceId * ClientSecID**Custom data services need to be updated to use these types. That way all of APIv2 is consistent.', 831, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-1156'),
    ('81', 'Import 3rd Party Models into Office Cloud via API (Model Marketplace)', 'As an Advisor, I would like to import my models into Office Cloud from external sources via API, so I can use my models in Office without having to manually re-create them.', 91, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, 'Cloud_Q3 2020', '2020-07-01T00:00:00', '2020-09-30T00:00:00', 0, 0, '278', 'Office Cloud - Model Marketplace Native Experience', 'CLP-1154'),
    ('82', 'Add Office Client Profile''s "Client Rank" and Account Profile''s "Business Type" Data Points to External Data APIs', 'As an Office integration partner, I would like the following data points to be added to the external Data APIs so the users can retrieve the "Client Rank" data at the household profile, and be able to determine if an Account''s "Business Type" is Broker Dealer or Advisor at the Portfolio Management Level.聽AC1. Add a data point,聽ClientRank, to the response of /v2/households/profiles[https://api-data-stg.morningstar.com/dataapi/v2/households/profiles]MaaS external endpoint: {color:#0563c1}https://www.us-api.morningstar.com/household/v2/profiles {color}The "Client Rank" field is free-from text field.!Office 3.x Client Profile General Client Rank.png!AC2. Add a data point, BusinessType, to the response of v2/portfolios/profiles[https://api-data-stg.morningstar.com/dataapi/v2/portfolios/profiles?householdIds=]{household-ids}聽MaaS externl endpoint: {color:#4471c4}https://www.us-api.morningstar.com/portfolio/v2/profiles {color} 聽 The Business Type field have 3 options from the drop-down list: "None", "Adivsor", "Broker Dealer"!Office 3.x Account Profile Business Type.png!聽AC3. The M* developer site''s API documentation should be updated with the new data points.聽', 102, 5, 2, '#a59e89', '2019-07-11T00:00:00', '2019-08-21T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud - Jul-Aug 2019', '2019-07-11T00:00:00', '2019-08-21T00:00:00', 8, 8, '273', 'Office Cloud - Standardizing Office APIs for 3rd Party Integrations', 'CLP-1106'),
    ('83', 'Risk Model for Portfolios', 'Risk Model requirement for Office Cloud is the default version of scenario analysis + pre-defined custom scenarios and on multi-asset model only.', 44, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, 'Cloud_Q2 2020', '2020-04-01T00:00:00', '2020-06-30T00:00:00', 0, 0, '18', 'Office Cloud - Client & Account Analytics', 'CLP-966'),
    ('84', 'GUID Project: Retire usage of non-GUID IDs (Phase 2/2)', 'The GUID ID project is a technical re-factoring for the generation and storage of DWM user created objects. The goal of this project is to move all IDs (client security IDs, account IDs, etc.) to GUID format because:* It will be easier to store data for these different types of objects in the same table (for calculation results, for example) if we have the same ID format* It will make the Office transition easier b/c office client securities and accounts use GUIDsFor the first part of this project, both existing IDs and GUIDs will be generated and stored for the objects. For example, both a ZZID and a GUID will be created for client securities.*For the second part of this project, we will start to only create GUIDs for these objects, and retire usage of non-GUID IDs.**This epic if for the second part of the project.*', 466, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 8, 3, null, null, 'CLP-564'),
    ('85', 'Strategy Components - Phase 3', '*Background:*聽To date we have built performance components, track record analysis component and strategy overview.Next we''ll focus on the Holdings Analysis component, Allocation component*Please note we have a dependency on the holdings data availability', 113, 5, 2, null, '2019-05-30T00:00:00', '2019-07-10T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud - Jun-Jul 2019', '2019-05-30T00:00:00', '2019-07-10T00:00:00', 6, 6, '11', 'Release Mercer Performance, Operations, and Portfolio Data in Cloud', 'CLP-1110'),
