    ('87', 'Office Cloud - Pop Up Client Reports', 'As an Office user, I want to generate a report and view it without having to switch to the reports grid. In an Office user''s day to day work flow, events happen that trigger the need to analyze and review an account or client using one of Morningstar''s reports. These events include an unexpected meeting with a client or to review the results of a change made in the portfolio, such as replacing one investment with a different investment.This workflow is uninterrupted, meaning the user is not going to stop and do something else mid-process. He or she is generating the report with the intent of reviewing the report immediately. As a result, the report needs to populate or appear in a separate window or tab in the browser. This action makes it easier for the user because he or she does not have to navigate to the reports section to view the report. It reduces the number of clicks and speeds up the time it takes for the user to see the report.After the review of the report is complete, the user may want to print, save, or email to a client.Acceptance Criteria聽聽', 98, 2, 5, null, null, '2019-07-10T00:00:00', null, null, null, null, 22, 22, '241', 'Office Cloud - Report Management', null),
