    ('93', 'Liquid Objects: Screens', '*Background:*聽Screens are a critical piece to the success of the Cloud upgrade. Users must have the ability to view the 3.x screens they''ve previously created in 3.x in Cloud so they don''t have to build from scratch again. Users will also be interested in validating that the output is consistent across 3.x and Cloud and so we''re deciding to read the 3.x results in Cloud and not convert to a v2 screen (for the near future)聽*Project Goal:* Minimize friction and risk of users moving from Desktop to Cloud for engaged use. Make this as painless as possible.*Proposed Solution:* 3.x screens single direction migration | Cloud screens not migrated back to 3.x*Explanation of Solution:* * All 3x screens are viewable in Cloud * All Cloud screens are not viewable in 3.x * Edits made to a 3.x screen would appear in Cloud after saving * Users cannot edit a 3.x screen in Cloud ** No adding investments, removing investments or search criteria*Definitions:* * Search Criteria 鈥?Term used interchangeable as a Screen*Non-functional requirements*:聽 # A 3.x created screen should not have any noticeable performance differences in Cloud compared to other screens loading in Cloud ## The user should not be able to tell based on load times or interactions what system a screen was created in # Scope of screens includes both Office and Direct # Users will not have the ability to view Cloud created screens in 3.x聽*Requirement Document*:https://morningstaronline-my.sharepoint.com/:w:/r/personal/phil_nagel_morningstar_com/Documents/Documents/Manager%20Research/Management%20Docs/Liquid%20Objects%20Proposal_Screens_v1.docx?d=w699b1ced15e04679a3bbfd8be094085f&csf=1&e=ztUdFl', 2, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 2, 2, '10', 'Liquid Objects - Lists', 'LIQD-254'),
