    ('96', 'Liquid Objects: Investment Lists', 'As a user, I need the ability to access and edit my lists interchangeable between desktop and web for office/direct cloud in order to rely more on the cloud platform as I proceed with the upgrade process聽All applicable functional requirements for investment lists will be linked to this ticket as user stories.Non-functional requirements include:聽 # A Cloud or 3.x created list cannot have any performance differences in each other''s system compared to their respective products ## The user should not be able to tell based on load times or interactions what system a list was created in # Scope of investment list objects includes both Office and Direct # Users on older versions of 3.x desktop will be able to view their Cloud created lists in 3.x, but it will exclude any Cloud supported investment types that aren鈥檛 supported in 3.x ## Users will need to be the latest version of desktop to view non supported investment types from Cloud聽Requirements/assumptions聽used for聽Q4 2018 Tech estimates available at - [https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/DWM/1.+Investment+List]聽*Definitions:* * User Created Object 鈥?An object such as a Model Portfolio, Client Account, Custom Benchmark, Account Group, Strategy (PMS Objects) * Column Set 鈥?Same as a Data Set in 3.x; Cloud uses the term Column Set * List 鈥?Same as Investment List, these terms used interchangeably * Synchronized - A setting used in 3.x when a list is applied to a reports or other areas of Direct & Office. A synchronized list will mean that edits to that list will also be applied to areas where the list is used.聽*Usage Info.:*聽聽Number of investments in investment lists:|*Product*|*Max Count*|*Avg Count*||Direct|6017|79||Office|2688|39||聽|聽|聽|||聽|聽|聽||聽聽聽聽聽聽聽聽聽聽聽聽聽聽 *Direct* *Range*|*UserCount*|*UserPercentage*||*1-40*|7638|55.92%||*40-80*|2236|16.37%||*80-200*|2400|17.57%||*200-1000*|1332|9.75%||*1000-2000*|41|0.30%||*2000-4000*|9|0.07%||*>4000*|2|0.02%||*Total*|*13658*|*1