    ('172', 'Liquid Objects: Data Sets', '*Background:*聽Data sets are a critical piece to the success of the Cloud upgrade. Users must have the ability to view all data sets they''ve previously created in 3.x in Cloud so they don''t have to build from scratch again.Yes, there are known data gaps that we will have to deal with and hope to close in the future.聽聽Non-functional requirements include:聽 # A 3.x created data set cannot have any performance differences in Cloud compared to other data sets loading in Cloud ## The user should not be able to tell based on load times or interactions what system a list was created in # Scope of data set objects includes both Office and Direct # Users will not have the ability to view Cloud created column sets in 3.x聽聽Requirements/assumptions聽used for聽Q4 2018 Tech estimates available at -聽[https://mswiki.morningstar.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=271566156]聽*Definitions:* * Custom Data 鈥?A data point created by the user or firm in the custom database * Column Set 鈥?Same as a Data Set in 3.x; Cloud uses the term Column Set * List 鈥?Same as Investment List, these terms used interchangeably聽', 8, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, 'PI0', '2019-05-01T00:00:00', '2019-05-31T00:00:00', 36, 4, '192', 'Liquid Objects - Column Sets', 'LIQD-1'),
    ('173', 'Refactor Morningstar Reports', '<p>	Legacy report generation solution pre-exists PDF teams on-the-fly reports and is very error prone and requires considerable overhead.聽 聽 * Switch out our service * Retire old service ** Turn off control M reporting jobs ** Retire file shares with old report docs on them ** Turn off MPS reports聽 * Figure out where to store old copies if they are needed for users/if they are even important to have client facing old reports * Testing plan (latest page, alerts, research components highlighted section) 聽 聽 ---- Global Fund Report Creation since our original implementation has transformed into a central process. We are being tasked by the Research Products team with retiring the legacy process and by the Cloud and Reports team to update our process so they have better visibility into what documents and securities are getting the most usage.聽 More details are needed to be added on as we build out this ticket for 2019 The existing solution, files are stored after report in the various folders here: (redacted)</p><p></p><p>	 The original implementation goal was to keep a history of GFR鈥檚 to improve transparency. Historical point-in-time reports are a requirement of the Due Diligence persona to see what the reports were saying when user''s receive an alert about them. The same process for capturing what the data is at point-in-time also how the equity reports aid users when they do their quarterly reviews. Our GFR''s also contain some inconsistencies and customization made to make the print date be the date from the data represented in the Cloud report. The date of the rating also doesn鈥檛 change unless it went from one rating i.e. Neutral to another, non-neutral rating. To work on this ticket we will need: 1. Change the GFR''s that are accessible in areas like Search, Research Components, Grid/Screener and from an Alert email to always show the latest data.聽 2. Switch our process to have GFR''s created on-the-fly like we do for ESG reports 3. To figure out how to generate point-in-time snapshots for a user has an alert or wants to see the historical reports they can see them in the Research Portal. We will use this solution to also swap out ETF, Stock, Target Date (when built), UK Investment Trust, and any other reports.聽</p>', 668, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, 'Cloud - Oct - Nov 2019', '2019-10-03T00:00:00', '2019-11-13T00:00:00', 19, 19, null, null, 'CLP-1163'),
    ('174', 'Cloud Platform Services From .Net to .Net Core', 'This epic''s scope is to discover the effort need to move聽services that are part of the cloud platform d to AWS. In order to do this any services that are .NET must migrate to .NET Core in order to be "Fargate Compatible"This work is very specific to the codebase it is being done on and as such we will need the involved teams to do their own discovery on the amount of work required.', 296, 2, 5, '#069de2', null, null, null, null, null, null, 5, 5, null, null, 'CLP-1122'),
    ('175', 'Dockerization of Cloud Platform Services', 'This epic is to get services that support the Direct/Office cloud platform running in docker containers so they can be moved to AWS', 405, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 3, 0, '13', 'Cloud on Public Cloud (AWS)', 'CLP-1125'),
    ('178', 'Security API GUID Changes', '+Background:+聽We identified a need to assign a common identifier in the for GUID and replace the existing/old internal identifiers. The change is applicable to client accounts, Model portfolios, temp accounts and Client securities.聽聽+Business Use case:+聽To reduce the anxiety and help users migrate their list from Desktop apps to Direct web(Office & cloud)聽Scope of Change聽 # In security API calls always return type of GUID when a request is passed with GUID ID''s # When user passes GUID IDs in the request for /security API, then pass back ONLY GUID IDs. This is so we can drive adoption of GUID ID. Make sure that this feature is easily turned on and off just in case this breaks something for one of our users # If the user makes a screening request, return GUID as the row id instead of old ID''s (e.g. ZZ IDs).聽聽聽', 743, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-1113'),
    ('179', 'When I''m in the grid, I would like to see more than 50 columns at a time', 'AC: * User is able to add up to XX columns ** limit based on spike ** API limit is 500 for &lt;5,000 rows * Alerts are updated with proper limit * Interactions remain the same ** currently, if user has 49 columns and adds a bundle or "add all" option, no columns are added * Enhance limitation to include rolling windows ** If data setting would push user over limit, show alert * Enhance limitation to include dynamic ranking columns ** If adding dynamic ranking would push user over limit, show alert聽Current Stats from 3xHere is column stats for Investment List and Data set:|*# of columns*|# of Investment Lists|# of Data sets||*1 ~ 10*|136547|85966||*10 ~ 50*|754145|154057||*50 ~ 100*|154023|30937||*100 ~ 500*|37956|17176||*More than 500*|228|75||*Avg*|32|30||*Max*|970|996||*Limit*|1000|1000|聽APIv2 Limit Info From Donglin:|*Use case*|*number of investment*|*number of columns count each time period as 1 column*||charting|less than 50|less than 91250 =365 day*50 year*5 datapoint||grid|less than 5000|less than 500|!image-2018-05-02-14-24-22-188.png!聽聽!image-2018-05-02-14-25-31-020.png!', 858, 2, 5, '#ff9867', '2019-07-11T00:00:00', '2019-08-20T00:00:00', null, null, null, null, 104, 29, null, null, 'CLP-511'),
    ('180', 'Include portfolio number in DWM/DAM workflow', 'We received a request from Merrill Lynch to see their internal model identifiers in the product. These identifiers are imported as the "Portfolio Number".聽This information is currently available in the AccountMaster table (AccountNumber field), as well as through the portfolio API. However, it is not surfaced anywhere in the product.This epic is to surface Portfolio Number in the appropriate places throughout the DWM/DAM workflow.', 496, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-1038'),
    ('181', 'CLP - Increase AC data update frequency', 'Improve the ability for AC to respond to missing/updated data in our upstream sources.1) Decrease the re-indexing timeframe, esp. for RT data2) Add ability to re-index ad-hoc, in between scheduled runs.', 320, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-1023'),
    ('182', 'CLP - Integrate Bond ID Search with One Search Framework', 'Integrate the Bond ID Search created by Subash and team into the One Search Framework.1) Definition of business requirements2) Analysis of tech integration requirements3) Integration, QA, UAT4) Delivery to Cloud', 321, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-1022'),
    ('183', 'Expand Benchmark Type Selections for MPT Data Points', 'For any MPT statistic (Alpha, Batting Average, Beta, Correlation, Downside Capture Ratio, Excess Return, Information Ration, Sharpe Ratio, R2, Tracking Error, Treynor Ratio, Upside Capture Ratio) that is reliant on a benchmark, a user can only manually select the benchmark - which is very tedious - or select only one benchmark type (Morningstar Category Primary Benchmark). This makes these data points unusable if a user has a large list of funds that all have different benchmarks and they want these data points calculated against another Benchmark Type (Prospectus Primary Benchmark, as an example). Throughout the rest of the platform, in various components when selecting a benchmark we''re giving users a number of choices ''By Relevancy'':* Best Fit Index* ETF Index Proxy* Morningstar Category Average* Morningstar Category Index* Manager Preferred Benchmark* Primary Prospectus BenchmarkWe should allow these same benchmark types to be applied to the MPT data points outlined above within column set management. The immediate ask is to focus on only getting these into the grid. As part of the acceptance criteria, we should make it clear to a user which benchmark is being used to calculate the data point in cases. For example, if I were to add two Alpha data points in my grid, one using Prospectus Primary Benchmark and one using Category Average, I should be able to tell which data point is which. If we need to prioritize the types that are added and do it in phases we can certainly do that. I would view Prospectus Primary Benchmark as the most important.', 429, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-948'),
    ('184', 'Component Broadcasting', 'As a user, I need the ability to change a setting in one location and have that applied to multiple components on the worksheet so I don''t have to do duplicative work. (This will also lead to investigating ability to change component settings across entire workbook)Our users have expressed that they don''t want to continue to have to change settings multiple times in various components.聽 For example, time period, benchmark, currency are all settings that are commonly shared.We need to work through some technical concerns so in this first phase we just wanted to focus on broadcasting settings to multiple components on a worksheet.聽 Phase 2 we would address how to broadcast a setting across an entire worksheet.聽', 348, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-883'),
