    ('189', 'Cloudy Portfolios - Edit Transactions', '*What this action is required?*A user often needs to edit transactions imported into Office because the data imported is incorrect. These edits are important because they can affect performance calculations and management fee calculations.For example, a dividend payment transaction is imported after the security paying the dividend was sold in the account. This delayed dividend causes performance errors. To fix, the user must edit the date of the distribution (dividend) transaction to match the date of the sale of the security.聽*How can a user edit transactions?*A user can edit a transaction by: * Opening 鈥淐lient & Accounts鈥?workbook. * Highlighting an account under a client record. * Clicking on the 鈥淭ransactions鈥?component. * Hover over the transaction and click the down arrow. * Select Edit. * Make changes in the 鈥淓dit Transaction鈥?dialogue window that appears. * Clicking Save*Acceptance Criteria* * After a user clicks Save, the components listed below should update within 5 seconds. * While the data updates, the user should be able to navigate to other areas of the program. * Components or pages that require updates to calculations should display a spinning wheel so that the user does not confuse old data as updated data. Selective blocking or asynchronous updates are acceptable. * Account level and client level components must update within 5 seconds. * Practice level components/data should update with nightly batch calculation process. * Components ** Transactions 鈥?Account Level ** Historical Return 鈥?Account and Client Level ** Market Value 鈥?Account and Client Level ** Account Analysis 鈥?Account and Client Level ** _MPT Statistics 鈥?Account and Client Level_ *** _If affected_ ** _Scatter Plot 鈥?Account and Client Level_ *** _If affected_ ** _Holdings Plot 鈥?Account and Client Level_ *** _If affected_ ** Client Grid 鈥?Account and Client Level *** Market Value column ** Practice Performance Activity 鈥?Practice Level *** Market Value line *** Cumulative Contributions line ** Allocation Components - Account and Client Level *** If affected. * After updates are completed, reports run should reflect changes. ** Reports Affected *** Client Billing Summary *** Client Position Summary *** Client Return Summary *** Performance by Security *** Performance Summary *** Snapshot *** Trade Activities *** Portfolio Unrealized Gains/Losses*Additional Details*Please document all APIs involved for spec document.聽聽聽', 80, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, '17', 'Office Cloud - AWS Batch (Cloudy)', 'CLP-1063'),
