    ('195', 'Grid Loading Prototype Phase 1', '*Grid Loading Problems:* -The user has no idea what their experience result will be or why the result is different with different settings -User does not know which combinations of settings slow performance -User does not know difference between marted and dynamically calculated data points -Editing a data point setting can change a marted data point to dynamically calculated -Combination of settings come from multiple places in the app -User can get to a dead end based on functionality we offer today -One user performing expensive calculations can cause instability for all Cloud users today.*Goal:* - Provide a predictable, acceptable, and stable grid loading user experience across the 鈥渟uccess鈥?spectrum (both under and over 7 seconds*).Keys to the prototype: * Demonstrate that a user can close their browser while waiting for data with DR, SS, or SC enabled, open the workbook later, and see the data that they were waiting for * Demonstrate that a user can wait past the current timeout period while waiting for data with DR, SS, or SC enabled, and the data will eventually show up * Demonstrate the difference between returning to a workbook with and without cached data (cached vs. refresh on open) * Demonstrate that a workbook with "stale" cached data must be fully refreshed when a data point is added/updated * Demonstrate that a workbook with "fresh" cached data only, only needs to ask for the new data, and not refresh all dataNot keys to the prototype: * Progress bar * Differences in the "short", "medium", and "long" waiting treatments * Recovery from a "never saved" workbook * potential changes in workbook section of File Management * Any tool tips, popups, helper text, etc. * Notification optionsThis prototype is to support the following workflows: * Updates to loading columns ** When a user adds or edits a column, only the columns that are added or updated should be refreshed ** When a user adds or changes grouping, only the grouping data points are requested.聽 Then the UI will become grouped. ** When a user changes Dynamic Ranking settings, only the ranking columns that are affected will be requested ** When any columns are added or updated, whether due to data points or Dynamic Ranking, a column will immediately be created at the proper spot, and then filled in when the data is retrieved. ** A user must be able to refresh all data at any time.聽 When that happens, all data is requested and loaded * Caching and retrieving cached data (only for saved workbooks when DR, SS, or SC are enabled) ** Every time a user updates data points or PA settings, the full data set is cached somewhere where it can be retrieved later. ** The data needs to be cached even if the user closes the browser before the data has been聽returned ** This data set will also contain the version of the grid inputs the last time the user clicked "done" or "apply" (PA, List, Column Set) ** It will also contain the date when it was last saved ** When a user opens a workbook that co', 460, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 24, 8, null, null, 'CLP-1011'),
