    ('200', 'Updates for handling proxy securities', 'In certain cases, clients may hold investments that Morningstar does not track. In this case, oftentimes users want to approximate the allocation and performance of that investment by using a ''proxy''.Merrill Lynch is doing this for their private SMA and bond data.Today in the product, we surface proxies by showing the raw, imported name of the unrecognized holding, along with the Morningstar data of the proxy. This is a little misleading. For example, in the screenshot below, Morningstar has not give the private SMA (ATLTANTA CAPITAL SMID CORE) a bronze rating, the rating belongs to the proxy. However, this is not clear to the user. !screenshot-1.png|thumbnail! *Design from component team*: !screenshot-2.png|thumbnail! And for the portfolio editor search: !screenshot-3.png|thumbnail!', 836, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 22, 22, null, null, 'CLP-870'),
