    ('206', 'Apply TRX model to more Office Cloud module', 'For the user who have both TRX and OC permission, user can post model portfolio from TRX to OC.聽 Then OC聽show TRX Model portfolio in File management&gt;Model Portfolio list, we will apply TRX Model to other fields in OC: # Model Portfolio Workbook, and Client/Account workbook&gt;compare with model worksheet; # Component Setting&gt;select a model portfolio # Client/Account setting&gt;setup model portfolio; # Save as another new model; # Report&gt;Current vs model report; # PS Workbook setting&gt;select a model portfolio; # Add notes to a Model Portfolio. # Planning*+API wiki:+*聽[https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/SWDO/Import+TRX+models+to+Office+Cloud+-+API]STG: [jean.jing@morningstar.com|mailto:jean.jing@morningstar.com]聽!Model List.png|thumbnail!聽聽', 46, 5, 2, '#F0A509', '2019-05-30T00:00:00', '2019-07-10T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud - Jun-Jul 2019', '2019-05-30T00:00:00', '2019-07-10T00:00:00', 20, 20, '78', 'Office Cloud - Model Marketplace Data Integration', 'CLP-1164'),
    ('207', 'As an office cloud user, I would like to customize viewed results in the Clients & Accounts Grid', '{color:#d04437}*Problem:*{color}聽Currently, there is no way for users to customize the results seen in Client & Accounts grid. This means users are seeing a lot of extra noise that might not pertain to their workflow聽 when they open the Client&Account grid. The follow are the two most common聽 聽 聽 {color:#de350b}聽*Issue 1:*{color} (all users)聽 currently the Clients & Accounts grid shows all Client/Accounts entered into the user database.聽 This list will include active clients as well as inactive clients. (see def below).聽 Although there is metadata indication if a client is active or not, the user has no way to focus this grid view on active users only.聽 聽 聽 聽{color:#de350b}*Issue 2:*{color} (Admins) Admins see ALL clients/accounts across the firm.聽 Some Admin workflows require them to focus on a list of clients for one particular advisor.聽聽 Although there is metadata indication on advisor, the admin has no way to focus this grid view on a single advisor book at a time.聽{color:#172b4d}*Definitions:*{color}聽+{color:#205081}Active Flag:{color}+ This is a client who is actively working with the advisor. The advisor is providing services & billing this client.聽 This client would be part of any practice analysis the advisor ran.+Inactive Flag+: This is a client who once did business with the advisor, but has discontinued the business relationship.聽 The advisor no longer actively reports, bills or provides advice to this client, but for compliance reasons, must keep that Client''s data on file for 5-7 years after the relationship has ended. This client would not be included in any current practice analysis, but the advisor would include this data in any audits that included past years.聽*Target:* All Office Cloud Users*Dependencies:* Office Cloud, DOPA (API work should be complete)聽聽{color:#172b4d}+*ACs:*+{color}*As an OC user, I would like a way to easily distinguish between inactive & active clients in the Client & Account area, so that I can quickly focus on my active clients when performing daily workflows.* # As a user, I聽 set clients who no longer do business with me to inactive because ## for compliance reasons, I do not want their records and history deleted from OC ## 聽I don''t want these clients in my daily views on my practice, reports, etc. # In most instances, I am only interested in seeing my active client list, as my daily workflow revolves around them. Therefor, I would like the option to default my Client & Account grid view to reflect only active clients. # There may be occasions when i need to see a list of my inactive clients, so i need a way to view all the Clients i have marked as inactive.聽 ## Example of this may be audits or is an old client comes back with a claim/complaint/etc. ## I am also need to find an inactive Client back to active if i start doing business with them again. # Because I may be approached by legal/compliance questions...... # Determine best way to label active/inactive Clients in Office Cloud # User still needs', 42, 5, 2, null, '2019-07-11T00:00:00', '2019-08-21T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud - Jul-Aug 2019', '2019-07-11T00:00:00', '2019-08-21T00:00:00', 0, 0, '18', 'Office Cloud - Client & Account Analytics', 'CLP-1161'),
