    ('211', 'Design for Groups Phase 2', 'Continuation from Discovery & User stories created in epic CLP-736.聽*How will it help our goals?* This will add additional parity for 3x users, aiding in the migration goal. (Many users already have Groups they have build to report on).聽 It will also expand functionality options for brand new users looking at Morningstar Office.*Target:* All Office Cloud users who use the system for any kind of reporting to their clients*Dependencies:*聽 OC, DOPA, Maybe PS*ACs:*As an Advisor/Admin, I need the ability to group accounts to help make reporting easier.As an Advisor/Admin, I need the ability to run performance reports on Groups so that I can use them for reporting scenarios that do not fit within the normal Client organization structure. * Ad Hoc Report Generation * adding Group to Batch Schedule * Filtering Reports by Group * "Reporting Client" options for Group聽*Unknowns* * Where else does CRUD Groups need to be accessed if report generation is added to actions? ** is there any connection/impact to OC-3032? * how does this impact naming/labels used for Groups?聽', 386, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-1092'),
    ('213', 'Additional Data API v2 Endpoints for Batching', 'CWP needs the following API endpoints batched to provide performance improvements to end users:|Endpoint|API level|settings level||performanceData|portfolio|portfolio||returnAnalysis|portfolio|portfolio聽||cumulativeContribution|portfolio|portfolio聽||frequencyReturnSeries|portfolio|portfolio聽||marketValueSeries|portfolio|portfolio聽||assetAllocation|portfolio|portfolio聽|聽*Request:*聽For first 6 APIs listed, enable portfolio level settings in addition to client level settings', 211, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-1046'),
