    ('215', 'Grid Loading Prototype Phase 2', 'Next Phases of prototype that will potentially contribute to more fluidly connecting the workflow: * Progress bar * Differences in the "short" (phase 1), "medium" (phase 2), and "long" (phase 3) waiting treatments * Any tool tips, popups, helper text, etc. * Notification optionsHigh Level Requirements: * When a user opens a workbook that contains cached data, the cached data will be loaded and displayed * A user sees if the data is cached and outside of the freshold. * If the user sees the grid is outside the freshold, they have the option to refresh the whole grid without having to go into PA or CSM.聽 * If cached data is loaded, and it is less than 24 hours old,聽if a user makes any changes to PA or column set, only the changed/added columns are requested * If cached data is loaded, and it is more than 24 hours old, if a user makes any changes to PA or column set, all data is requested * If the user refreshes the grid or sets up a new grid and clicks done/apply, they then see progress in the grid in different stages: ** the user immediately sees that the grid is loading ** the user then has some idea of how long the grid loading is going to take to complete ** the user knows their options for continuing to work if the grid is going to take longer to load. * The user has the option to cancel the grid loading calculation. If they cancel the calculation, they do not lose the previously calculated data.聽 * The user has the option to refresh the grid at any time, regardless of whether the grid data is considered fresh or not.聽聽', 461, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 19, 8, null, null, 'CLP-1036'),
