    ('221', 'Design for Security/Holding Settings', 'h2. Main documentation lives under Epic: CLP-1180*UX link:*聽[https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/SENROM05URT#/316930042_01_Cover]聽聽*Visual Spec:*聽https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/Y8NROTH23RS#/316931675_01_SPC-Cover_h2. *+Security Settings+*h3. *Exclude Securities from Performance (by Practice)**_As an advisor, I need the ability to excluded securities from performance calculations in order to properly report client/account returns to my clients._*|*3.X Name*||Settings > Preferences > Exclude Securities 聽||*What does this do?*||Allows the user to control customizations made on securities in the practice & in they are included in the return calculations on the reports they generate for their clients. 聽 For additional information go to [portfolio accounting setting impact|https://morningstaronline-my.sharepoint.com/:x:/g/personal/kristen_carstensen_morningstar_com/EcQ3pvXmYnhEkuma8K6Hp30BL_9xPDGNuEq4lvU_SpCQIQ?e=vfTnb9] 聽**聽||*Why do we have this?*||Allows the user to control customizations made of securities in the practice so that they can set preferences that impact the entire practice. 聽||*What does the user need in OC?*|| - 聽聽聽聽聽聽聽聽 Determine where & how these exclusion preferences should be accessed - 聽聽聽聽聽聽聽聽 *The ability to globally exclude a security from performance calculations when running returns on Clients or Accounts* o聽聽 Anytime any account in my practice hold "security x" it will automatically be excluded from performance calculation when I run performance reports for any of the clients in my practice. o聽聽 This is a blanket rule, setting applies to all, no exceptions o聽聽 As default I would like to see a list of securities held in the account to make my exclusion selection from o聽聽 In cases where I have liquidated a security mid- performance period, I need the option to view liquidated securities in order to make an exclusion election if necessary. 聽|聽h2. *+Holding Settings+*h3. *Exclude Holdings from Performance (by Account)**_As an advisor, I need the ability to excluded holdings from performance calculations in order to properly report client/account performance to my clients._*|*3.X Name*||Settings > Preferences > Exclude Securities 聽||*What does this do?*||Allows the user to control customizations made on securities in the practice & in they are included in the return calculations on the reports they generate for their clients. 聽 For additional information go to [portfolio accounting setting impact|https://morningstaronline-my.sharepoint.com/:x:/g/personal/kristen_carstensen_morningstar_com/EcQ3pvXmYnhEkuma8K6Hp30BL_9xPDGNuEq4lvU_SpCQIQ?e=vfTnb9] 聽**聽||*Why do we have this?*||Allows the user to control customizations made of securities in the practice so that they can set preferences that impact the entire practice. 聽||*What does the user need in OC?*|| - 聽聽聽聽聽聽聽聽 Determine where & how these exclusion preferences should be accessed - 聽聽聽聽聽聽聽聽 *the ability to exclude a security held in a specific account from perfo', 51, 5, 2, null, '2019-05-30T00:00:00', '2019-07-10T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud - Jun-Jul 2019', '2019-05-30T00:00:00', '2019-07-10T00:00:00', 0, 0, '58', 'Office Cloud - Portfolio Accounting Settings', 'CLP-1191'),
