    ('245', 'Unsupported Data Types', 'This may need to be broken down into several stories, but there are a few data types that are still not supported in the Grid. # *Random date, two random values* ** Example: Share Split 鈥?On a random date, we need to communicate a "From" value and a "To" value: "On X date there was a split from 1.00 to 3.00" ** This may be considered in "Map Structure" since split type and several dates will be included ** 3x solution shown below: ** !image-2017-11-22-14-24-50-322.png! ** !image-2017-11-22-14-25-18-478.png! # *Random date range, random text string* ** Example: Manager History (note: not in v2 yet) ** !image-2017-11-22-14-27-06-590.png! ** !image-2017-11-22-14-27-35-445.png! ** SAL Solution:  !image-2018-04-26-18-34-58-154.png! # *Map Structure* ** Example1: Fee Schedule *** 3x solution: separate columns; all the way to 9th breakpoint. *** !image-2017-11-22-14-36-11-414.png! ** Example2: Distribution *** 3x solution: individual columns *** Can be one map or multiple *** Data from v2: *** {noformat}{"m": {"RecordDate": "20151218","EffectiveReinvestPrice": "NULL","ExcludingDate": "20151221","ReinvestmentDate": "20151221","FrankedAmount": "NULL","CurrencyId": "USD","PayDate": "20151222","Value": "0.20628","TaxRate": "NULL","FrankedRate": "NULL","FrankedCredit": "NULL","DeclareDate": "NULL","DistributionType": "2"}{noformat} *  ** Example3: Qual/Quant (GCS-12) ** Example4: Extended Performance *** Requires work from APIv2 to move EP flag to map structure for GS to use for visual treatment *** 3x solution: italics when a number represents extended performance', 829, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'GCS-24'),
    ('246', 'Design for: Additional Account Settings', 'Main document for project can be found in Epic CLP-1180*Visual Desgin:*聽[https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/EDN181GTCM6#/316926084_Setting-A2]h2. *+Account Settings:+*h3. *Aggregate Options**_As an Office Cloud portfolio accounting user, I need the following settings to be supported in Office Cloud so that I can properly customize reports I share with my clients._*聽*_As a Desktop Office user migrating to Office Cloud, I need the following setting to be supported in Office Cloud so I can seamless continue my portfolio accounting workflows in Office Cloud._*聽**聽 * Each of the below setting are customizable at the account level (Account Settings) ** This includes Quick & Transactional Accounts * Each setting is independent of one another. * Each setting is either selected or not. * By default, each of these settings = No * Setting preferences made in Office 3X should reflect in Office Cloud聽聽 **聽聽聽**聽|*3.X Setting Name*||_Exclude Account from Client Aggregate_ 聽__聽||*What does this setting do?*||Account will not be included in any actions initiated from the Client Level up. This includes: - 聽聽聽聽聽聽聽聽 Asset Under Management reports - 聽聽聽聽聽聽聽聽 Billing calculations - 聽聽聽聽聽聽聽聽 Reporting done on the client or practice level 聽 For additional information go to [portfolio accounting setting impact|https://morningstaronline-my.sharepoint.com/:x:/g/personal/kristen_carstensen_morningstar_com/EcQ3pvXmYnhEkuma8K6Hp30BL_9xPDGNuEq4lvU_SpCQIQ?e=vfTnb9] 聽**聽||*Why do we have this setting?*||Users want to be able to run individual ad hoc actions on an account but doesn''t want it to be part of workflow output done on the client or practice level.||*What does the user need in OC?*|| - 聽聽聽聽聽聽聽聽 The ability to select the option at the account level - 聽聽聽聽聽聽聽聽 Content/Labeling to help them understand what the selection does - 聽聽聽聽聽聽聽聽 Visual differentiator when viewing this account in Client & Account Grid - 聽聽聽聽聽聽聽聽 Visual indi