    ('277', 'Mercer - Strategies and Track Records', '*+Create Note+** * Tag a note to a strategy (strategy id) -* Tag a note to a track record (performance id) -{color:red}no longer in scope {color}* Track records have a strategy id that allows us to aggregate all track records that roll up into a strategy id * Search for strategies and track records (in tag field) * Share a note that is tagged to a strategy-{color:red} or track record {color}-* Auto-tag to notes when in the grid *+Notes Component +*- Return and display notes that are tagged to strategy -{color:red}and track records{color}- in notes component * Investment Analysis workbooks: if a strategy {color:red}-or track record-{color} is in focus, return all notes that are tagged to that strategy {color:red}-and/or track record -{color}* If the user has a strategy in focus, return the notes tagged to that strategy (strategy level) a{color:red}-nd also return any notes that are tagged to any of the track records that link to that strategy (performance ids) &gt;&gt; there is a strategy id for track records and that strategy id is the link  -{color}* If a user asks for strategy level only, only return notes tagged to strategy level (do not include track record) * -{color:red}If a user asks for track record only, only return notes tagged to that strategy鈥檚 track records  * If the user has a track record in focus, return the notes tagged to that track record  - don鈥檛 return notes tagged to the strategy level (should validate this and see if it鈥檚 different than what we have today) {color}- OUT OF SCOPE: _APIs are not built to support this in phase 1_* Model portfolio workbooks:  a user can have a model portfolio that holdings are strategies and/or track records * If a model portfolio is in focus: (in addition to what we return today), also return any notes that are tagged to a strategy or track record that is held in that model as a holding * This is similar to what we do today for underlying holdings but we will need to be able to include strategy ids, performance ids for track records * Dependency: We would need an API that returns all holdings of model portfolios 鈥?so not just investments but also these strategies (strategy id) and or track records (performance id) as holdings as well 鈥? *+Dependencies:  +** API that returns model portfolios that have strategies (strategy id) and or track records (performance id) as holdings?  * Both the Mercer and Morningstar strategies and track records will have a strategy id (confirmed) * Both Mercer and Morningstar track records will have a performance id(confirmed) * Entitlement and sharing &gt;&gt; need to know if all users will have the same entitlement in a firm * Need to know the strategy id/performance id when in the grid for auto-tag (confirmed, will be available) *+ALERTS +** We do not have alerts that can be set or triggered at the strategy level yet so until then, we need to make sure that we aren鈥檛 allowing users to set alerts on strategies indirectly through the grid or first time set up modal *', 108, 5, 2, null, '2019-05-30T00:00:00', '2019-07-10T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud - Jun-Jul 2019', '2019-05-30T00:00:00', '2019-07-10T00:00:00', 11, 11, '11', 'Release Mercer Performance, Operations, and Portfolio Data in Cloud', 'NERTS-282'),
