    ('307', 'Design for Assigning Clients to Report Objects', '*Problem:* as we have developed features like upload outside documents (CLP-805)& Groups (CLP-736), there are now instances where a report object (pdf being the most common) are associated with more than on Client. Users need a way to manage how these report objects are associated with a Client(s), especially since it has impact to sharign via the Web Portal.*How will this help our goals*: creating more developed behaviors with OC regarding reporting, will allow us to provide more robust reporting option to our users. This will support the goal to migrate 3x users who already have the ability to edit clients associated with a report.聽 By not just adding, but improving how these behaviors work in OC it will encourage migration & the sale of new users. (since another goal is to make OC a more well rounded portfolio accounting system)聽*ACs:**As an Office Cloud user, I need the ability to add or remove clients assigned to a report or uploaded document so that I can organize my files and share relevant information with my clients.*聽 * I would like to assign new clients to a file * I would like to remove assigned clients from a file * When I publish a report that has multiple clients assigned, I would like to publish the report to the web portals of all assigned clients ** When I add clients to a report that has already been published, I would like to publish the report to the newly added clients'' web portals ** When I remove clients from a report that has already been published, I would like to remove the report from those removed clients'' web portals * When I remove a report from the web portal that has multiple clients assigned, I would like to remove the report from the web portals of all assigned clients * In the Reports grid, I would like to see how many clients a file is assigned to ** If I change the number of clients assigned, I want the grid to be updated to show that information * For files that have no clients assigned, I should not be able to publish to the web portal * For published reports with multiple clients assigned, I should not be able to "View in Client Web Portal"*Out of Scope* * Dealing with "View in Client Web Portal" for files assigned to multiple clients聽聽*UX InVision link:* [https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/A7NRNWD4DSX]聽聽', 93, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, 'Cloud - Nov-Dec 2019', '2019-11-14T00:00:00', '2019-12-25T00:00:00', 0, 0, '241', 'Office Cloud - Report Management', 'OC-3810'),
