    ('313', 'Design for Upload Documents -Phase 2', '*Problem:* currently office cloud users have no way of included customized materials made outside of Office Cloud (like Newsletters) in the pdf reports they are generating for their clients.聽 Many time advisor may have a third party that helps them create market update newsletters and such. Advisors like these items to be included in the pdf generated during batching reporting so it makes the report presented to their clients look cohesive/ professional.*How will this help out goals?* This feature would help make Office Cloud a more well rounded reporting tool and well as help in 3x migration efforts (since this feature is available in current 3x).聽 This should benefit the goal of new sales & migration.*Target:* All Office Cloud Users*Dependencies:* Office Cloud Squad*ACs:**As an Office Cloud user, I need the ability to add an outside document into my batch schedule so that I can included customized material made outside of Office (like newsletters) within the reports I share with my clients.* * I would like to add an outside document to a new Batch Schedule I am creating ** I should be able document I already uploaded via the Reports area ** If I am an Admin user creating a batch, I should be able to choose from any uploaded document myself, or any other user int he firm has uploaded. * I would like to add an outside document to a Batch Schedule I have already created (edit) ** I should be able document I already uploaded via the Reports area ** If I am an Admin user creating a batch, I should be able to choose from any uploaded document myself, or any other user int he firm has uploaded. * I would like the option of adding a document to an existing batch, during the time of Upload ** _did we review this idea with tech already? I know it was disused in Chicago at one point._ ** _This is nice to have until we explore some more of the unknowns._ * I would like to have some customization options when it comes to order in which the document appears in the batch. I would like the following options at minimum: *  ** first page of batch ( after cover page if cover page is selected) ** last page of batch*Unknowns* * Would i need the ability to upload a document while Create/Editing a batch? Given that flow is a modal is it even possible right now? May have to consider if this should be in scope or not. * from a technical side, do we have to limit doc types attached to Batch to pdfs only? * Do users need to attach more than one document to a batch?聽 How often does this happen & Why? ** If we allow, how does this impact setting the order of appearance?*Out of Scope* * Any uploading document workflows that are outside the focus of Batch Schedules * Depending on investigation of Unknowns: adding more than one outside doc.聽 I am not confident there is a strong use case here to have to include it in this round of design.*What is considered done?*User has at least one mean of included an outside document in a Batch Schedule. OK limiting the scope of thsi work ', 94, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 3, 0, '241', 'Office Cloud - Report Management', 'OC-3654'),
