    ('317', 'Design for: Customizing viewed results in the Clients & Accounts Grid', '{color:#d04437}*Problem:*{color}聽Currently, there is no way for users to customize the results seen in Client & Accounts grid. This means users are seeing a lot of extra noise that might not pertain to their workflow聽 when they open the Client&Account grid. The follow are the two most common聽 聽 聽 {color:#de350b}聽*Issue 1:*{color} (all users)聽 currently the Clients & Accounts grid shows all Client/Accounts entered into the user database.聽 This list will include active clients as well as inactive clients. (see def below).聽 Although there is metadata indication if a client is active or not, the user has no way to focus this grid view on active users only.聽 聽 聽 聽{color:#de350b}*Issue 2:*{color} (Admins) Admins see ALL clients/accounts across the firm.聽 Some Admin workflows require them to focus on a list of clients for one particular advisor.聽聽 Although there is metadata indication on advisor, the admin has no way to focus this grid view on a single advisor book at a time.聽{color:#172b4d}*Definitions:*{color}聽+{color:#205081}Active Flag:{color}+ This is a client who is actively working with the advisor. The advisor is providing services & billing this client.聽 This client would be part of any practice analysis the advisor ran.+Inactive Flag+: This is a client who once did business with the advisor, but has discontinued the business relationship.聽 The advisor no longer actively reports, bills or provides advice to this client, but for compliance reasons, must keep that Client''s data on file for 5-7 years after the relationship has ended. This client would not be included in any current practice analysis, but the advisor would include this data in any audits that included past years.聽*Target:* All Office Cloud Users*Dependencies:* Office Cloud, DOPA (API work should be complete)聽聽{color:#172b4d}+*ACs:*+{color}*As an OC user, I would like a way to easily distinguish between inactive & active clients in the Client & Account area, so that I can quickly focus on my active clients when performing daily workflows.* # As a user, I聽 set clients who no longer do business with me to inactive because ## for compliance reasons, I do not want their records and history deleted from OC ## 聽I don''t want these clients in my daily views on my practice, reports, etc. # In most instances, I am only interested in seeing my active client list, as my daily workflow revolves around them. Therefor, I would like the option to default my Client & Account grid view to reflect only active clients. # There may be occasions when i need to see a list of my inactive clients, so i need a way to view all the Clients i have marked as inactive.聽 ## Example of this may be audits or is an old client comes back with a claim/complaint/etc. ## I am also need to find an inactive Client back to active if i start doing business with them again. # Because I may be approached by legal/compliance questions...... # Determine best way to label active/inactive Clients in Office Cloud # User still needs', 390, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'OC-3032'),
    ('318', '[Sustainability] Existing UI Sanity testing automation maintain', '# Generate current vs model report for prospect # Run Snapshot report for prospect and it''s account# Run Current vs model report for client and it''s account # Existing UI test cases maintenance', 148, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, '151', 'Office Cloud Sustainability items - 2019', 'OC-2966'),
    ('319', 'Client Report Name & Address', '*{color:#de350b}Problem:{color}*聽 Office users typically fill in the Client Name field for internal use workflows. Using _Last name, First name_ formats, or legal titles that make the custodian records.聽 This Client Name format is not always the ideal way advisors would like to display names for client facing materials.聽 They prefer something more human and something less formal.{color:#de350b}*Goals:*{color}聽 This will play a major part in helping with overall migration goals.聽 Many users have been inquiring about it because they depend on it for their quarterly reporting.聽 Many Cloud only users have also started to make use of this concept from desktop, so it will make new sales happier as well.*Dependencies*: OC, Design, DBA, DOPA? * Current Office Desktop Usersh3. {color:#de350b}*AC*{color}*AC1: As a user, I don''t always want the Client Name to be what displays on client facing material.聽 I would like the ability to set a separate聽 name to display on client facing materials such as client reports.* # As default, the聽 Client Name is what populates on reports ## When that is the case, any time i update the Client Name, the name that displays on the reports should update as well. # I would like an option to opt out of using Client Name on reports ## when i opt out of using Client Name, I should be prompted to enter my alternative name to display on reports ## At any point if i change the report name, that change should reflect the next time I run a report for that client. ## If I have opted out of using Client Name on reports, no changes made to the Client Name will impact what i see when i generate a report for the client.*AC2: As a user, I don''t always want the main address in the Client Profile to be what displays on client facing material.聽 I would like the ability to set a separate聽 address to display on client facing materials such as client reports.* # As default, the聽 Client Profile address is what populates on reports ## When that is the case, any time I update the Client Profile address, the address that displays on the reports should update as well. # I would like an option to opt out of using Client Profile address on reports ## when i opt out of using Client Name, I should be prompted to pick one of two options: ### to enter my alternative address to display on reports #### If I want to enter an alternative address, these are the optional fields provided: ##### Address 1 ##### Address 2 ##### City ##### State ##### Zip ##### Country/Region? ### to not display any address on a report ## At any point if i change the Client Profile address, that change should reflect the next time I run a report for that client. ## If I have opted out of using Client Profile address on reports, no changes made to the Client Profile address will impact what i see when I generate a report for the client.*AC3: As a desktop user, I would like my Client Report Name preferences to carry over to Office Cloud so that my workflows are not disrupted when I upgra', 36, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 6, 6, '58', 'Office Cloud - Portfolio Accounting Settings', 'DCV-4873'),
    ('320', 'Build Tool to Verify Report Data', 'We need to make our report data accuracy, and let this testing automated in each release.Scope:all office cloud standard reports.*Solution:*1. In QA stage, compare report data xml between QA and STG.2. In UAT stage, compare report data xml between UAT and Live.3. In QA sign-off day, prepare the report data xml on STG. After STG release, compare the report data xml with the previous xml.4. In UAT sign-off day, prepare the report data xml on Live. After Live release, compare the report data xml with the previous xml.', 281, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'OC-2530'),
