    ('330', 'UMA Sleeve Realloc UX/I Design', 'When an investor opens a multi-strategy (aka UMA) account, s/he will want to make sleeve allocation changes to that account, e.g. change sleeve strategy, sleeve weight or both. Allowing investors to make these changes is one of the benefits of UMA, e.g. money movements inside an account is not a taxable event, thus making strategy changes within a UMA is tax efficient.The goal of this design epic is to create a workflow experience for TAMP advisors to make sleeve allocation changes for a given multi-strategy account.聽*Problem*聽||Question||Example|||What is the problem our users are facing?|When an investor opens a multi-strategy (aka UMA) account, s/he will want to make sleeve allocation changes to that account, e.g. change sleeve strategies, sleeve weight or both. Allowing investors to make these changes is one of the benefits of UMA, e.g. money movements inside an account is not a taxable event, thus making strategy changes within a UMA is tax efficient.||_Who is facing this problem?_|The advisor is facing this problem and needs a way to help his/her investor to reallocate their sleeves.搂聽Donny Jackson, an advisor who is 45 years old and hates technology, need a strategy forward way to help his investor April to reallocate her UMA account. Donny wants to explain the new sleeve allocation, fee to April and ask April to sign off this change.聽||_Why are they facing this problem?_|UMA sleeve change will have a lot of restriction that needs to be the dynamic calculated.聽 e.g. minimus of each sleeve. Fee is dynamically calculated. So it is very hard to use a paper form to make this change.||_How often does the user need this feature/ face this problem?_|often|聽聽*Current Solutions/Background*聽||Question||Example|||Tell us more about the current functionality/workflow of the product. How are we handling things today?|This is a new feature. But a kind of similar as the "Strategy change" of Single Strategy|**聽聽', -1, 2, 5, '#ff9867', null, null, null, 'Managed Portfolios - Q3 2019', '2019-07-01T00:00:00', '2019-09-30T00:00:00', 57, 57, '29', 'UMA (Multi-strategies) MVP', 'MPUMA-2243'),
    ('331', 'Performance Page Enhancements', 'Given that we launched our MVP version of Performance > Returns page on March 7th, 2019, we should be able to make modest data point and table feature enhancements based on user feedback and project priority. The purpose of this feature epic is to capture and track these enhancements.聽In scope * Adding data points to the table where applicable, dependent on data availability in Model API * Adding features to improve the usability of the data table, e.g. freeze first column, freeze h-scroll position when sorting, export, etc. * Improving layout of page features, e.g. removing unnecessary white space, reposition certain UI features, etc.Out of scope * Anything outside of this page', -1, 5, 5, '#046895', null, null, null, 'Managed Portfolios - Q3 2019', '2019-07-01T00:00:00', '2019-09-30T00:00:00', 27, 24, '99', 'MPS Factsheet Migration', 'MPUMA-2165'),
