    ('338', 'Enhance Cash Management', 'Investment team (Sp. Select Equity PMs) wants to use cash-like ETF/MF vehicles in lieu of cash for our Select Equity Portfolios ("SEPs"). This requires changes to how our Optimizer generates positions for our SEPs on a daily basis.Base on discussions with Mike D and Andy Kwon, we''ve determined an approach similar to how SEP+FI portfolios'' holdings are generated. Below are the scope items that the UMA and Red squad will implement based on this approach.h5. Scope (not final)||No.||Scope||Ownership|||1|Tech Design|Red & UMA||2|Update Optimizer database to save and update cash like holdings data for SEPs|Red||3|Update logic that generates the file for Fiserv (note, need to determine if this is covered as part of scope 2)|Red||4|Update logic that generates the file for daily (end of day) batch import to Direct 3.x FTP (mim admin account)|Red||5|Update logic that generates the file for daily (beginning of day) batch import to Direct Cloud聽(mim.us admin/service account)|UMA||6|UI for Traders to provide Cash allocation for SEPs|UMA|聽', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 16, 0, null, null, 'MPUMA-1358'),
    ('339', 'Fee Service Foundation', 'Work will include - * Develop framework for the MP apps/tools to access our fee data via a fee service using AWS infrastructure, e.g. API Gateway, Lambdas, Terraform... * Dynamo DB setup for sleeve fees * Fees API to retrieve fees from MIS API for single strategy using user id from user profile. User id will be input to fees API * Fees API will Calculate fees based on model allocation passed as input params to service and retrieve static fees element from user profile * Setup Account fees in MIS_FISERV * Setup UMA product in Stars', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'MPUMA-1253'),
    ('340', 'UMA Proposal Workflow - foundation', 'The epic is done when MVP functional and non-functional features are done and promoted to the production environment. The MVP features should allow an advisor to use the US TAMP advisor portal''s UI to create a multi-strategy proposal, sans proposal PDF. More info and ACs can be found in the linked [wiki page|https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/MISHOME/UMA+Proposal+Workflow].', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, 'Managed Portfolios - Q3 2019', '2019-07-01T00:00:00', '2019-09-30T00:00:00', 63, 63, '29', 'UMA (Multi-strategies) MVP', 'MPUMA-820'),
