    ('353', 'Custodial Cost Basis Report', '+edit 5/21/2018 - After conversation with Sandeep and Rahul this feature will be a component within Office and not a report.+The purpose of this component is to reconcile the Cost Basis information calculated in Office Cloud using open lots (aka Transactional cost basis) to the Cost Basis information provided by client''s custodians in the form of official custodial Cost Basis files.The addition of the component is part of a larger project of pulling in Custodial Cost Basis Data into Office Cloud to improve Gain/(Loss) reporting as well as providing our rebalancer (TRX) with the most accurate information for Tax Loss Harvesting and trade proposal generation.The advisor can access this component at their discretion to identify differences between the Office Cloud and the custodian then take the necessary steps to correct discrepancies. Steps including updating the transnational cost basis in office to match Custodial cost basis.The report will access data populated in the PASDB tables:PasHoldings_TLPasTaxLotI have attached mockups of a report similar to those used by Office Cloud competitors (Orion and PortfolioCenter) that we would like to convert to a component similar to the "Securities in Practice" component.', 63, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, 'Cloud_Q1 2020', '2019-12-26T00:00:00', '2020-03-18T00:00:00', 0, 0, '102', 'Office Cloud - Cost Basis Improvements', 'CLP-413'),
    ('354', 'Phase 1 - Marting USD Monthly MPT''s', 'We want to pre calculate and store Monthly MPT''s in USD.聽聽It''s extremely beneficial for storing the MPT''s in USD as majority of Direct cloud users base is in U.S a. Here are 2 main advantages # Pre calculating allows users to screen on MPT''s in USD currency聽 # Pre calculating increases the performance of Dynamic ranking. As we want to deliver scheduled batches it will improve performance if a user report has MPT''s in USD聽+Details of work we plan on covering in this epic.+聽 * As this is phase 1 , the Dp''s we planning to cover in this epic are : STD Deviation , Sharpe Ratio(*Morningstar , Arithemtic & Geometric Methodology*) , Alpha, Beta, Tracking Error & Downside Capture Ratio.聽聽For these dp''s we''ll calculate based returns based of Total , Market , Gross based on universe applicability.聽 * For the above mentioned Dp''s we plan on Pre calculating *Monthly*聽MPT''s聽for聽6M, 1Y, 2Y, 3Y, 4Y, 5Y, 7Y, 10Y, 15Y, 20Y timeperiods for annualized and non Annualized. Annualization only applies to timeperiods greater than or equal to聽 1Y. *Check below DP''s to see for what Dp''s annualization applies.*聽 * 聽*I don''t see any EP on and off Dp''s in XOI. Based on that information we can ignore EP*聽 and don''t need to have separate columns for EP * +We will use Mstar Default Benchmark & RiskFree for MPT''s calcs.+聽The Dp''s choosen in phase 1 are聽Current Options in UI:聽聽!image-2018-07-20-09-20-29-522.png!聽聽Here are all the list of Dp''s:聽[PerformanceId] [char](10) NOT NULL, [EndDate] [int] NOT NULL,/* Standard Deviation */[StandardDeviation6Month] [float] SPARSE NULL, [StandardDeviation1Year] [float] SPARSE NULL, [StandardDeviation2Year] [float] SPARSE NULL, [StandardDeviation3Year] [float] SPARSE NULL, [StandardDeviation4Year] [float] SPARSE NULL, [StandardDeviation5Year] [float] SPARSE NULL, [StandardDeviation7Year] [float] SPARSE NULL, [StandardDeviation10Year] [float] SPARSE NULL, [StandardDeviation15Year] [float] SPARSE NULL, [StandardDeviation20Year] [float] SPARSE NULL,鈥?Standard Deviation Annualized [StandardDeviation6MonthAnnualized] [float] SPARSE NULL, [StandardDeviation1YearAnnualized] [float] SPARSE NULL, [StandardDeviation2YearAnnualized] [float] SPARSE NULL, [StandardDeviation3YearAnnualized] [float] SPARSE NULL, [StandardDeviation4YearAnnualized] [float] SPARSE NULL, [StandardDeviation5YearAnnualized] [float] SPARSE NULL, [StandardDeviation7YearAnnualized] [float] SPARSE NULL, [StandardDeviation10YearAnnualized] [float] SPARSE NULL, [StandardDeviation15YearAnnualized] [float] SPARSE NULL, [StandardDeviation20YearAnnualized] [float] SPARSE NULL,/**** Sharpe Ratio ****/鈥?Sharpe Mstar [SharpeRatioMorningstar6Month] [float] SPARSE NULL, [SharpeRatioMorningstar1Year] [float] SPARSE NULL, [SharpeRatioMorningstar2Year] [float] SPARSE NULL, [SharpeRatioMorningstar3Year] [float] SPARSE NULL, [SharpeRatioMorningstar4Year] [float] SPARSE NULL, [SharpeRatioMorningstar5Year] [float] SPARSE NULL, [SharpeRatioMorningstar7Year] [float] SPARSE NULL, [SharpeRatioMorningstar10Y', 623, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-679'),
    ('355', 'External Office Reports Folder and Report API(s) for External Office Integration Partners', 'As an Office user, I would like to access my clients'' OC reports in 3rd party tools.聽{color:#000000} Office Cloud uses 2 APIs to construct the reports page, one is for getting folders:[https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/SWDO/OC+Report+Folder+Managerment]{color}{color:#000000}, and other one is for getting reports [https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/SWDO/OC+worker+tech+design.]{color}{color:#000000}We would like to leverage these existing endpoints.{color}聽', 39, 0, 6, null, null, null, null, 'Cloud - Oct - Nov 2019', '2019-10-03T00:00:00', '2019-11-13T00:00:00', 3, 0, '79', 'Office Cloud - Report Sharing Integration', 'CLP-1047'),
    ('356', 'Publication Name', '*Goal*: Remove collections and move them to publication name to allow content creators to use any template for publications.This will allow historical content availability without creating more collections or changing names of existing collections.*Story 1*: As a creator of thematic content, I need to be able to choose a publication name for any template format in any collection so that I don''t have to request a new template when publication names change or when I need a new component in the collection.*Story 2*: As a creator of thematic content, I need to be able to create new publication names or modify existing names. * *Story 2 AC 1*: If a user or a role contains a publication name permission, he/she has the right to create new or modify existing publication names. * *Story 2 AC 2*: User has access to a web UI for publication name and preferably other types of metadata, such as thematic tags.聽', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'RPS-3845'),
