    ('361', 'Ratings 2.0 Quant API Implementation', 'Next steps:1.	Possible ticket for next sprint: Agree with Quant team on the signature of endpoints2.	Possible ticket for next sprint: Understand how RDB data is structured3. Look at if else logic from Quant to derive the overall rating4. Identify tables in RDB that that IQR, reference data and prices5. Get blessing from API guild*End point 1:*Inputs : < Shareclass ID, People Rating, Process Rating, Parent Rating >Output : Dictionary - <shareclass ID>: <overall rating> {Note: Rating can be Gold /Silver/bronze or numeric 1,2,3 or both}End point 2:Input : <Fund  ID, People Rating, Process Rating, Parent Rating >Output : Dictionary - <shareclass ID>: <overall rating> {Note: Returns data for all share classes under that fund. Rating can be Gold /Silver/bronze or numeric 1,2,3 or both}End point 3:Input : <Strategy  ID, People Rating, Process Rating, Parent Rating >Output : Dictionary - <shareclass ID>: <overall rating> {Note: Returns data for all share classes under the strategy. Rating can be Gold /Silver/bronze or numeric 1,2,3 or both}End point 4:<universe call>Open Questions: 1.	Should the output be json , xml or both2.	Should the calls be GET or POST. If the request is large possibly using POST3.	Should the calls be synchronous or asynchronous4.	Is public access a requirement. I don鈥檛 think so5.	Leveraging MaaS will provide authentication. Should this be wrapped around MaaS', -1, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 8, 8, null, null, 'RPS-3716'),
