    ('373', 'ETF Reports Transition to 5P Format', '*Technical notes:* * Right now, to our knowledge, the new ETF editor will be聽*identical* in all aspects to the current GFR, except it will be tied to one or more ETF performance ids, instead of funds and shareclasses.聽 This includes: ** parent editor and rating ** QB integration ** multiple translations ** current method of tying GFR to parent in DB DocExt table * So we will want to explore if we can simply re-use the current GFR editor.聽 This might save a lot of work, but we want to make sure we don''t introduce additional complexity into the GFR editor, since it is already very complex * We will create a new collection id for this content.聽 This will be a single collection for all regions. We need to decide what to do about the format * We will need to switch the API ETF universe endpoint to use this new collection * For now, we need to keep the ETF datapoints in the stand-alone data points editor. But this can go away soon*MVP*聽_Caroline Update 12/6/18_This is what can be released this year 2018. # (must have) Basic doc functions and workflows of GFRs (creation/cloning, FRES queue, MR reviewer, doc ownership, translations, etc.) # (must have) BR: Cannot modify archived docs, cannot modify live ratings, override checkbox/reason # (must have) Parents implementedThis is what can be added early 2019. # (must have) Alerts for doc and data points # (must have) Custom data population for GFR ratings DPs (use same ones)聽*Background*: Kunal and Haywood have requested that MR modify ETF reports to match the 5 pillar text format in GFRs.*ETF collections in scope*: # 574 AUS ETF report # 585 CAN ETF report # 738 Asian ETF report # 462聽US ETF report # 聽606 EMEA ETF report*MR would like to explore the most feasible options for transitioning content to the new format. In all cases, historical ETF documents will not be moved to the new format.* # New ETF collection(s) that are copies of the GFRs # Allow ETF vehicles in the current GFR collections but find a way for products to be able to easily identify vehicle types in order to generate the right report (static or digital).*Handling of Live and Archived ETF Reports in Transition*: * +Archived+: Nothing. Leave聽as is in old聽ETF collections. * +Live+: Make working doc copies in the new format to allow global ETF analysts to edit and relaunch using the original publish dates.*Mapping of Old ETF Text Fields to 5P Format for LIVE Docs Only (ETF to GFR):* # ETF deck = GFR analysis deck # Take, Morningstar Take = Analysis # Fundamental View, Portfolio/Fund Construction = Process # Taxation (do not map) # Fees = Price # Alternatives (do not map) # Bull/Bear (do not map)*Special Scenario Vanguard Funds with Different Vehicles*: Vanguard has OE and ETF vehicles mapped to the same fund ID FSUSA06UL6. Currently, MR publishes separate reports for the index fund and the ETF. As per [~abryan], it would be easier if his team could simply add the ETF performance ID to an existing GFR for the same fund ID聽FSUSA06UL6. * +ETF+ = ', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 132, 129, null, null, 'RPS-3234'),
