    ('375', 'Secondary Flag', 'Tech Notes # data point name = focus # principal/secondary - data points are labeled as principal and secondary in UI and API # applies to performance IDs (share class level) and only for collections that have security mapping. # How will this impact other collections, incl all MR - MR collections UI shouldn''t change. Concept doesn''t apply. No change to API. No impact to MR consumers. # *Wiki*: [https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/RTECH/Principal%2C+secondary%2C+etc+security+mappings] # col IDs out of scope and no UI changes: ** company reports (all principal DB, UI no changes) ** models (all principal DB, UI no changes) ** moat category (*out of scope - no changes at all*) # col IDs in scope (UI and DB changes) ** stock analyst notes ** Selects ** Observers ** Canadian Insights-------------------------------------------------------Problem Statement: Currently, RPS UI does not allow users to indicate if a given security in a write up is Primary vs Secondary. The lack of this functionality limits readers'' ability to narrow down search and therefore shrinks visibility of Morningstar research.Proposed Change: This change should be applicable to Analyst Note, Analyst Company Report, Select Presentation, Observer Series, Analyst Presentation.Example: Let''s assume an analyst is writing an Analyst Note (or any of the collection types presented above). The main focus of the report is on Ford. However for analyst also mentioned GM and Fiat.We envision that the Securities Selector section will be changed to reflect "Securities Selector Primary" and "Securities Selector Secondary". Respectively, analyst will enter Ford in the first former section and GM and Fiat in the latter.聽+Stories+:(4-5 sprints) # Investigate current state of each collection (5 pts) ## UI and DB ## API ## Alerts ## Launcher/site update ## How impact doc ext primary tag ## Idea: add new DP in docSecurities table. IsPrimary (1,0) ## DB - schema changes (1 to 2 pts) & data migration from doc ext (8-13 pts)(L/XL) # API聽 (---------RPS-3107---------) (L/XL)聽 ## Need to add API search parameter to distinguish primary vs secondary documents ### *note*: many products share class/company searches. Should return primary as default. # Alerts - should be same # UI (L) - Use separate user controls for principal and secondary selectors # Launcher/site update (M) # How to handle historical (M) - Assume that all historical securities are principal. Data migration to backfill to principal in doc security for only equities only. 3 values are NULL, (1) principal, (2) secondary.聽Enhancement stories:On March 21, Elizabeth, Dan Rohr, Patrick, John T., Dilani, Caroline, and Eugene met and the following enhancements were requested to be added.聽聽https://msjira.morningstar.com/browse/RPS-3618 Update Moat Framework and Valuation Models (added to current Sprint so will be in the 1^st^ release)https://msjira.morningstar.com/browse/RPS-3619 Add control to check/uncheck all (added to next Sprint so will +not+ be i', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 4, 4, null, null, 'RPS-3106'),
    ('376', 'Manager Selection Memo & Write Up Production', 'Caroline Notes 11/1/2018: * Fiduciary services - watch list * Produced manually PDF * Frequency Qtrly*Purpose:*聽Brief comment on the fund. Why did we add it or remove it? Why was it place on or off watch? The attached pdf is an example.聽+New collection called Fiduciary Services Memo+ * Not share class specific. Title will be Fund Name. * Should basically mirror the format of the Fund Analyst Notes collection * Max character count of 1,600 (with spaces) but no limit (show character count above the field) * No html controls. * Corrections: analyst makes initial edits, sets to ready, Compliance makes edits, sets to ready, FRES makes final edits sets to live', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'RPS-3037'),
