    ('382', 'Ratings 2.0', 'Need to support expansion of vehicle types under coverage based on strategies and parents. Currently only support OE, ETF, CEF, SMA vehicle types. MR needs to be able to associate (map) research content with other vehicle types such as CITs (collective investment trusts). # Source: Data API, RDB, etc. Best source. # Storage: What if any data needs to be stored in RPS DB # Corporate Action/Changes: How to handle changes from chosen source(s) such that documents/associated research are valid聽+Potential Future Workflow:+ * Strategy Ratings Committee: ratings committees vote on strategy pillar ratings (people and process) which sits at strategy ID level. * Strategy RPS Publishing: strategy text and pillars entered in RPS in one UI using strategy ID. Content applies to all active vehicles for the strategy. * Parent Ratings Committee and RPS Publishing: parent text and pillar rated and published for all relevant company IDs included in parent analysis document. Content applies to all active vehicles for the group of companies. * Share class level pillar ratings: Price and performance calculated by Quant team and used as input to calculate analyst rating for each share class in each vehicle along with the strategy and parent ratings. * Ratings history: RPS should store a M* analyst rating and individual pillar ratings for each share class ID regardless of vehicle.聽', -1, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, 'Ratings 2.0 - Q3 2019', '2019-07-01T00:00:00', '2019-09-30T00:00:00', 156, 122, '46', 'Increase Fund Ratings Efficacy', 'RPS-2737'),
