    ('385', 'Parent Committee in RPS, retire analysis editor', '*Parent Committee in RPS Docs, retire analysis editor* * (must) Electronic voting (online/RPS) * (must) Flexible committee members * (must) Flexibility regional committee decisions * (nice-must) Custom grouping of company IDs ** More than one CID ** More than one Brand ID * (must) Mapping grouping of CIDs using Brand ID as search in addition fund share class ID, ticker, fund ID, respective names investments and company names * (must) Analysts allowed to add/remove individual CIDs * (nice to have) User can specify CIDs that are different roles other than provider or advisor * (must) Push a notification to committee members that ready for voting * (must) Email notification when last required voter has approved, which allows analyst to publish ASAP * (must) Email notification when there is dissent, which informs that someone needs to slot for an in-person committee ASAP ** Allows someone to immediately schedule an in-person * (must) Record approval or dissent * (must) Different committee members vote at different times * (must) Analyst needs to choose between in-person and electronic ** Send email notification upon submission for both electronic and in-person meeting requests * (okay) RPS will no longer slot in-person meeting submissions. Ask analysts to schedule in-person meetings themselves. ** *Note about current scheduling in-person meeting slots*: Pipeline processor currently keeps tracks of all submissions and static meeting times * (option) Could keep committee UI (not required) * (option) Could put committee UI in the parent document collection (Caroline would rather have it separate) ** (must) Text editing/set ready has nothing to do with rating and voting *** Saving (no change) *** Ready (soft message to analyst that parent voting not yet completed) *** Launch (hard business rule & user message that cannot launch without approved parent rating) * *Next steps*: Navi will be in the office tomorrow 