    ('394', 'Parent Enhancements', 'Wiki [https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/RTECH/Parent+Enhancements]*Goal*: Allow parent content to be associated with a group of company IDs rather than a single company ID.*Pain points*: * Time consuming: Burdensome and repetitive for analysts and editors to copy and paste same content (i.e. text and pillar rating) across several company IDs and translations. * Latency issues: Takes time to manually update all associated company IDs which contributes to stale parent content. * Translations disappear: Translated parent content disappear from fund reports when original content language content is updated.*Requirements include*: * Publish parents separately from fund text such that products can consume parent research without accompanying fund reports * Parent pillar rating, author, and text should be the same for all company IDs referenced by the lead parent content. This includes all translations. * Lead analyst can use an unrestricted number of the following to populate company IDs covered under the parent content: ** Branding ID/name(s) ** Company ID/name(s) (advisor and/or provider roles) ** Fund ID/name(s) ** Fund share class ID/name(s) ** Fund NAV ticker(s) * Ability to add/remove covered company IDs individually or in batch, preferably with a simple way to select multiple CIDs and mark as not covered * Analyst can see company IDs covered and those not covered ** for example if choose 2 different branding IDs but excluding only 4 companies from one of the brand IDs, those 4 excluded company IDs show up in the excluded section * Covered and Not Covered sections should reflect the same data: ** checkbox column ** company ID ** name ** company ID country name ** # active fund IDs or share classes (ask Bridget). *Note*: Nice to have if this section is expandable to be able to see the list of vehicles. *** advisor = NZ/AUS funds *** provider = everything else ** # live funds IDs covered by a research report聽*Note*: Nice to have if this section is expandable to be able to see the list of vehicles with doc IDs. Additionally, nice to have if can then click to open any of the doc IDs to get a closer look. *** OE, CEF, ETF, SMA, TD, 529? ** 聽', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'RPS-1857'),
