    ('504', 'Lumpsums in RM5', 'Some providers who use batch only have been sending lumpsum in the batch participant XML all along. Schwab has indicated that they would like to start sending lumpsums in both, batch and real time participant XML.Preliminary research done by the T3 team showed that:* The data merge logic for lumpsum was developed only for the batch layer and applies only to batch enroll* Lumpsum data sent in the real time participant XML is not recognized by the RM5 UI In this epic, we will be updating the data merge logic so it applies to all batch processes and the UI as well, and will be making all RK-sent lumpsum information non-editable on the UI with messaging added to inform the user to contact the recordkeeper/provider for updates to incorrect lumpsum sent in the participantXML.', -1, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 5, 5, null, null, 'RMC3-67'),
    ('508', 'Disable SR for 401A', 'Typically with 401(a) plans, employers agree to match 100% of the participants contribution. This is usually agreed聽to by both the participant and employer. The participant typically cannot change their contribution without the employer agreeing to the change since that would mean that the employer also needs to increase their match of the contribution.However, the lack of flexibility is sometimes applied to specific contribution sources. For example, a participant may not be allowed to change their pretax contribution without the employer''s consent, but may be allowed to change their posttax contribution.Due to this, we need to be providing the capability for the Record-keeper to indicate which account is not advisable for savings rate advice. For the example above, the record-keeper would indicate that the participant is not eligible for contribution changes to the pretax 401(a) account, but is eligible for contribution changes to the posttax 401(a) account.', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'RMC3-25'),
    ('509', 'Sentry', 'Placeholder for work that will be needed for Sentry''s record-keeper conversion and move to RM5, tentatively scheduled for 10/20/2018.', -1, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 15, 15, null, null, 'RMC3-17'),
    ('510', 'COLA Adj', 'Production data showed that there are 92 users with dual record-kept pensions (inside pensions). The participant schema does not have a provision for pensionIDs that recordkeepers could send. This means that identifying which record-kept pension''s COLA preference was changed in a prior session becomes challenging.The best solution would be to introduce a pensionID attribute in the participant schema to be able to differentiate between each inside pension and track which account has what type of cost of living adjustment indicator.For now, we are moving forward with askign the user if cost of living adjustments should apply or not, and that preference will be applied to ALL of their pensions (UI entered and inside). 聽 * Allow a user to indicate if cost of living adjustments should apply to their pensions or not ** COLA preference should apply to ALL pensions held by the participant. This includes UI and recordkeeper sent pensions * RM assumes that cost of living adjustments apply to pensions by default. ** So, when a returning user visits the UI for the first time with this feature in place, and the user has pensions already recorded or sent in the participant XML, the COLA preference should be shown as selected by default, but made editable to the user can change this preference ** When a user visits the UI for the first time with this feature in place, provide a way to notify to user that COLA will be assumed by default, but make it editable to the user can change this preference ** Returning users see their previously chosen COLA preference * All existing user records will need to be updated prior to production to set cost of living adjustment to true (or appropriate indicator) in the database * Batch will continue to honor changes made to COLA preferences on the UI. If users do not return to the UI, then use pre-set cost of living adjustment indicator of true that will be pre-populated for all users * This is a global change聽*+Old requirements - not to be used+*:Pensions in RM5 currently assume that cost of living adjustments apply to a pension. However, not all employers adjust pension payouts based on cost of living changes. * Allow user to indicate cost of living adjustment on the UI for an existing pension or a newly added pension * RM assumes that cost of living adjustments apply by default to pensions. ** If a user who had previously entered pension visits the site for the first time after this feature is introduced, then the check box for cost of living adjustments will be checked by default. ** If a user is entering a pension for the first time, the pension card should have the check box for cost of living adjustments will be checked by default * Indicate "true" or "false" in the contineuinflationafterstartage attribute in the wfe input based on whether the user has indicated that adjustments would apply to their pension ** Pension projections will change based on whether inflation adjustments were applied or not to the associated pens', -1, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'RMC3-7'),
