    ('537', 'Modeling Inherited IRA Accounts [2019 Q4]', 'Some clients want to enable WFE to be able to model both a Traditional or Roth IRA that is inherited.  The rules for distributions from Inherited IRAs are different than "regular" IRA''s that an investor may own.    THe Use cases for modeling inherited IRAs are as follows:* Inherit a Traditional IRA from a Spouse* inherit a Roth IRA from a Spouse* Inherit a Traditional IRA from a Non-Spouse* Inherit a Roth IRA from a Non-SpouseWithin Each of these Use Cases, the rules can differ depending if the original owner of the IRA is less than or greater than 70.5 at death.The stories associated with this Epic will provide more detail on the modeling', -1, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 15, 15, null, null, 'WFE-4285'),
