    ('540', '2019 CMA Updates [2019 Q4]', 'Epic to contain all WFE work related to collecting updated 2019 CMA data, producing new config files, testing and sending to clients.Also in scope are additional data point updates contained in the Source xls which we get from David Blanchett.Other Config File Update Epic (WFE-1368) contains items also in scope for update during this season:State Tax Updates - WFE-3365Others - TBD at this time.', -1, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 29, 29, '207', 'Support & Help Grow CAS Relationships', 'WFE-4166'),
    ('541', 'DRIVe: Containerization [2019 Q4]', 'There are two major components to this:1-Containerizing the engine2-Making the published "versions" of config easily acquirable (for example, as packages on msnexus or something)聽At the end of all of this, each build should: * publish an image with the latest build (and label)Each container should be able to: * programmatically fetch config/tax/etc, similar to a package manager (if not by a package manager)聽', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 29, 17, null, null, 'WFE-4154'),
