    ('543', 'Social Security Calculation Adjustment', 'Thru research and client conversations, we discovered that an additional COLA adjustment needs to be made to the Social Security calculation.  In essence, every time SS is calculated by WFE, the final step in the  process is to multiply the calculated benefit by the cumulative COLA factor from age 62 until SS Benefit Commencement Date.', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'WFE-4098'),
    ('544', 'TIAA CRM Request: Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute', 'TIAA has a plan sponsor (Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute) who has questions about the WFE Engine and how we calculate / project out things.Background: POA is a projection only system that uses WFE to calculate probability of success and aggregate retirement readiness statistics for a plan population.They want "calculations" for the following:1)聽聽 Calculations of the projected account balance at retirement age2)聽聽 Projected Social Security Benefit amount at retirement age3)聽聽 DB plan benefit and the assumptions used to project these benefits to retirement age4)聽聽 Investment rate of return assumptions used for each type of calculation5)聽聽 Interest rate and mortality assumptions, cost of living increase assumptions and the factors used to convert the account balance to annual income at retirement age6)聽聽 Salary increases assumed at various ages7)聽聽 All other assumptions used聽7 is being handled by [~pkavana] with David Blanchett.聽We should create a word document with examples on how the engine calculates the other six items.聽 We will most likely need to re-order and go with: # Salary Curve # Social Security (follows 1 since it is based on salary) # DB plan benefitsthen move into # Investment Assumptions (CMAs) # Interest Rateand then: # mortality curveand then how this all gets used in the monte carlo to project retirement income (we may also have to explain a monte carlo to them).聽 In addition, we will also probably have to explain that the values they are seeing are inflation-adjusted dollars.聽This is a large lift, but we have time to work on it, so we should start now.聽For more background, please read the email chain attached.', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'WFE-4093'),
    ('545', 'Roth Contributions [TBD]', 'Under current IRS law, an investor can only make Roth IRA contributions if his/her income falls within a certain range depending on tax filing status.  WFE currently applies this income test, but does not fully implement the law.  The tickets under this Epic will address the following issues in order to allow WFE to fully implement the law:* Definition of MAGI for Roth IRA Purposes* Applying the income test for every year in the forecast* Applying the Contribution Phase-Out Methodology for Income between the Two Ranges*', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 9, 9, null, null, 'WFE-4061'),
