    ('648', 'Ops Dashboard and File transfer integration', 'As operations, we want to incorporate file transfer source/destination concepts into the existing client/file concepts of the operations dashboard, so that we know where we expect to receive and deliver files for each client and how many files we expect per client.From a workflow perspective, we believe the OpsDashboardConfiguration -> FileMapping interface supports the user experience provided the Client drop down supports adding a new client, maybe it spawns the Client Configuration page and the refreshes to show the newly configured client.聽 Same goes for Vendor.Below are the acceptance criteriaAC1: When configuring a relayed file in the file configuration screen, adding a client should also configure File Relays for that client聽AC2: Vendor->Client (FTP->OutboundFiles and OutboundFiles->FTP) relay jobs de-activated in File Transfer Config tab. Vendor->ETL (FTP->InboundFiles) can remain for now. File transfer should continue to support these relaysAC3: All clients currently configured in the retired File Transfer config are present in the new File Mapping screenAC4: ftp -> file configured per-vendor on the Operations Dashboard Configuration pageAC5: file -> file configured per-client on the Operations Dashboard Configuration page聽This epic is created with reference to ticket聽 https://msjira.morningstar.com/browse/GISIR-338聽聽', 19, 2, 5, '#6ec762', null, null, null, null, null, null, 19, 19, null, null, 'MIP-327'),
