    ('654', 'Design: Practice Management Report in Office Cloud (Phase 1)', 'This is phase one in a multi-phase approach to a larger Practice Management Dashboard project.*The purpose of this phase is to simply make some practice level data available in excel to the user. It is a parity task.*As an Office user, I do not have access to practice level data. I need this data to efficiently review my accounts, make business decisions, and fulfill compliance requirements. By allowing the user to generate three practice management reports, the user will be able to fulfill these workflows.*General requirements are:* * 3 reports are: AUM, Global Account Performance Review, Global Unrealized Gain/Loss * My suggestion, should be one launch point to run the reports, needs review by Enrique''s team. * Excel output only, no UI display. * All settings are locked down and not displayed except for date options. User can select a limited number of date options. * Reports will generated using the on-demand engine, not batched data. * Admin user should see all client/accounts in practice/firm. Advisor should see just their client/accounts. * After user runs report, need notification telling them that report will be available for viewing or downloading in the Reports section of Office. It would be good to have some messaging that indicates it could take some time to generate the report. * While report is generating, user needs to be able to navigate to other parts of the program. * After report calculation finishes, ** Notification on framework pages where report should appear in Reports section as an .xls file which the user can open/download or download to open. * Should be one place to run all three reports.*Out of Scope* * UI display of data, to come in later phases. * Any other practice report outside of the three mentioned * Report popping up automatically when complete. * Admin does not need the ability to run the report on just one advisor. Its always all data. * Dynamic messaging of timing of report that changes based on size of report. It is too hard to estimate the length of time for these reports.*Current Desktop Process Flow*Process flow should be similar to desktop in that the user goes to the universal bar menu, chooses Reports&gt;Management Reports&gt;Selects the desired report. A dialogue window opens with settings options and date range. User selects settings and clicks run. Message pops up saying " Your report has been generated and can be viewed or downloaded from the Reports page, under the Reports tab." User goes to the reports page and clicks on the report to download/open in Excel. There is no notification of completion except for the status column in the reports page. Its saying "processing" or ''finished."聽聽', 59, 5, 2, null, '2019-05-30T00:00:00', '2019-07-10T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud - Jun-Jul 2019', '2019-05-30T00:00:00', '2019-07-10T00:00:00', 6, 6, '57', 'Office Cloud - Practice Management Data (for Q3 deadline)', 'CLP-1267'),
