    ('781', 'Office Cloud Peer Analytics', '*Background Information*As a Office user, I want to group investments located in investment list and screen grid views result so that he or she can more efficiently analyze data. To meet this need, we want to add a more basic version of DWM/DAM''s Peer Analysis tool to Office Cloud investment grid view.This feature will help a lot in reaching the goal of migrating 1000 users to Cloud. It is a feature that has been asked for in user research sessions and provides a value add feature not found in Office desktop.*Acceptance Criteria*1a) Peer Analytics tool should be available for all security universes.1b) Within the Peer Analytics tool, the user will need: * 1) Grouping * 2) Conditional Formatting * 3) Benchmarks聽2) Grouping Options * Global Broad Category Group * Global Category * Investment Type * Morningstar Category * Custom groups can be ignored. Office users cannot create custom groups in CDM.3) Conditional Formatting Options * All Numeric Data * Uses data points listed in Column Set * Operator - Between, Not Between, Equal To, Greater Than, Less Than, Greater/Equal To, Less Than/Equal To, Not Equal To * Min - Max fields * Color coding options * Action button to delete or duplicate * Add formatting rule button4) Benchmarks Options * Display Benchmark 1 - show same options as DIrect in drop down menu * Display Benchmark 2 - show same options as Direct in drop down menu5) Do not include聽Dynamic Ranking, Summary Statistics and Scorecard options.聽', 90, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, '279', 'Office Cloud - Investment Research', 'CLP-1104'),
    ('782', 'July-Aug Billing.', '# Decimal display for Billing Summary Report # Practice Current View: Add allocated fee information# Auto Upload TDA Custodian Fee file', 36, 5, 2, '#F0A509', '2019-07-11T00:00:00', '2019-08-21T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud - Jul-Aug 2019', '2019-07-11T00:00:00', '2019-08-21T00:00:00', 34, 34, '62', 'Office Cloud -  Billing Parity', 'CLP-1272'),
    ('783', 'Import Positions via Excel in Office Cloud', 'Wiki:聽[https://mswiki.morningstar.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=306900087]聽UX Link:聽[https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/56NRPFIHAXZ#/screens/316935565]聽聽Visual link: [https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/Q5NRPJHXBNY#/screens/316936050]聽----聽*As an Office Cloud user, I need to be able to import account positions via Excel and create a quick account.*We need to be able to support positional portfolio import for these three types of portfolios in Office Cloud: * Client Accounts (first priority) * Model Portfolios (second priority) * Custom Benchmarks (third priority)Import interface: * We only need to support Microsoft Excel positions import * We do +NOT+ need to support any of the other XML or CSV import interfaces that Office 3x currently supports. That is out of scope for this project.From a functional perspective, Office Cloud positional import should work exactly the same as it does in Direct, but with these key differences: * Security matching must be done against the 3x security master ** Any new securities that come in via import should be created in 3x security master ** Defaults for securities: *** If Morningstar match found: Display as Morningstar Security = Yes, Price Source = Whatever is in global settings *** If no match found:聽Display as Morningstar Security = No, Price Source = Imported * Portfolio data must be posted to the 3x databases rather than the Cloud databases ** Basically we need to follow what happens today when Office Cloud users create a quick account 鈥?the accounts show up in 3x as well * During client account holding import, we must also allow users to import "Client Name" information ** "Client Name" will be one additional field available for selection when users are mapping the columns of their excel file ** This new field is mandatory ** Users will be expected to enter the text name of the client exactly how it appears in the client management section of Office (i.e. "Eileen Bingle" or "Bingle, Eileen") ** We will not support matching on SSN or any other identifier except the text client name ** If we cannot find an exact single-match to a client *  **  *** Allow users to search for and select a client (just like they can with security match), but this optional *** Client name field is required.From a business standpoint, it would be good if we can deliver this by the end of Q3 2018. That way there is still time in Q4 to use this as a selling point to hit the 1000 user conversion mark.聽', 87, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, 'Cloud_Q1 2020', '2019-12-26T00:00:00', '2020-03-18T00:00:00', 67, 32, '279', 'Office Cloud - Investment Research', 'CLP-1170'),
    ('784', 'Integrate Hypo with Office Cloud - Phase 1', '*Initial Launch Requirements ("Single Portfolio" Workflow)*Functional # User can launch Hypo from OfficeCloud鈥攅xact launch points to be confirmed # User can view their OfficeCloud (static) model portfolios in Hypo and choose one # User can view their OfficeCloud client accounts (quick, transactional) and prospect accounts (quick) in Hypo and choose one # User can set basic assumptions for the portfolio (initial investment value, time period) # User can set one benchmark # User can generate the new Hypo report # User can view Hypo PDF reports in OfficeCloud Reports page (and include in batch reporting, publish to CWP, etc) # Show asset allocations as long-rescaled聽(OC only, other products such as AWS may want to show negative values)聽Non-functional # Data used in Hypo UI and reports are RDB, consistent with data source for OC reports # Performance requirements 鈥?not a concern, there is no SLA for OC users # Be able to launch only for specific OfficeCloud users (EAMS) # Note: Hypo uses setting id (Productid/Instid/Groupid) for feature configurations. So OC needs pass us a setting id. For office 3.X, for example it passes and id AWSOE. If you want office cloud report configuration the exactly the same as office 3.X, you can just reuse id AWSOE, otherwise please choose a new id.聽All other requirements including OfficeCloud snapshot report will be handled +*after*+ initial launch in OC.', 506, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-940'),
