    ('790', 'Upload Outside Documents in Office Cloud', '{color:#172b4d} *As an Office Cloud user, I would need the ability to uplaod documents created outside of Office Cloud so that I may securely share they with my clients via Client Web Portal.*{color}{color:#d04437}*Problem:*聽{color}Office Cloud users would like to securely share documents created outside of Office Cloud with their Clients via CWP.聽 Right now, a user can only share pdfs generated within OC, but users would like the ability to share outside documents as well.聽聽*Who is the target?*聽All Office Cloud Users who use聽 share reports on CWP*What are they trying to do?*聽electronically share documents created outside of OC to their clients in a secure manner*What is the scope of the ask?*聽scope is limited to聽**聽Uploading outside documents for the purpose of sharing on the CWP.聽 For this phase it is OK to limit scope to uploading one document at a time.*what are the known dependencies?* * Office Cloud * Client Web PortalThe following file types are supported by CWP for clients to send to their advisors. We should support the same list for advisors to send to clients.聽*what is the AC?*AC1: As an OC user, I would like to upload an outside file for the purpose of sharing it with my client via CWP聽 聽AC1.1: I need a way in which to associate this outside file with a client or account聽聽 聽AC1.2: If i am an Admin user, I should be able to associate the outside file with any client or account in my firm. Regardless which log-in is owner of that client.聽 聽AC1.3: I would like to ability to perform upload action from Reports area or from the individual Client action icon in Clients & Accounts.AC2: As an OC user, I would like the ability to remove an outside file from being shared on the CWPAC3: As an OC user, I need to be able to easily identify docs that have been added from outside of Office CloudAC4: As an OC user, I need to be able to easily identify all doc shared in CWP (OC source & outside of OC)AC5: The max file size I can upload is 50MBAC6: The following file types are the only file types the upload supports:|.doc|Microsoft Word Document||.docx|Microsoft Word 2007 Document||.xls|Microsoft Excel Workbook||.xlsx|Microsoft Excel 2007 Workbook||.pdf|Adobe Acrobat Document||.xps|Microsoft XPS Document||.txt|Text File||.bmp|Bitmap Image||.gif|GIF Image||.jpg|JPEG Image||.jpeg|JPEG Image||.png|PNG Image||.zip|Zip File|', 99, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, 'Cloud - Nov-Dec 2019', '2019-11-14T00:00:00', '2019-12-25T00:00:00', 6, 0, '241', 'Office Cloud - Report Management', 'CLP-1050'),
