    ('792', 'Cash Flow Component - Practice Management Dashboard', '*As an advisor, i would like a way to monitor all incoming & outgoing cash flows for my practice so that I can keep track of important activity in my practice.*AC1: I would like to view cash flow information for set time frames.AC2: I would like to know the following numbers on a practice level: * Capital Inflow * Capital Outflow * Net Capital FlowAC3: I would like the ability to view cash flows in more details as it pertains to each client & accountAC4: If I am an admin, I would like to see this information on the whole firm, but also have the ability to filter by advisor._Global Cash Flow report for Office 3.x is attached for reference._*Other items to answer:* * What transaction types show up on cash flow reports? * what are key data points when viewing cash flow info?聽 Are there dp in the 3.x report that are not needed? * Is there special information the advisor would like to draw attention to on this report? (cash flows over x amount, cash flows in retirement accts, etc)聽聽', 282, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-813'),
