    ('807', 'Enhance backend batch import', 'Currently we might deadlock issue, send data Kafka time out issue during concurrent import large file through backend batch import process.Purpose for this epic is to support Data Catalyst import through backend batch rather than ETL.聽July 2 did some adjustment for Reids(client security service)Reids Part * Redis - CDC sync -2 sps * Redis- Framework- 4 sps * Redis - client security write back Data Base - 2 sps * Redis-聽 Create/update/ Delete/Search - 3聽Import API聽 * Create Client Security聽 to Redis -2 * Update Client Security to Redis -5 * Delete Client Security to Redis-2 * Get Client Security to Redis -2 * 聽 聽Tech Integration -3Account Holding (model portfolio)- 15 * Create Client Security to Redis聽 * Update client security to Redis聽Investment List -5Investment list + CD-5Investment List on new UI -5Matching (user defined security matching) to Redis聽 -5聽QA Test Strategy聽Part 1: Import API function Testing - 4 pointsPart 2: Interactive/Backend- AH+ Model portfolio+ CB 4Part 3: Interactive/Backend- IL+IL/CD 4Part 4: check security uniqueness + Concurrent Test 12聽聽聽聽聽', 419, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, 'Cloud - Jul-Aug 2019', '2019-07-11T00:00:00', '2019-08-21T00:00:00', 141, 141, null, null, 'CLP-1211'),
    ('808', 'Include Prospect''s Household data in the response for external Households Data APIs', 'As an Office user, I would like my Prospects'' data along with my Clients'' data be available through the external Households Data APIs, so I can view both prospects and client through my 3rd party applications.MaaS: [https://www.us-api.morningstar.com|https://www.us-api.morningstar.com/]AC 1.聽 /household/v2/households {color:#172b4d}endpoint should return both "prospect" and "client" householdType in the response.{color}AC 2. /household/v2/profiles {color:#172b4d}endpoint should return both "prospect" and "client" householdType in the response.{color}', 103, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, 'Cloud_Q1 2020', '2019-12-26T00:00:00', '2020-03-18T00:00:00', 0, 0, '273', 'Office Cloud - Standardizing Office APIs for 3rd Party Integrations', 'CLP-1209'),
    ('809', 'Morningstar Model Marketplace', 'This Epic is to put the Morningstar Model Marketplace within Office Cloud.聽 Current the Model Marketplace is live to approximately 260 RIA Firms through our Rebalancing platform TRX.聽 As the version is currently in production the TRX team will provide documentation around the API calls needed for Office Cloud.I have provided a high level overview of the capabilities we are looking for once the Marketplace is in Office.聽 I have presented this original solution to be a "Workbook" within Cloud, but am open to making Marketplace a Component.[^Model Marketplace Mockup.pptx]^Use Cases:聽[https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/PFS/Project%3A+Model+Marketplace]^聽+About Morningstar Model Marketplace+A聽centralized聽distribution聽platform where advisors can聽research聽third-party investment models,聽personalize the strategies to聽fit their clients鈥櫬爊eeds,聽and execute trades through TRX.Model Marketplace enhances our Morningstar Office鈩犅燙loud platform by empowering advisors to customize models from a variety of asset management firms and weigh them against the full extent of Morningstar analytics. Centralizing this workflow helps聽advisors聽lower costs and save time by scaling the investment management, portfolio monitoring, and rebalancing functions at their firms, while maintaining discretion on how their clients鈥?money is invested.聽Currently the Mo聽', 573, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-1208'),
