    ('811', 'Design for: Report Settings', 'Main document for project can be found in Epic聽CLP-1180*UX link:*聽[https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/WRNROI5DHP8#/316929208_01_Cover]聽[*{color:#172b4d}Visual link:{color}*聽https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/BWNRMFLPF7M|https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/BWNRMFLPF7M]Report Settings JTBD * I need to be able to CRUD Report Pre-Sets the included the following settings: ** Report Pre-Set Name ** Bond Yield ** Return Type ** Fee Type ** Display Accrued Interest (Yes/No) ** Include inception to date return on Performance Reports (yes/no) ** Reporting Currency ** Cover Page Disclosure ** Include Logo ** Cover Page * I need a way to review & manage the Report Pre-Sets I have created * I need ability to select one of my Report Pre-Sets as the Global default * Client Report Pre-Set should automatically default to the Global level ** I need to know my Client Pre-Set is pointed to follow Global level ** When reviewing my Client, I need to know what settings the Global level contains * I need the ability to have a Client Report Pre-Set stop following the Global level ** If I opt to stop following the Global level, I must select a different Report Pre-Set in my firm to be saved for that Client ** When reviewing my Client, I need to know what report settings are included in the Report Pre-Set saved to that Client|*What does Report Pre-set & Settings do?*||路聽聽聽聽聽聽 Determines reporting options used when user generates any Morningstar or Presentation Studio Template as a report. 路聽聽聽聽聽聽 Impacts CWP UI: o聽聽 Reporting Currency o聽聽 Return Type o聽聽 Fee Type 路聽聽聽聽聽聽 To be in line with work in DOMA-8698, it should also impact appropriate Client & Account Workbook components 聽 For additional information go to [portfolio accounting setting impact|https://morningstaronline-my.sharepoint.com/:x:/g/personal/kristen_carstensen_morningstar_com/EcQ3pvXmYnhEkuma8K6Hp30BL_9xPDGNuEq4lvU_SpCQIQ?e=vfTnb9] 聽**聽||*Why do we have this settin