    ('816', 'Ability to default account settings for a user or firm', 'In many cases, users want to default the account settings for all of their accounts to something that is a little different than the standard Morningstar default settings.聽For example, our Orion integration users may want to default to use ''Earliest Common'' calculation start date instead of the standard ''First Portfolio Date'' option.聽Or, as in the case of Merrill, they needed to default all of the firms account settings to use imported performance data instead of Morningstar calculated performance.Users can of course change these settings one-by-one for each account, but that becomes unreasonable when users have many accounts (in the case of some of our Orion users, 11K accounts).We need an easy operational way to update the default portfolio settings for a user or a firm.', 202, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-1184'),
