    ('819', 'Account Dynamic Aggregate Tool', 'As an Office user, I would like to aggregate several accounts (but not all) under one client into one account so that I can perform analysis on this aggregated account. This feature helps reach the 1,000 user migration goal. An example use case is if I have 5 accounts under one client. 3 accounts are tax-deferred and 2 accounts are taxable. I want to aggregate all three tax-deferred accounts together and view them as one account to see total exposure of a certain asset class within my tax deferred portfolio.', 41, 0, 1, null, '2019-11-14T00:00:00', '2019-12-25T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud_Q1 2020', '2019-12-26T00:00:00', '2020-03-18T00:00:00', 0, 0, '18', 'Office Cloud - Client & Account Analytics', 'CLP-1169'),
    ('820', 'Response time Estimator', '+Background+As part of supporting the new Grid loading approach where an user is allowed to access direct cloud features while waiting for advanced analytics to load, we plan on providing the user with an time estimate on how a request might take when advanced analytics features are turned on. The work at investment level is already complete in previous planning cycle and we plan on extend it to Portfolio Objects聽聽+Business Use case.+聽 * To provide a consistent experience for users between investments and portfolio objects by notifying/providing users with choice to use other direct web features.聽+Scope:+聽 # Enhance the current time estimator to estimate the number of investment to be processed and estimate time.聽 # Include infrastructure load into the estimates.聽 # For auto correction, log all information on time estimates provided for previous request & actual time take to process the request聽 # Create a dashboard of information in step 3.聽聽', 708, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-1155'),
    ('821', 'RBC Catalyst', 'Currently, the Import team does a bulk import of the data from EDM every month on STG.*RBC signed a contract with data catalyst and we have to deliver them monthly updates within 5 business days of availability of performance-ready month end data from EDM. We need to meet this deadline starting May 31, 2019,*In order for data catalyst to accomplish this goal, we have to get data from Import on the first day of every month. This can only be done if the import process is completely automated and promoted to Prod.*Feature requests to completely automate import flow**May 31  goal *1.  Account custom data points should be accessible in the cloud (existing s3 buckets supported by data services team)2. Separation of the client databases. Automate blotter flow. 3. Promote existing batch import process to Production to support monthly updates for RBC.4. Support data catalyst to onboard other pilot customers (our initial target is other EDM clients).5. Also, make sure that data catalyst has access to market data (https://s3.console.aws.amazon.com/s3/buckets/stg-mstar-timeseries-dri/?region=us-east-1&tab=overview) on prod.6. EDM needs to add their tickets for their promotion to Prod tickets.*6 months goal * ( To be added as a separate CLP ticket)Currently, data catalyst client is blacklisted so the data imported will to end up in Mart. We would like data catalyst to be whitelisted and follow the same flow as any other client so that the data ends up in Mart. This will allow data catalyst clients to view holdings level data in direct UI', 663, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-1123'),
    ('822', 'Returns based of Custom import of Custom securities', 'Background:聽We have a request from Merill Lynch to聽 * Import security level returns for custom securities (their hedge funds) on a quarterly basis * When they are viewing an account where one of the custom securities is a holding, they want to see the imported return in the holding analysis view and in presentation studio * If they create a proposal based on an account with one of the custom securities as a holding, then the return of the proposal incorporates the imported return of the聽custom security聽聽+Scope:+聽For each of these cases: # Custom security - no proxy - no imported returns - is holding of an account聽{color:#ff0000}Result: No returns in UI, as expected{color} # Custom security - no proxy - has quarterly imported returns - is holding of an account聽{color:#ff0000}Result: We see DRI in database, but no returns show on UI{color} # Custom security - proxy - no imported returns - is holding of an account聽{color:#ff0000}Result: Return values from proxy show on UI{color} # Custom security - proxy - has quarterly imported returns - is holding of an account聽{color:#ff0000}Result: We see custom DRI iin Client1 table, but the return shown on the UI is calculated based on proxy DRI, not custom DRI{color}聽', 715, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-1114'),
