    ('832', 'Allow users to view portfolios in workbook, even if they have more than 2000 portfolios', 'Currently, there is a hard limit on the number of accounts that can be displayed in the grid (right now it''s 2000 accounts). This means, if a user has more than 2000 accounts, it is impossible for them to view certain accounts.聽This is causing a problem for users of our Orion Data Services pilot who have more than 2000 accounts. And generally, it just prevents any user with more than 2K accounts from using DWM.We need to update how users select portfolios to view in a workbook.*Specifically, we need to be able to handle these cases*: # As a wealth manager, I鈥檇 like to compare the client account and proposal side by side, so that I can understand whether proposal has improvements in some areas vs client account # As a wealth manager, I have a client coming in tomorrow and I want to analyze all of his accounts to gather my talking points and recommendations for him (maybe create a proposal, etc.). There could be one or multiple accounts belonging to this client, but probably not more than 20. I may also want to view all accounts within this client鈥檚 household to have a full picture of his family鈥檚 investments. # As a wealth manager, I just found out some information or news about a particular investment and I want to analyze all of the accounts that hold that investment so that I can determine if I should recommend a change. # As a wealth manager, I just received a question from a client regarding the performance of one of their accounts. I would like to analyze the account to assess the situation and provide an answer to the client. # As a wealth manager, the firm has just put out new guidance for moderately aggressive portfolios. I鈥檇 like to open all of the accounts I manage that fit that risk profile to understand how I need to adjust them to comply with firm guidance. # As a wealth manager, I would like to view all accounts aligned with a particular model, policy or benchmark so that I can analyze their compliance with firm guidelines. # As a portfolio strategist, I鈥檇 like to compare the characteristics of model portfolios in the same style/category through ranking and combining multiple factors into one score. # As a portfolio strategist, I鈥檇 like to review all accounts belonging to a specific advisor so I can prepare for a meeting with that adviser. # As a strategist, I have been tasked with analyzing the accounts of a particular advisor whose performance has been sub-par. I want to analyze all of this advisors accounts so I can see if this is a systematic problem, or isolated to only one or two accounts. # As a member of the firm鈥檚 home office, I have noticed under performance from our Chicago branch. I would like to open all of the accounts in the Chicago branch to analyze if this is a systematic problem, or isolated to certain advisors or accounts. # As a due diligence analyst, I have been tasked with reviewing a certain set of model portfolios. I would like to analyze these models one by one, or perhaps compare one or two, to understand i', 219, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-1066'),
    ('833', 'New Import UI - Import list from workbook for DWM/DAM', 'This epic is to make importing a list available from the investment workbook in DWM and DAM, just as it is in Office Cloud.', 589, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 8, 8, null, null, 'CLP-1059'),
