    ('840', 'Model Portfolio Workbook for Office Cloud Phase 1.5', 'We need to expand the workflow to how Advisors can access their Model Portfolio Workbooks.Currently Advisors can only access a Model Portfolio Workbook via the following workflow:聽 * Add a default workbook "Model Portfolio" under File Management -> Workbooks. Type: Portfolios Owner: Morningstar , add "Read Only" label * Click "Model Portfolio" workbook, all existing model portfolios will be loaded into grid viewA new workflow needs to be added so that Advisors can also launch the workbook when selecting a model in file management.AC1: Additional Workflow * **This workflow should be identical to the DWM workflow * User selects model from list of Model Portfolios in File Management * User is prompted to select Model Portfolio Workbook in which to view model * Model Workbook launch with selected Model in focus', 566, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 5, 5, null, null, 'CLP-955'),
    ('841', 'Import TRX Models into Office Cloud via API', '*Acceptance Criteria:* As a user of both Office Cloud and TRX I would like all the models I have in TRX to be surfaced in the Office Cloud Model Portfolio Workbook.聽*Description:* The DOPA team will create a Models API that TRX will use to post updates when models are created/updated/deleted in TRX. 聽These will be models the advisor has either created themselves or subscribed to via the Model Marketplace.Having Office Cloud team create the api will also accomplish long term goal of having an integration api other platforms can use to import models into office.When TRX calls the Office model api we should be using the same authentication piece we use for the SSO. In which case the user will need "integrated" Office/TRX via the integrations page in Office Cloud.聽*+Business Requirement:+*聽[https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/PFS/TRX+Model+Marketplace]*+API wiki:+*聽[https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/SWDO/Import+TRX+models+to+Office+Cloud+-+API]', 47, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 31, 31, '78', 'Office Cloud - Model Marketplace Data Integration', 'CLP-953'),
