    ('843', 'Allow users to edit a security from the holding analysis component', 'If a holding is imported as unrecognized, a user may want to update the mapping for the security.Today, they would have to navigate away from the holding analysis space, go to CDM > Custom Investments, then search for the security, update it and then navigate back to the holding analysis component.We''d like to user to be able to make those types of edits directly from the holdings component.*Step 1*: User navigates to holding analysis page and clicks the hover action menu for an unrecognized security !image-2018-11-26-11-24-34-697.png|thumbnail! *Action Menu Options*:* Morningstar Report -- If the security is not matched to a Morningstar record, disable this option.* NEW: Edit Security -- When a user clicks this option, open the edit security modal*Step 2*: User clicks ''Edit Security''+For Direct users+, they see this modal: !screenshot-1.png|thumbnail! +For Office users+, they see this modal: !screenshot-2.png|thumbnail! *Step 3*: User makes a changes and clicks ''Done''* If user changes the name or ticker of an un-mapped security, then the new name and ticker are displayed in the holdings analysis component immediately after the user clicks ''Done''* If a user adds or changes the mapping of the security, then the entire row for that security in the holding analysis component changes to the mapped security', 218, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 21, 21, null, null, 'CLP-935'),
    ('844', 'Sharing of Portfolio Objects', 'Users can not currently share portfolio objects. This epic is to allow for the sharing of these objects from the row menu actions in their "file management" sections, and the workspace grid.聽* Sharing permissions available (read only, read write)* Only shareable with the same firmNeed to work out what happens when a user deletes/unshares a shared object in use by others. Are they warned it is in use, can they override that warning and break downstream objectsLinks between objects. If I share a client account that uses a custom benchmark but I don''t share the custom benchmark does the person shared with see that custom benchmark? Similarly proposals and client accounts and other links.Can I see portfolio settings even if I can''t edit them. Currently I can''t聽', 758, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 3, 3, null, null, 'CLP-929'),
