    ('866', 'Entitlement for non-US or Canada MQR data', 'The data/research team is聽asking for Morningstar Quant Rating data point to become entitled so that they can permission clients to see this data for US domiciled funds, non-US domiciled funds, or both.聽 The details of how they want this to be permissioned is outlined in the 5 steps below.聽+Data Points in Scope+: *FACT3031 - Morningstar Quantitative Rating*This includes all the parameter variations of this data point: # Morningstar Quantitative Rating 鈥?Overall # Morningstar Quantitative Rating 鈥?Parent Pillar # Morningstar Quantitative Rating 鈥?People Pillar # Morningstar Quantitative Rating 鈥?Performance Pillar # Morningstar Quantitative Rating 鈥?Price Pillar # Morningstar Quantitative Rating 鈥?Process Pillar # Mornignstar Quantitative Rating DateRules for entitlement:聽 # If the fund Domicile = United States OR CANADA, all MQR/MQR related data points are available to all global Direct users. # If the fund Domicile NOT = United States OR CANADA, all MQR/MQR related data points are restricted and not visible to all global Direct users, except users with @Morningstar.com email addresses. This applies upon launch of this entitlement. # Only once a client licenses additional data will we turn on the fund Domicile NOT = United States OR CANADA data for view for a client.聽 Licensing details will follow the process in #4 and #5 below.聽 # If I am a scorecard or select list user, the Product Owner (Ewa, Sashka, Marc, etc) will alert the Direct Entitlement team to allow access to specific user(s) to enable access for the MQR/MQR related data for Domicile NOT = United States聽OR CANADA (ie, what is currently blocked in #2 above). # When/if a scorecard or select list user cancels their contract, the Product Owner (Ewa, Sashka, Marc, etc) will alert the Direct Entitlement team to disable access to specific user(s) to disable access for the MQR/MQR related data for Domicile NOT = United States聽OR CANADA (ie, what is currently blocked in #2 above).Any questions, please let Dan Costello or Sara Mersinger know.聽*Comments from Eileen*We need to dig into how this is done in 3x a bit more (see Andy''s info below), but at a high level I think we will need to: # Read AMS rules for which users have access to non-US/Canada MQR data and include these in our ETL feed that runs every 2 hours # Build some process by which we strip out values for MQR if the funds are non-US/Canada UNLESS users have been granted access to this data 鈥?I think we could possibly leverage what we did for index entitlement, but we will need to explore this more fully', 425, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-390'),
