    ('873', 'Practice Management Report - Assets Under Management', '*Design:*UX:聽[https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/PWNROY92F5B]Visual:聽[https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/JFNRP0N2NM6聽|https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/share/JFNRP0N2NM6][^Illustration-PNG.zip] and聽[^Illustration-SVG.zip] refer to CLP-1267 for details聽As an Office user, I want to review my firm''s assets under management listed out by account and aggregated at the firm level in one report.. This allows me to efficiently review each account instead of having to run one report for each client or accounts. This also allows me to provide data for compliance requirements.*Acceptance Criteria*1) Report will live in a Practice Management Reports modal in the Office Cloud Home Page. The modal will include option to run any three of the practice management reports. The modal should be a simple list of the reports with a Run button to kick off the report generation process.2) Once the user clicks run, a dialogue box should appear asking the user to select an "As of Date". The end date will always be either most recent month end or previous month end. No other settings should be displayed. However, we should have an information icon explaining how the data is calculated or what settings were used.3) The report output will be excel and the data included will be the same as the 3x report.4) Settings are locked down except for "As of Date". Settings used are: * All custodians * Report Type - Excel * Report Asset by - Broad Asset Class only * Currency follows global reporting settings * Display amount and % for each asset class breakdown on account level and practice aggregated data. * Exclude: ** Inactive clients ** Prospects ** Closed accounts (closed before end date) ** Account excluded from client aggregate ** Shared clients ** Unmanaged assets/accounts.5) After running report user receives message saying we are generating your report (official content to come). Message will be the same regardless of calculation time.6) After report is complete, user receives message saying report is available in the reports section (official content to come).聽 This behavior is the same as 3x.7) Data should be calculated via the nightly batch process if possible. If not, the report should be run on-demand.8) Please see visual for possible design of how report will look in the Reports Grid.9) Admin user should see all accounts in practice/firm. Advisor should see just their accounts.聽*Suggested Content for Report Generation Window*What You''ll See In This Report * The report displays each of your accounts'' market value as well as their sum total, broken out by broad asset class in Excel format.What You Won''t See * Inactive Clients and Accounts * Unmanaged Assets and Accounts * Accounts Closed before Report Date * Prospects * Shared Clients聽', 61, 5, 2, '#1954a0', '2019-07-11T00:00:00', '2019-08-21T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud - Jul-Aug 2019', '2019-07-11T00:00:00', '2019-08-21T00:00:00', 18, 18, '57', 'Office Cloud - Practice Management Data (for Q3 deadline)', 'CLP-1273'),
