    ('877', 'Practice Level Report - Global Performance Sumamry', 'As an Office user, I want to review what is driving the performance of my accounts in a single report. This allows me to efficiently review each account instead of having to run one report for each client or accounts.*Acceptance Criteria*1) Report will live in a Practice Management Reports modal in the Office Cloud Home Page. The modal will include option to run any three of the practice management reports. The modal should be a simple list of the reports with a Run button to kick off the report generation process.2) Once the user clicks run, a dialogue box should appear asking the user to select a "Start and End Date". Start date can be any date. The end date will always be聽 1) most recent month end date or 2) previous month end.3) The report output will be excel and the data included will be the same as the 3x report.4) Settings are locked down except for "Start and End Date". Settings used are: * End date must be "l * Return Type follows global reporting settings * Fee Type - always net of fees * Report Type - Excel * Currency follows global reporting settings * Display amount and % for each asset class breakdown on account level and practice aggregated data. * Exclude: ** Inactive clients ** Prospects ** Closed accounts (closed before end date) ** Account excluded from client aggregate ** Shared clients ** -Unmanaged assets/accounts.- {color:#ffab00}Cannot support in phase 1.{color} ** {color:#ffab00}No Aggregate figures.{color}5) After running report user receives message saying we are generating your report (official content to come). Message will be the same regardless of calculation time.6) After report is complete, user receives message saying report is available in the reports section (official content to come).聽 This behavior is the same as 3x.7) Data should be calculated via the nightly batch process if possible. If not, the report should be run on-demand.8) Please see visual for possible design of how report will look in the Reports Grid.9) Admin user should see all accounts in practice/firm. Advisor should see just their accounts.聽*Suggested Content for Report Generation Window*What You''ll See In This Report * The report displays each of your accounts'' performance returns grouped by client. Return figures used time-weighted return and net of fees methodologies.What You Won''t See * Inactive Clients and Accounts * Accounts Closed before Report Date * Prospects * Shared Clients', 60, 5, 2, '#9faebf', '2019-07-11T00:00:00', '2019-08-21T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud - Jul-Aug 2019', '2019-07-11T00:00:00', '2019-08-21T00:00:00', 27, 25, '57', 'Office Cloud - Practice Management Data (for Q3 deadline)', 'CLP-1274'),
