    ('879', 'Practice Management Report - Global Unrealized Gain/Loss Report', 'As an Office user, I want to review the unrealized gains and losses of my accounts in a single report. This allows me to efficiently review my accounts instead of having to run one report for each client or accounts.*Acceptance Criteria*1) Report will live in a Practice Management Reports modal in the Office Cloud Home Page. The modal will include option to run any three of the practice management reports. The modal should be a simple list of the reports with a Run button to kick off the report generation process.2) Once the user clicks run, a dialogue box should appear asking the user to select an "As of Date". The two options for this report will be last month end and last business day. The default is last month end. No other setting options should be displayed. However, we do need an information icon indicating what settings are being used.3) The report output will be excel and the data included will be the same as the 3x report.4) Settings are locked down except for "As of Date". Settings used are: * Report Type: Excel * Do NOT apply Less Dividend Reinvestment from Cost Calculation and Less Capital Gain Reinvestment from Cost Calculation * Currency follows Global Reporting Settings * Display amount and % for each asset class breakdown on account level and practice aggregated data. * Exclude: ** Inactive clients ** Prospects ** Closed accounts (closed before end date) ** Account excluded from client aggregate ** Shared clients ** Unmanaged assets/accounts.聽 Cannot be supported in Phase 1.5) After running report user receives message saying we are generating your report (official content to come). Message will be the same regardless of calculation time.6) After report is complete, user receives message saying report is available in the reports section (official content to come).聽 This behavior is the same as 3x.7) Data should be calculated via the nightly batch process. If not, the report should be run on-demand.8) Please see visual for possible design of how report will look in the Reports Grid.9) Admin user should see all accounts in practice/firm. Advisor should see just their accounts.聽*Suggested Content for Report Generation Window*What You''ll See In This Report * The report displays a list of each account''s positions and its associated gain/loss by amount and percent. in Excel format. Market value, share quantity, and % of account are also included. The dividend and capital gain reinvestment are included in the cost figures.What You Won''t See * Inactive Clients and Accounts * Accounts Closed before Report End Date * Prospects * Shared Clients聽', 62, 5, 2, '#1954a0', '2019-07-11T00:00:00', '2019-08-21T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud - Jul-Aug 2019', '2019-07-11T00:00:00', '2019-08-21T00:00:00', 14, 14, '57', 'Office Cloud - Practice Management Data (for Q3 deadline)', 'CLP-1275'),
