    ('884', 'HTML Support', 'Establish milestones and plans to support 鈥?and ultimately deprecate 鈥?HTML components as we transition to packaging by component.聽 * Evangelize web components first聽 * As teams begin to upgrade to web components, gradually socialize path to deprecate HTML.聽 * What are costs / benefits of supporting聽HTML?聽If we deprecate HTML, how would that simplify our implementation聽going forward?聽 * Work with product teams to understand barriers to adopting web components.聽聽 * Need to ensure web components are flexible or configurable enough to support all use cases.聽 * Deprecate on a per-component basis?聽', 9, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 2, 1, null, null, 'MDS-7763'),
    ('885', 'Axis values and labels', 'A number of teams have logged defects and/or feature requests relating to display of x and y axis labels in charts. Most relate to cases where labels are longer than expected 鈥?or at least longer than our charts were designed to gracefully handle 鈥?and could theoretically be resolved 鈥?at least in the short term 鈥?by establishing clear limits for maximum label size. The reality is that long labels are not uncommon, and the number of requests in this area speaks to a broader need to provide product teams with more robust options for handling unwieldy labels.聽 聽IN SCOPE FOR Q2/Q3 2019: - Improve guidance on best practices (MDS-7403)聽 - Explore feasibility of wrapping x axis labels to 3 lines with truncation (MDS-7462) - For x axis labels, give product teams option to adjust the number of frequency of values displayed (MDS-5996)聽OUT OF SCOPE BUT MAY BE CONSIDERED AS FUTURE DIRECTION: - Make display of values (MDS-5996) responsive to chart size, for example display every nth value only after specified breakpoint is hit, or calculate the value of n based on available space. (TBD depending on scope) - For Horizontal Bar chart only, allow product teams to specify a max width for y axis labels, beyond which labels are truncated - For Horizontal Bar chart only, make max width setting responsive to chart size (TBD depending on scope)聽聽*Word Document:*聽[https://morningstaronline.sharepoint.com/:w:/s/designsystem-o365group/ESJkM1hXIuBMh7F_vAjNjFYBIct2AItQRR-EcZEtNEMNqw?e=UZaSqa]聽', 2, 0, 5, null, null, '2019-08-15T00:00:00', null, 'MDS - 2019 Q3', '2019-06-25T00:00:00', '2019-09-30T00:00:00', 18, 14, '105', 'Chart Improvements', 'MDS-7725'),
    ('886', 'Morningstar Style Guide', 'The Morningstar style guide is a primary resource for writers and editors that governs the way the company uses language in all of its products, from research reports and blog posts to marketing emails and magazine articles. It is currently a PDF that is housed in several locations on our intranet and distributed to various departments via email. * The goal of this effort is to consolidate this content and make it accessible to writers, editors, designers, and others within Morningstar that may have use for it.聽聽 * Attached document contains additional background and details.聽 * *Scope of this epic is limited to Milestone 1 in the attached, pending the outcome of discovery around technical approach. Future investment TBD based on what we learn from Milestone 1.*聽聽', 12, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 1, 0, null, null, 'MDS-7714'),
