    ('890', 'Contribution', 'Individual contributors and teams worldwide have product design ideas with potential to transform our business. How do empower them to do so?How can we provide tooling and processes聽to allow contributors to: * Learn what similar problems have already been solved by Morningstar teams * Connect and collaborate with like-minded individuals who have interest in working on those problems * Prototype, test, and validate, their ideas against customer and business requirements * Tap into existing Morningstar resources for inner-sourcing, design, architecture, and engineering to develop their ideas * Access systems, repositories, and tools as necessary to complete the work * Publish their work in a shared repository where it can be reviewed, hardened, and potentially extended by other teams, and ultimately contributed back to MDS.Through user mapping, storyboarding, and other techniques 鈥?a 3-5 day design sprint? 鈥?elaborate high-level requirements and a testable prototype for a proposed solution that is usable, technically feasible, and viable from a business perspective.', 5, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 8, 1, null, null, 'MDS-7472'),
    ('891', 'MDS Coverage Pilot', 'Provide product teams with automated methods to stress test their MDS implementation and identify areas where聽 coverage in the UI could be improved. For example, to quickly locate areas where MDS components or styles have not been referenced correctly.聽This ticket is a result of some recent team conversations around wanting to better understand聽_how_ teams are implementing MDS and whether or not teams are getting the full value of what MDS provides, from a perspective of inheriting future updates to MDS for free.One rough idea of a way to do this would be to create a "stress testing" version of the MDS library that changes everything (components, constants, etc) to be a very noticeable color. Teams would install this stress test version of MDS in to a branch of their product and have clear visibility of _where_ they are maintaining links to MDS library styles.Alternatively we could look at tooling to scrape application pages for the expected style references.聽This will help to point out places where teams could be using constants more, places where markup customizations are breaking their linkage to components, etc.聽===============================Possible approaches * Create a report by analyzing the quality of coverage within our codebase. For example see聽[https://segment.com/blog/driving-adoption-of-a-design-system/]聽for one possible approach.聽 * Track the number of times a given component is invoked or a given action is triggered in the UI. For example, this could be done using Google Analytics Events, or a tool like Heap.聽 * Scrape application pages to assess how often elements like buttons and links are formatted using the expected MDS styles. See linked Codepen prototype for an example.聽 * Other ideas TBD. The intent of this ticket is to guide discovery, not prescribe a solution.聽Questions * Can we聽 coverage by component? For example report the number of buttons, top hats, etc? * Report the number of web components vs HTML? * Automate reporting for all pages in a given application? * Add a property in all web components that allows us to turn on visual highlighting of web components?聽ResourcesGoogle Analytics Events:聽聽[https://support.google.com/tagmanager/answer/6106716?hl=en)]聽CSS-only solution for UI tracking:聽[https://www.smashingmagazine.com/2014/10/css-only-solution-for-ui-tracking/]聽聽Heap analytics info and standards at Morningstar:聽聽[https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/DWM/Heap+Analytics+Info+and+Standards]Driving adoption of a design system (shared by Nad)https://segment.com/blog/driving-adoption-of-a-design-system/?utm_campaign=Design%2BSystems%2BWeekly&utm_medium=email&utm_source=Design_Systems_Weekly_91Visualizations         https://assets.contents.io/asset_4oNkucmh.png	https://assets.contents.io/asset_AhwoqoFO.png聽聽聽', 11, 2, 5, null, '2019-07-08T00:00:00', '2019-09-29T00:00:00', null, 'MDS - 2019 Q3', '2019-06-25T00:00:00', '2019-09-30T00:00:00', 6, 4, '85', 'Coverage & Support', 'MDS-6824'),
