    ('943', 'IX | Goal Selection (Circle Back - Jason)', 'Review and refine user flow, visuals, and聽interactions for production-fidelity goal planning聽prototype, including coding refinements. Included in this flow are: # Orientation welcome note # Quote # Group/Goal ("I want to") # Summary screen of selected goals ** Summary screen that allows users to set goals for specific decades in their lives ** Summary screen聽that allows users to聽view, add & remove life goals*What do users need most right now?* * Be oriented in the聽flow and understand what they are about to do/currently聽doing ** Sign posts ** Progress聽indicator (non-stepper) * Select goals that聽resonate with them and feel personal鈥攕omething they''ll be聽more likely to stick with for the long term鈥攐r the ability to create their own.*What''s critical?* * Interaction should be performant - users should be able to add, remove, set an order to, and view all of their selections.聽 * Copy and design should be clear about expectation of the user. * Recording the interactions and assigning them to the Guest ID (even if only on browser) * Identify bumpers to keep users on the happy path and develop accompanying UI*How does this fit into the service?* * Kicks off the user''s goal setting journey and beyond * Starts to build trust by聽being聽a service that "looks like me"聽聽聽', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, '64', 'InvEx Goal Onboarding Q2 MVP', 'IX-214'),
