    ('961', 'Financial Statement', 'There is plenty of information about a company that you''ll want to know as a value investor, but that you can''t get from a casual glance at a stock quote or from reading most stock market commentary.Financial reports are a company''s annual and quarterly performance results. You can learn a lot from a company''s annual report. It will explain what products and/or services the company sells and give you an idea of how the company sees itself. Here we will focus to build out the the dashboard for financial data, include below three important sections:* The balance sheet, also called statement of financial position, portrays the financial position of the company by showing what the company owns and what it owes at the report date. The balance sheet may be thought of as a snapshot, since it reports the company''s financial position as a specific point in time. Statement of changes in shareholders'' equity result from company profits or losses, dividends and/or stock issuance.* Income statement - can be thought of more like a motion picture, since it reports on how a company performed during the period(s) presented and show whether that company''s operation have resulted in a profit or loss.* Cash flow - reports on the company''s cash movements during the period(s) separating them by operating, investing and financing activities.', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, 'DELETE ME (old SAL)', '2019-07-01T00:00:00', '2019-09-30T00:00:00', 0, 0, null, null, 'SALSZ-2459'),
