    ('1059', 'Suppressed holding issue', '*Background:*聽In聽Q3 2017, the rules on portfolio disclosure were altered to help Australia. Portfolios that were previously fully suppressed now had their top 10 holdings released, ahead of the full holdings later. This is a particular issue for EMEA because compared to the US, EMEA gets data not only more frequently, but also much faster, and in return the data is embargoed for the majority of funds. (Please use the fund聽Schroder QEP Global Core Eq I Inc to test)*Issue:*聽Various聽attribution and holdings-based capabilities across Direct are affected as these components believe they are analysing a full portfolio despite reading only top 10 holdings. Below are the Presentation Studio components where the issue has been identified.*1锛墈color:#333333}Holdings-Based Style Map ( HB Style Map -Chart 锛墈color}*In the attachment "HB Style Map" it is evident that the style map looks correct when looking at the holdings as of 30/11/2017, however style maps as of 31/12/2017, 31/01/2018 and 28/02/2018 look off. The HB Style map聽has advanced settings to let users decide on which portfolio to choose (including "most recent common portfolio" setting),聽however this isn''t enough聽to forestall the top 10 effect.聽**聽Please refer to JIRA https://msjira.morningstar.com/browse/DSSV-7738Data source need to be provided by Data Production team:聽https://msjira.morningstar.com/browse/DPO-12915聽*Note*: Cloud HBSM chart has the same issue as 3.x. When the issue is fixed, please notify Primrose Wang/Rong Wu to verify data in Cloud.聽_*2) Top 20 Shared Stock Holdings (Comparision:Holdings Report) - FIXED at Jan 21, 2019 Release*__In the attachment "Top 20 Shared Holdings" you can see what the original weightings of the Top 10 holdings are in Workspace at the bottom of the picture, while at the top you can see that the weightings are then rescaled in Presentation Studio because the component assumes that the Top 10 holdings are the "full portfolio" (only weightings)._聽_Please refer to JIRA聽https://msjira.morningstar.com/browse/DSSV-6168._{color:#172b4d}_*3)*聽*Common Holdings*聽 *(* *Holdings*聽 *Similarity - Chart* *) - FIXED at Jan 21, 2019 Release*_{color}_In the attachment "Common Holdings1" you can see similarity of holdings between the UK (Lazard Emerging Markets A Acc) fund and Offshore fund (Lazard Emerging Markets Eq A Acc) on the portfolio date of 30/11/2017 (full holdings). The picture is completely different when looking at holdings as of 28/02/2018 ("attachment "Common Holdings2").__Please refer to JIRA聽https://msjira.morningstar.com/browse/DSSV-7740_聽*4)Time Series - {color:#333333}Chart{color}*When creating model portfolios we can see that the Size and the Value-Growth scores begin to behave strangely after the portfolio suppression (see attachment "Time Series").聽{color:#333333}Please refer to JIRA聽https://msjira.morningstar.com/browse/DSSV-7808{color}{color:#333333}Data source need be supported from Portfolio Calculation team by this project:聽https://msjira.morningsta', -1, 0, 5, '#a59e89', null, null, null, null, null, null, 4, 4, null, null, 'DSSV-6100'),
