    ('1263', 'Apply user global settings to search results', 'As a user, I want my global settings/preferences for country, exchanges, and currency to be reflected in my security search results, so that I get the most relevant responses to my queries.聽Details: GCS uses a "best match" feature (GCS-42) which I''d like to expand over the entire platform. It checks the search results against a user''s designated preferences, in the following order (from their ticket):聽 # GCS-465聽聽-User''s import preferences (exchange and currency)-聽 ## -Compare exchange to聽LS01Z- ## -Compare currency to聽OS05M- # Currency from global settings (if Base Currency or Category Currency, go to next) ## Compare currency to聽OS05M # Country from global settings ## Compare Country to聽OS01V ## Compare Country to OS020聽Adding this layer of user preferences will allow us to provide user consistency across the platform, and give users a more relevant search experience - with results tailored to their region and currency settings. This will add significant value when moving into international markets.', 135, 0, 1, null, '2019-11-14T00:00:00', '2019-12-25T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud_Q1 2020', '2019-12-26T00:00:00', '2020-03-18T00:00:00', 0, 0, '181', 'Search Usability in Cloud', 'CLP-1120'),
    ('1265', 'Making Research Portal Topics, Publications, and Authors searchable', 'To better position Authors, Topics & Publications in returning search results and take users directly to their respective pages. Topics, Publications and Authors hosted in the Research Publishing System API (collections) can being returned as documents.-Search will need to index and return the results in their Search api -Long term, Search will need to work with Research Portal to understand synonyms that should resolve to topics (e.g. if a user types in ESG, we should elevate the Sustainability Matters topic) -Framework and Research Portal will need to get the search results elevated in the search box to be a top hit when a user searches for Topics, Authors, Publications', 539, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-687'),
    ('1266', 'Support real-time updates for custom data points in data point search', 'The search team is working on an enhanced data point search service. This service will include both Morningstar and custom data points.聽Because custom data points can be added, removed, or updated at any time, the search service needs to be aware of those changes in real-time so the search results for custom data points are accurate.So, we need a way to send real-time information about custom data points to the search service.More specifically the real-time load needs to capture and send information about these actions: * New data point created * Data point deleted * Update to Name, Display Name, Owner UUID or Product of an existing custom data point ** Owner and product changes should really never happen, but let''s account for this just in case.The real-time feed should include this information: * CDP ID * Action taken: add, delete, update * Information about the data point: ** Name ** Display Name ** Owner UUID ** Product Name of the owner (e.g. "Direct") *** This will always be Direct right now, but there may be others later 鈥?we should join to APPUSRRLTD to get thisOther Notes: * This epic is for the *on-premise* solution only. There will be further discussions about moving this search to AWS on the framework created by Amine''s team in the future. * The team had previously discussed that this real-time data update will be achieved through kafka messaging style data loads. This will required the CDM team to build a producer and the search team to build a consumer for this information * This real-time feed will only cover custom data point information, not any information about values for the data points', 774, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-416'),
