    ('1469', 'On Demand Data for PFM [Q3 2019]', '[https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/SWDO/On+Demand+Update+Import+PFM]*PFM events that will impact user aggregation, budget, or on demand status:* * Login:聽CP-2777 ** If (1) a CWP user logs in/PFM component is instantiated, (2) their aggregation status is A4 or A5 and (3) their on demand O1 status time stamp is more than an hour ago, then switch their on demand status to O2. * Account Aggregation:聽CP-2346,聽CP-2664, CP-2760 ** If a user''s on demand status is O2, then trigger account aggregation. ** If (1) the BAA component triggers account aggregation and (2) the user''s aggregation status is A1, then switch their aggregation status to A2. ** If (1) account aggregation is successful and (2) the user''s on demand status is O2, then switch their on demand status to O3. If it''s unsuccessful, then switch their on demand status to O1. ** If (1) account aggregation is successful and (2) the user''s aggregation status is A2, then switch their aggregation status to A3.聽If it''s unsuccessful, then switch their aggregation status to A1. * Import:聽CP-2347, CP-2348 ** If a user''s on demand status is O3, then trigger import and calculations. ** If a user''s aggregation status is A3, then trigger import and calculations. ** If (1) import and calculations are successful and (2) the user''s on demand status is O3, then switch their on demand status to O1. If they''re unsuccessful, then switch their on demand status to O1. ** If (1) import and calculations are successful and (2) the user''s aggregation status is A3, then switch their on demand status to A5. If they''re unsuccessful, then switch their on demand status to A4. ** If import and calculations are successful, then refresh the data in Aggregated Account List and PFM components. * 聽Set a first time savings target/budget:聽CP-2778 ** If (1) a user''s budget status is B2 and (2) they click on the button that sets a savings target, then set their budget status to B3. ** If (1) a user''s budget status is B2, (2) they don''t have a savings gap but want to adjust their savings target and (3) they hit save in the Edit Savings Target/Budget component, then set their budget status to B3. ** If (1) a user''s budget status is B2, (2) they have a savings gap but want to adjust their budget and (3) they hit save in the Edit Savings Target/Budget component, then set their budget status to B3. * Delete an aggregated account:聽CP-2771 ** If (1) a user deletes an aggregated account and (2) they no longer have any aggregated accounts, then set their aggregation status to A1.*PFM UI components and their interaction with user statuses:* * Aggregated Account List: ** A1 - empty CTA state CP-2765 ([https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/d/main#/console/15244152/316934343/preview]) ** A2 - first time aggregation in progress聽CP-2766 ([https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/d/main#/console/15244152/316934339/preview]) ** A3 - first time import and calculations in progress (same as A2) ** A4/O1 - import/calculation failure (same as A5) ** A5/O1 - fu', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, 'Financial Planning - Q3 2019', '2019-07-01T00:00:00', '2019-09-30T00:00:00', 0, 0, '55', 'CWP: Personal Financial Management (PFM) MVP', 'CP-2112'),
