    ('1481', 'Research Email Alerts on Followed Authors, Topics, Publications', '*JTBDs:* Research Topic, Publication and Author followers: When I''m monitoring a Topic, Author and/or Publication, I want to be alerted whenever Morningstar publishes any research content referencing any of the Topic, Authors or Publications that interest me.When I鈥檓 responsible for monitoring thematic content (e.g. topics like Sustainable Investing, publications like Asset Flows or Authors like Ben Johnson); I want to be alerted whenever Morningstar publishes any research content referencing any of these.聽聽*Background:* Topics and Publications are a feature that allows Morningstar to showcase original, innovative Morningstar content to users of Research Portal at any given time. The Morningstar content presented in topics are a the result of a curated library of research content assembled and provided by Research Portal鈥檚 site editor. Publications are Morningstar鈥檚 regularly broadcast compendium of Institutional and Advisor research offerings.聽Following Topics, Publications and Analyst (Author) pages provide an easy way for users to track when Morningstar鈥檚 global analyst team produces and publishes new content that is relevant to a user鈥檚 investment strategies or idea generation interests.聽 * We assume that Cloud users care more about the timeliness of security related research alerting (e.g. Manager research about funds in their lists like DODGX) rather than thematic research alerting and they should be treated differently. * We assume that Cloud users want an easy and intuitive way to sign up and opt-in to receive for thematic research digest emails they follow*MVP for this Project* * Allow users that "Follow" Morningstar Authors, Topics, or Publications Research (collections identified and curated by us) the option to sign up to receive email alerts for their email account聽 ** From the 鈥淔ollow鈥?workflow ** From Research Portal Alerts page ** From Alerts app * Sign up/Cancel Alert email聽 * Topics, Authors, Publications that triggered the alert * Receive email notifications ** Document name聽 ** Document summary聽聽 ** Link to the doc in RP聽 ** Unsubscribe from alert email * Email will be a daily digest * Notifications will link back to the single document in Research Portal * HTML email - digest only? * Need to consider what if digest includes one of the documents that has multiple topics, publications, and/or author鈥檚 tagged聽 * Weekly Digest Notification * Frequency - user need to cut through the noise, the frequency at which they receive notifications via email will be handled differently than Security research and only arrive weekly as a digest.聽*Risks/Open Questions/Considerations* # Duplicate Alerts -聽Topics, Publications, and Analyst page content is not mutually exclusive. A variety of combinations could occur that we will be tasked to design a good experience around. For instance, if they decide to, user鈥檚 can 鈥淔ollow鈥?the Asset Flows _Publication_, the _Author_ Kevin McDevitt and the Manager Research North American _Topic._ The monthly A', 697, 0, 5, '#069de2', null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-982'),
