    ('1490', 'Office Security Mapping Issue Solution', '*Issue description:*When a client imports custodial data into Morningstar Office, the product maps securities being imported to the corresponding security in the product鈥檚 security database. The mapping logic used is complex and securities mapped using a reused ticker may result in an incorrectly mapped security. For example, Box, Inc. uses the ticker BOX. The ticker BOX was previously used by SeaCube Container Leasing Ltd. SeaCube Container Leasing is delisted and no longer traded on public markets. Its ticker has been reused by Box, Inc. During the import process, custodian position files containing the ticker BOX map to SeaCube Container Leasing by default even though the account truly owns Box, Inc.聽*Solutions:* # Import team is fixing the mapping logic to make sure we are not mapping securities to old inactive securities or other securities with the same ticker # Compare imported security price to morningstar security price and show any differences to the user on logging into Office # Show any reused securities to the user so that the user is aware of such securities # Force the user to see the warning of any incorrect securities being held as a holding for any client or account # Save log of such warning messages and store it in the database for future audit #', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 15, 15, null, null, 'DCV-2860'),
