    ('1609', 'Holiday Calendar Solution', '*List of Reasons why we observe data issues during holidays*:* NAV data globally do not have value on holidays (regional)* We do not have one source of truth as a holiday calendar service based on regional and exchange.* Equity data do not update data on holidays. Specifically EquityDB (geproddb62).* Any data set (for example, NAV, Market Price, etc.) do not update data on weekends except Return Index (TRI, GRI, DMRI). NOTE: Original source of RI data set is Timeseries* QUANT DB populate data on holidays to calculate data set like Risk Model. *Proposed Solution / Approach To Consider:** Build or agree on single source of holiday calendar (e.g. XOI Holiday DB Table) database as source of truth for Morningstar and communicate.* System to provide information within service when holiday related data is not available so that consumer can make decision based on the response.* Notification / awareness process when there is no data to be processed on a holiday to reduce false alerts and same communication every year* On holidays source (Collection) to copy data from yesterday that MUST include information such as Morningstar_Generated, AsOfDate, Holiday_Infomation (so that service can be queried), other metadata as needed. Downstream data process can consume and make decision systematically which can potentially be surfaced through API (possibly). In that way product will know why data is empty or has AsOfDate different from today.Whichever solution is implemented, it must be well communicated to all products so that during holidays we can avoid false positives either from Data Issues reported by Product or from Monitoring. This will improve data consistency and handle Holiday gracefully.', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'DTCLAN-300'),
