    ('1652', 'New data (XOI/TSDB - Kafka - Mart) workflow''s quality', 'NZ was used as data source for Mart in the past. NZ will be gone. New data source, XOI/TSDB and new update method (Kafka producer and consumer) are used to populate Marts after NZ retires. The main goal of this Epic is to make sure we can measure if Mart is in SYNC with the data source in a timely manner so that we can guarantee the new workflow is functioning. For each table in the mart (that is affected by the new workflow), we need to check the data source and compare the data coverage with that in Mart. For example, the DRI table in the mart, the number of securityIds should be roughly the same as its data source. The number of records with yesterday''s DRI value not equal to NULL, should be roughly the same (less than 0.1% ) as that in the data source. If measure the total number of records is not reasonable (because many to one or one to many table mapping between the source and mart), we can pick specific universe, e.g., U.S Open end funds, and measure the source vs Mart.聽The output of this measurement need to be reported daily through dashboard or API call and make available to operation team. POs need to define critical threshold for Operation team.聽', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'DTCCHI-434'),
