    ('1686', 'PPI-3802 Fixed Income Indexes', 'Target deadline: 2019 Q1https://msjira.morningstar.com/browse/PPI-3802client:VeloMorningstar Indexes is developing a suite of new fixed income indexes to be launched in Q1 2019. In 2019, we budgeted 350k in new sales across 20 logos for this fixed income data, but we need a delivery platform.聽*Goal*: As Indexes business, we want to deliver new Morningstar fixed income indexes using centralized Morningstar ecosystem to external clients so that we can serve our clients better and in a one-Morningstar fashionICE data(Calculation agent, third party data)>> load in mart (by Data Service Team)>> surface through APIv2>> Velo generate feeds for clientsICE: Intercontinental Exchangehttps://www.intercontinentalexchange.com/index*Attention:*聽There will likely be entitlement work to ensure that no unauthorized users of APIv2 have access to data where source = ICE. This type of parameter specific entitlement does not currently exist in APIv2聽Include:Index dataPortfolio dataHolding dataProposed Approach:Based on preliminary discussions with the Data services and Velo teams, here is the proposed approach for meeting these requirements:Data services team will load ICE data into the data martICE data will be surfaced through APIv2 using either (a) existing data points with a new source parameter (i.e. Source = ICE) or (b) New data pointsVelo will retrieve the ICE data using APIv2 and generate feeds for the index clients (this allows us to take advantage of all the feed setup, data point selection, etc. that already exists in Velo)Index product management has created several data packages targeted at different client profiles/use cases.NOTE: There will likely be entitlement work to ensure that no unauthorized users of APIv2 have access to data where source = ICE. This type of parameter specific entitlement does not currently exist in APIv2聽', -1, 5, 5, '#6EBDAB', null, null, null, null, null, null, 9, 9, '261', 'Publish New Morningstar F