    ('1739', 'Ability to call Office Positions end Points (Sets) via Oaut2 by third parties', 'From Todd:Dermot & Rahul have been exchanging emails on 3rd party integration for the purposes of calling our API鈥檚.  We have identified two auth flows for our June 30th commitment (traditional login, and delegated login for velo via ClientId) and Dermot has identified the next flow he鈥檇 like to support which basic OAuth.  I think the backend is transferable and what we are really talking about is a clean way (no copy/paste of ClientIds/AccessTokens) of integrating. My understanding of the use-case is simple (let鈥檚 assume that the 3rd party is RedTail CRM for ease of explanation):User authenticates to RedTail using their RedTail credentials in the normal way.Within RedTail there is an opportunity to provide an integration with Morningstar Office Cloud (or other app depending on the integration).RedTail instantiates a login from within their app which opens a Morningstar Login window within their product.User logs into Morningstar using their Morningstar credentials which RedTail never possesses.On success, a token is transparently provided to RedTailRedTail can now make API calls on-behalf of the customer using that revocable connection.  I think that the vast majority of the work is within UIM, and we鈥檇 like to piggyback on the JWT related work we鈥檝e done with backend & EAMS integration.', 201, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-541'),
    ('1740', 'PDF App to AWS Cloud', '1. Move PDF batch to AWS Batch.Status: Done and Live.New PDF Batch system will leverage AWS Cloud Watch Event and AWS Batch. AWS Cloud Watch Event creates rules to set time and submit batch job to AWS Batch. Jobs can be prioritized. Running environments can be pre-configed and automatically scale up and down. AWS Batch pulls latest docker image from AWS ECR for each job, automatically build a docker container on pre-configed compute environments (servers, cpus ...) and run the batch job. After job finished, AWS Batch will stop and shutdown servers.2. Move Chicago DR to AWS CloudStatus: In ProgressWe want to shutdown all Chicago DR servers and keep an infrustructure script in AWS. When there is a DR, we can run this script to build up all of our applications in AWS Cloud and switch our GTM to these AWS Cloud servers. In this case, we don''t need to physically own Chicago servers and this will help us save our operation cost.', 5, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 39, 36, null, null, 'PDFR-4426'),
