    ('1753', 'Enhancement to Impacted Accounts - Notes', 'The structure of ML accounts often include model portfolios and custom SMAs as holdings within those accounts. This is different than the typical account structure that we original built for. As a reminder: the impacted accounts functionality within notes today (when selected) and if there is a security tagged to the note, looks to see which users in that firm have accounts that hold that specific security. From there, the note get sent automatically to that auto-generate group of users and they are able to see that impacted security in the context of the note. The current API we''re hooked up to does not work for models as holdings in accounts and we need to ensure that the M* id is being used for the custom SMAs (as it is to bring in performance data). The goal that if user A creates a note and tags it to Model B and user C has Model B within one of their accounts, User B would become part of that impacted accounts group so they would receive the note. or If User  A tags a note to a custom SMA (using M* mapped identifier) and User B holds that SMA in one of their accounts that User B would be part of the impacted accounts group.Please note: this is not contractually obligated work by 2/1 for ML but it does impact the experience for them since their account structure is unique.+Dependency: +In order to allow for this, we need the API team to confirm if there is an API that exists that includes the models as holdings and custom SMAs (using the M* identifier, so should be the same as any other security). For impacted accounts functionality, we depend on DataApiV2 endpoint /dataapi/v2/portfolios?holding={performanceId}. This endpoint can return accounts that contains a given holding. API team doesn鈥檛 have similar endpoint that can return accounts which contains a given model portfolio/SMA.', 423, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-984'),
