    ('1832', 'Portfolio Service API', 'Background:Currently, we have different APIs serving portfolio data, such as PMS API, PA API, Vanguard API, Fidelity API, etc. Our goal is to have a standard service layer API that is both internal and external facing, in the short term acting as a proxy to relay the incoming request to the related API, based on Product such as Direct, Office, EDM, IWT, etc. and in the long term potentially using the same engine to calculate the same data field for all Products. The benefit will be that if in the future, if we are going to consolidate all those APIs (for the reason of simplicity, scalability, maintainability, or other technology reasons), the consumer of the Portfolio Service API would not be impacted. The scope of this API could expand to more products that need portfolio data, such as AWS, .com in the future. Our long term vision is to create a Portfolio Service API that will power and serve all portfolio data and calculation results. Each data field, as well as input parameters and output format will be clearly documented and will be product agnostic. For example, Market value, we will power the Market value for all products, all different types of portfolios such as positional with history and transactional accounts, etc.PBC MVP (Minimum Viable Product) data fieldsThe data fields we are going to support in this Phase I will be the data from the wiki page below, for positional with history accounts. If the column of 鈥淩equested by Portfolio Software鈥?is marked as 鈥淴鈥?(you can click on the column header to do the sorting), then it is in scopehttps://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/DWH/Portfolio+Data+Inventory%2C+Sample+Calcs+and+Progress', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'DOPAMAT-760'),
