    ('1841', 'PMS API - DWM', 'This Epic will track the work that PMS API should do to support PBC needs. Currently we have below two tasks target to PBC March release, but may not limited to these in the future.1.	PMS API supports PBC MVP data, the 44 data points in PBC data list(attached excel in Requirements Document), they have been supported by ADS but not in PMS API.Estimation: Server side Dev - 3 weeks, Portfolio Accounting QA 鈥?3 weeks, testing method should be similar with RS API testing.Plan: create JIRA tickets, and put them into next sprint backlog.2.	PMS API supports 3.X portfolios: New/Edit/Delete 1) Investment Policy; 2) Model Portfolio; 3) Editable Client AccountEstimation: Server side Dev 鈥?5 weeks (2w for policy, 1w for model, 2w for account), Portfolio Accounting QA 鈥?estimation will be provided laterPlan: arrange into sprint after getting detailed request like which settings should be supported.Note: 1)	the scope doesn''t include performance related, if have performance request, then we need do re-estimate. 2)	the scope doesn''t include Account Group and on-the-fly portfolio, which may be in scope later but currently we don鈥檛 know request details.', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'DOPAMAT-751'),
    ('1842', 'Custom Security Link Field', 'This story is to allow the home office user to create security link fields which can be leveraged for holdings of a portfolio.  A security link field is just a link to an existing M* tracked or User Defined security.  One example of a field which may be created is Firm Defined Benchmark.- Only a home office user can create the field and set attributes.  Home office users will want to name the field, and define whether all users in the firm are able to change the values or just read the values.  E.g. only a home office user can set that for FCNTX the Firm Defined Benchmark is the M* US Index and everyone else in the firm can use that benchmark, or anyone in the firm can not only read it but also change the Firm Defined Benchmark to M* Global Index. - All users in the firm should be able to add a security link field to a grid, sort on this field, group by this field, and calculate summary stats based on securities in this field.  When viewing the security link in the end product we should not show the ID but the resolved name for the ID.- All users in the firm should be able to easily find all investments which are assigned to any benchmarks which are set for any securities.  This means I want to see all the securities which don''t have M* US Index set within my set of investments.- Users who are permissioned to do so can easily change the linked security.- Users have a way to manually bulk change linked securities for multiple securities at once.- Users have a way to import linked securities in bulk.', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'DOPAMAT-750'),
