    ('1972', 'Dynamic Calculations for Return Based Stats in SQL Mart', 'What is dynamic calculation? A simple example is rolling returns of a fund. Another example is Alpha based a specific benchmark, or of a specific time period, or in a specific currency. In a word, dynamic calculation is triggered when a user defines a calculation based on an ad-hoc start/end date, benchmark/risk free rate, or currency. It is commonly used by all Direct users. Why is this project critical? This is because the current tech solution for dynamic calculation in data API (which is the back of Cloud) cannot meet Direct users'' needs. In Direct Cloud today, it takes 8-10 seconds to display rolling returns of 15 funds in their base currencies. If I change the currency to USD, it takes another 6-8 seconds. If I bring in another column Alpha with a specific benchmark, it takes another 6-12 seconds to calculate. All above actions take less than 1.5 seconds in Direct 3.x.', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'DTPA-1975'),
    ('1973', 'Use Case: Grid Data Screener - US Open End Fund ONLY', 'MER-15154All actions once the grid is loaded such as Locate, Sort, Delete, Move, Use side slider, should have very low latency or act as the grid does with less than 1K investments currently. Raise grid 1st page results to 2K, versus 1K.   We should really see how high we can push this limit. Part of this use case is to grid page load for 1K investments.Steps:* Login* From managed investment click on US Open-End Fund* Click screener popupTo get ~2k rows of data filter investment list using following -* Return with value 2* Morningstar Rating with 4 start rating* Then click OK to populate gridTo get ~1k rows of data filter investment list using following -* Return with value 1* Morningstar Rating with 5 start rating* Then click OK to populate gridAfter the grid is populated apply sort, locate etc.', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'DTPA-759'),
    ('1974', 'Onboarding/Access to Data API v2', 'Hello, As discussed with Dan, we are looking to get access to Data API v2 so we can prototype getting the data via our Matlab and R plug in.We already have an existing Apigee key.. Our goal would be to explore the data sets already available in Data API v2 and see how we can get this connected to our R and Matlab Plug in. Thank you.', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'DTPA-704'),
    ('1975', 'Cross Listing Data Enhancement', 'Certain exchange traded products are traded on multiple exchanges and/or in multiple currencies. In this case, one of those listings is considered the primary and will always be traded in the portfolio currency, while all others are considered cross listings and may or may not be traded in the portfolio鈥檚 currency. Due to this unique structure and limitations in Morningstar鈥檚 database, data for cross listings is incomplete in Morningstar products. For example, NAV, distribution, and therefore total returns are not available for cross listings in Direct 3.x or Direct Cloud.In addition, two smaller projects are also included in the scope of this project: (1) An adjustment to market price return methodology and (2) a new Market Capitalization Weight data point.This project seeks to improve cross listing data availability. The complete and signed-off requirements can be found in the attached Excel document. Please note that since sign-off a decision was made to limit scope to Neteeza and APIv2 only (no XOI or old stack). The details of this decision are documented in the attached PowerPoint presentation.', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'DTPA-660'),
