    ('1979', 'Scorecard Calculation', '*Purpose*The investment scorecard is used to assign weights and create custom criteria of quantitative and qualitative factors to calculate an overall score. Any numeric data points can be included in the scorecard.*Two Methods*+Standardized values+: converts raw data points topercentile rank and applies user selected weights to thosepercentile ranks. These weighted percentile ranks are thenaggregated to create the score for the investment.+Custom grades+: allows users to define rules for data pointsand assign a numeric, text, or symbol grade based on that criteria. Gradecolumns can then be added to the report for an individuallygraded data point, an aggregated grade for a time period, oran aggregated grade for an entire investment.', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'DTPA-2832'),
    ('1980', 'Grid/screen Integration', 'In this Epic, we are going to make sure different parts of data, objects and features works seamlessly in API and Cloud components.On data , we have Morningstar data and User defined data. Morningstar category vs Custom category. Morningstar return and user imported price and return.On Entity, we have Morningstar collected/defined securities/entities and user defined securities and entities. Open end fund vs custom fund and custom securitiesOn objects, we have list/screen, column set and IdlistOn features, we have dynamic calculation, ranking, grouping, locate, sort, screen, conditional format.We want to make sure user don''t notice that we have these different concept in our back end when they are using Cloud.', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'DTPA-2642'),
    ('1981', 'Fractional weighting methodology', 'Morningstar Research introduced a new methodology for calculating percentile ranks and fractional ranks (see the Project Details section in the linked document for details), which is based on assigning the same weights to distinct portfolios in the peer group of funds to be ranked for a numeric data point. For funds that are share classes of the same underlying portfolio in the peer group to be ranked, each share class that has value in the data point to be ranked will get the same fractional weight. Compared to current ranking methodology, in addition to the fractional weight change, the ranking formula has been changed as well.', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'DTPA-2631'),
