    ('2065', 'Add ''All Investments with Custom Data'' view for Apply Custom Content page', 'Today in CDM, you must pull up a list to view custom data. This makes it a little tough to review data you''ve imported if it''s not in a list.So, we want to add a new option to view "All Investments with Custom Data."When the user selects this option, instead of using a list we will display all securities that have data for the custom data points in the column set.The option would be a part of the list selection model like this:  !screenshot-1.png|thumbnail!+Here is what the finalized default logic would look like after we add this option+: * If the user has no custom data points > Default to Custom Data Points tab (no change) * If the user has custom data points > Default to the Apply Custom Content tab ** Has the user selected a list in CDM before? *** If yes: Default to that list *** If no: Default to "All Investments with Custom Data" (instead of the first alphabetical list) **** If ''All Investments with Custom Data'' is empty, then notify user and prompt them to open a list or add investments*After we make this change, here is what some common workflows would look like:* +User has never used CDM before+ 1. User is immediately directed to Custom Data Points section 2. Once they have added a data point, they navigate to Apply Custom Content 3. In Apply Custom Content, they see notification and tool tips to get started adding data+User who has used CDM before,聽but never switched the list and column set+ 1. User is taken to Apply Custom Content 2. All Investments with Custom Data and All Custom Data Points are shown+User who has used CDM before, and switched the list or column set previously+ 1. User is taken to Apply Custom Content 2. User sees the last list and column set they had open in Apply Custom Content', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'PBCCDI-1965'),
