    ('2083', 'Design for Report Warnings for Transactional Accounts', '*Issue:* Currently, Office Cloud users are not being warned in cases where the underlying account data in a transactional account may be causing inaccuracies in the calculations displayed in the reports they generate.聽 Sometime the inaccuracy is not large enough for the user to catch it by reviewing the report alone.聽 聽Without having these instances called to attention, advisors are at risk of聽 sharing inaccurate reports they have generated with their clients.{color:#ff0000}*Goal:*{color}聽To help advisor keep the trust of their clients by ensuring they only share reports with accurate data by helping them identify and correct potential issues with the underlying聽 transactional account data.*How it currently in 3x works:*聽 Because the system needs to be given the report time frame before it can calculate and come back with possible calculation issues, the user first goes through all the steps to generate a report (ad hoc or batch run).聽 Once calculation is complete the user is provided with the finished report & a warning file that lists out any potential issues for the given report period.聽 The user is not forced to act on anything, merely provided the information after the report is complete.聽[^Example of Report Warning in 3.x]聽 &聽[^report warning sample.txt] To correct the user has to update the underlying data and rerun the report. * *[Transactional Report Warnings.xlsx|https://morningstaronline-my.sharepoint.com/:x:/g/personal/kristen_carstensen_morningstar_com/EYBVDVxWKzlNgf_uvocqLUABoOmDcAAOPEZ-jNGtihFPJA?e=3UcWpV]* * *educational pdf from desktop:聽[^ReportWarnings.pdf]***聽*Dependencies*:聽 OC, Framework (warnings), DOPA (owners of calculations)*Out of Scope:* * being able to edit transactions or data in OC that isn''t聽already editable ** for example> if a certain transaction type is not editable in OC, the recommend needs to take that into account this phase. (long term goal is to edit all transactions... and them warnings an be updated accordingly) * Making major technical changes to when the system can currently flag these warnings.聽 ** So of the items may already be able to flag prior to report generation, if that is the case, its fine to use that in consideration for the solution.聽 ** Other items will not be easy to identify prior to the system actually running the on demand calcs. Once we move to reports being supported by Cloud Portfolios (this is a far out item currently(, then there will be more room to evaluate some more user friendly solutions around report warnings. ** Making use of Cloud Notifications. ** Updates to current Nav Menu.*Unknowns*: * Do we need to break out stories for AdHoc report generation vs Batch report generation? * Are any of these warnings things that can be called out sooner than post report generation?聽聽 * Should I be able to suppress or snooze low priority warnings ** for example: if I don''t report on cost basis in Office Cloud, I am not concerned with the ''transaction missing original cost or date informa', 68, 2, 5, '#a59e89', null, null, null, 'Cloud - Oct - Nov 2019', '2019-10-03T00:00:00', '2019-11-13T00:00:00', 13, 5, '66', 'Office Cloud - Data Management', 'OC-4763'),
