    ('2095', 'Rebalance API (MaaS)', 'As a PM or RIA, I would like to re-balance an individual account or households to match to its associated model or investment policy statement. I would to do this at various levels of sophistication. I would like to run a 1:  Simple Security, Account level rebalance, where I have a portfolio and am comparing it to a model portfolio I have just created by selecting and adjusting weights of the securities in the model and I would like to run a rebalance to generate trade proposals to rewieght the actual portfolio to the model without taking into account any tax implicationsWe absolutely need to start with 1 and then 2 to build out the calculation library for rebalancing. Then we need to leverage Office Cloud components + potentially build our own rebalancing workbook Then we need to start throwing in constraints to the calc library and update the workbookThen we can graduate to household and class level given that there is a workbook to play with 2: Simple Security, Account level rebalance with Tax implications, where I have a portfolio and am comparing it to a model portfolio I have just created by selecting and adjusting weights of the securities in the model and I would like to run a rebalance to generate trade proposals to rewieght the actual portfolio to the model with taking into account tax implications at the lot level of the holdings in my portfolio as well as avoid short term gains through wash salesWith regards to data points needed for 2, we will need 鈥渢rade lot inputs鈥?+ 鈥渓ast 30 days of transactions鈥?in addition to all the inputs for use case 2, Last 30 days of transactions and updated calculation logic when rebalancing such as Tax lot methods, and wash sale logic check.3: Run 1 and 2 for my entire practice/batch of accounts and build a notification engine + UI components sharing the output4: Add constraint handling 4,5: Household level, Class level re-balances with Tax implications and location optimizationI would like to do these tasks on the fly by providing or linking the inputs required to run the calculations and would like the output to be1: In a UI component review page where I can view and edit my trades as well as see a summary of the trades/Tax impact2: In a PDF report showing me the trades and Tax impact3: In an excel or .csv file that I can upload to my custodian or download to my deviceEnvironment : QABase URL: https://rbdev.ade586fc.easn.morningstar.com/RebalanceAPI/apiTest Endpoint URL:Environment : UATBase URL: https://rbuat.ade586fc.easn.morningstar.com/RebalanceAPI/apiMaaS URL: http://www.us-stg-api.morningstar.com/TRX-rebalanceEnvironment : ProductionBase URL: https://rbprod.ade87344.eas.morningstar.com/RebalanceAPI/apiMaaS URL: http://www.us-api.morningstar.com/TRX-rebalanceProduct Page:https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/PS/PID0449+-+TRX+-Rebalance+APIAPI Swagger:https://msstash.morningstar.com/projects/TRX/repos/rebalanceapi/browse/TRX_Rebalance_API/src/TRX_Rebalance_API/swagger.jsonTest Endpoint URL:Product ', 664, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 5, 5, null, null, 'TRX-993'),
