    ('2200', 'TRX Test Automation', '*Automation Epic*The goal is to create an automated regression test for TRX driven from the UI. The regression test will consist of tests, their expected results and a set of databases crafted to create many test case scenarios. Other types of tests, such as performance and API tests, will be described in other epics. The automation will be done with the Nightwatch tool. The expected results will be JSON files. The categories of development: WORKFLOW TESTS, PAGE OBJECTS, SETUP, BUGFIX.For the most part, test cases will not dynamically create their data through UI automation. Databases will be created which contain data that triggers the TRX features we want to test. When the common workflow automations are executed, many test cases will automatically happen. E.g., for the rebalancing tests, there will be clients which are OOB/not OOB, OOB/not OOB in cash, have trade restrictions which prevent rebalance, etc. This approach will allow the creation of new test cases without adding automation code. Just adding new聽_data_聽will make new test cases happen. WORKFLOW TESTS depend on PAGE OBJECTS. Page objects will be created as necessary to support the workflow tests. There are existing page objects and workflow tests to use as templates. E.g., pages: clientPage, modelCompliancePage, tests: clientPageTest, rebalanceSingle. *Agile* Each WORKFLOW TEST will likely be a single story with multiple tasks. The tasks will usually be the workflow test and its required page objects. Page objects can be developed in advance of their use by tests.*WORKFLOW TESTS* Create Nightwatch Tests that run and verify the main workflows in TRX. This story will rely mostly on the data in the QA template database to trigger the functions of TRX. Workflow tests will not usually create data during the test. *PAGE OBJECTS*A page object for each page (screen) in TRX must be able to do the following:Basics- Navigate to the page- Read parameters that identify the objects to be retrieved, e.g., a client ID.- Read the page and compare it to the expected result- Generate the expected result JSON for that page- Take action to move to the next step, if anyAdvanced- Filtering, sorting- Views, e.g., chart vs grid, trades vs positions- Sub-pages*SETUP* System setup data entry and retrieval. This is mostly to verify that the data entered persists in the database and can be retrieved. These tests will also be combined with the WORKFLOW TESTS to verify the data is used correctly, but to a smaller extent than in the WORKFLOW TESTS. E.g., System Settings, Client Detail, Models.聽*BUGFIX*Create tests which verify bug fixes to insure they are fixed and stay fixed', 820, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 11, 11, null, null, 'TRX-4111'),
