    ('2202', 'Apigee - Switch from Plain Text API key to Oauth2', '*From:* Santosh Yadav <[Santosh.Yadav@morningstar.com|mailto:Santosh.Yadav@morningstar.com]>  *Sent:* Thursday, August 01, 2019 2:58 AM *To:* Santosh Yadav <[Santosh.Yadav@morningstar.com|mailto:Santosh.Yadav@morningstar.com]> *Cc:* Core Services Team <[coreservicesteam@morningstar.com|mailto:coreservicesteam@morningstar.com]> *Subject:* Apigee - Switch from Plain Text API key to Oauth2聽_This email is sent to 鈥淭echnology Team List鈥?and 鈥淎pigee Users鈥?_聽All,聽If you are user of Apigee, please read on. Apigee supports two methods for APIs authentication i.e Plain text API key and Oauth2. Currently most of the Apigee users are using API key base authentication. API key based authentication is less secured and exhibits the security risk. API management is one of our core technology platforms and we need to adhere to the industry best practices to keep up to date with security trends. Oauth2 would help us enhance the Apigee security and lesson the business risk.聽*+What we expect from Product Teams:+*Product teams need to start using Oauth2 as the API authentication method instead of plain text API key. Please follow below page with entire information on how to use Oauth2 for the API calls.[https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/CORE/Apigee%3A+Request+Authentication%2C+Authorization+using+Application+Credentials]聽聽*+Developer Apps Tracker not using Oauth2:+*To monitor the progress of Oauth2 adoption, we will be updating below page regularly (at least monthly) to track the teams who are not using Oauth2.[https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/CORE/OAuth+usage+report]聽You can reach out to [coreservicesteam@morningstar.com|mailto:coreservicesteam@morningstar.com] if you need any help in implementing this change.聽*Note:*1) There is no commitment to remove API key based authentication globally at this moment. We will revisit it later after Oauth2 is adopted organization wide.2) Oauth2 access token is valid for 24 hours and you need to adopt your code to regenerate the token once expired (Above documentation contains the sample code for more information).', 240, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 13, 13, null, null, 'NERTS-306'),
