    ('2234', 'Volatility calculation of weekly return data', 'In Europe Performance teams use weekly returns to calculate volatility over various time periods, they don鈥檛 use monthly returns. We need weekly returns as calculation source before we can approach those teams.In your List, open 鈥淧erformance & Risk鈥?Column Data set and modify performance data points, such as 鈥淭otal Return (3Y 鈥?Mo end)鈥? In the 鈥淩eturn Frequency鈥?drop-down we are missing 鈥淲eekly鈥? Same goes for Standard Deviation, Sharpe Ratio, Alpha, Beta, etc.We need to add Weekly Return Frequency to support Performance teams in EMEA as they report and run analysis on a weekly basis. In Direct desktop we have 鈥淲eekly return鈥?as source data for these data points (second screenshot, using Alpha data point as an example). !weekly missing.png|thumbnail! Direct 3.x example: !3,x.png|thumbnail!', 854, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-1309'),
