    ('2249', 'SAL reports in Morningstar for Advisors (Office & AWS)', '*Business Case:*Office:{quote}As an advisor accessing Morningstar for Advisors iPad app using Office credentials, I want to view the new fund reports (SAL reports) on the quote page for stocks, open-ended funds and ETFs to access relevant research, performance indicators and more for the given fund.{quote}AWS:{quote}As an advisor accessing Morningstar for Advisors iPad app using AWS credentials, I want to view the new fund reports (SAL reports) on the quote page for stocks, open-ended funds and ETFs to access relevant research, performance indicators and more for the given fund.* The new SAL report will be available to both US and CAN (eng/french) users.{quote}*Requirement:** Display SAL reports on the QUOTES page of Morningstar for Advisors (iPad) due to Quick Take retirement. It will be displayed to both Office and AWS users.* Supported securities: Stock, OE and ETF. For rest of the security types we continue to display QT report till there is a SAL version available.* Currently, for AWS, QT reports are routed through AWS. However, when migrated to SAL, the respective reports will be consumed directly from SAL; same as for Office.', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 5, 5, null, null, 'MOBSOLN-12'),
    ('2250', 'SAL reports for managed investments in Morningstar for iPad', '*Business case:* {quote}As an individual investor accessing Morningstar for iPad, I want to view the new Fund Report (SAL reports) on the quote page for Open-ended funds (OE) & Exchange Traded Funds (ETF) to access relevant research, performance indicators and more for the given managed funds.{quote}*Requirement:*Display SAL reports for OE & ETF on the QUOTES page of Morningstar for iPad mobile app due to Quick Take retirement. Once the new version goes LIVE, iPad users will see the new SAL reports ONLY; there will be NO navigation to the QT reports.', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'MOBSOLN-8'),
    ('2251', 'SAL reports for STOCKS in Morningstar for iPad', 'Display SAL Reports on the QUOTES page of Morningstar for iPad mobile app due to Quick Take retirement.*  [^High Level Analysis - SAL Migration for Stocks_Morningstar for iPad (Retail App).docx] *  [^Re_ QuickTake (QT) Retirement 鈥?SAL migration of Morningstar for iPad app.msg] *Impacted screens** 鈥淔ull Report鈥?view of Stocks, OE and ETFs* Start with Stock Quotes page which is implemented in www.morningstar.com. *Go-to-market strategy for STOCK** Introduce SAL reports for STOCKS in Morningstar for iPad (DO NOT retail access to QT pages).* Once the new version goes LIVE, iPad users will see the new SAL reports ONLY; there will be NO navigation to the QT reports. * Provide users with some explainer text about the new SAL report.We will co-ordinate with .com for rest of the security types (OE & ETF) and will follow .com to roll out the new SAL reports respectively.*Important links** https://mswiki.morningstar.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=160457969* https://msstash.morningstar.com/projects/AS/repos/sal-components/browse/components/app/README.md* https://msstash.morningstar.com/projects/AS/repos/sal-components/browse/INTEGRATION.md* https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/PDS/SAL+Integration+Setup+Guide', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'MOBSOLN-6'),
