    ('2257', 'Improve Office Cloud UI sanity test Automation Coverage to 100%', 'scope: make all critical priority test cases automated.[https://morningstar.testrail.net/index.php?/suites/view/373&group_by=cases:section_id&group_id=5847&group_order=asc]聽#1 [IA_Household_ExportClients|https://morningstar.testrail.net/index.php?/cases/view/660224]聽#2 IA_ClientAccountViewList#3聽[IA_GlobalSetting_Billing_Disclosure|https://morningstar.testrail.net/index.php?/cases/view/643778]聽/聽聽[IA_GlobalSetting_Reporting_Disclosure|https://morningstar.testrail.net/index.php?/cases/view/786041]#4聽IA_ConvertToCRM', 492, 5, 5, '#a59e89', null, null, null, null, null, null, 8, 8, null, null, 'OC-4820'),
    ('2258', 'ESG changes 2019', 'Morningstar intends to make a methodology change to our ESG data set at the end of Oct 2019, including the Sustainability Rating, to leverage Sustainalytics鈥?new ESG risk rating.聽These changes include:*Fund Level changes*: * 20 cases where data point names/labels need to change * 7 new data points * 10聽data points that should be deleted/removed from products * 6 existing data points that provide the % of AUM distribution for controversy data that we recommend most products add, if they鈥檙e not already displaying these data points.*Company Level changes*: * 4 data point removals * 2 data point additions * 5 data point renamesImpact for both聽*Direct & Office 3.x.*Entitlement is needed for the 2 new data pointsSustainability Rating 2.0 - October 2019 Release Details:聽[https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/IPPMO/Sustainability+Rating+2.0+-+October+2019+Release][https://morningstaronline.sharepoint.com/:x:/s/ESGProgram/EVaJhmikKHpKmZbfrPaRAxcBqiV0AO8b20slb-h1VQroTA?rtime=xSubAOTz1kg]聽', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 4, 4, null, null, 'DSSV-10067'),
    ('2259', 'Analyst Rating 2.0', 'Morningstar will launch the new 2.0聽 Analyst Ratings on October 31st of 2019.聽Because all ratings are valid for 12 to 14 months after they are issued, new ratings cannot roll out for all analyst-covered funds at once. Instead, as funds come up for review, they will be evaluated using the new methodology.聽Three major changes are as below:*1.*聽*Ratings at the Share Class Level* Analyst ratings have historically been applied to the fund. With 2.0, we will be switching to a share-class level rating which will allow share classes within a fund to have different analyst ratings.*2. Performance and Price Pillar Ratings* Pillar ratings for performance and price will be removed, but they will continue to have text. Please note, pillar ratings for Performance and Price will not be removed for funds that are still rated under the current methodology. Because fund ratings are valid for 12 to 14 months, both rating methodologies will co-exist after the initial launch. Those funds rated under the new (2.0) methodology will not populate pillar ratings for Performance and Price, those funds rated under the current (1.0) methodology will continue to display Performance and Price pillar ratings until they are reviewed and rated under the new methodology.*3. Pillar Rating Scale*The 5 point numeric scale that we send to products will not change. The mappings will change, however. Pillar descriptions marked with an * are subject to change.E.g.: 聽|Current State|聽|Future State|聽||Scale|Pillar Rating聽1.0|Scale|Pillar Rating 2.0||3|Positive|5|High||3|Positive|4|Above Average||2|Neutral|3|Average||1|Negative|2|Below Average||1|Negative|1|Low|*4. Analyst Name will change from single value to multiple***|FH00A|Analyst Name|聽', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 4, 4, null, null, 'DSSV-9641'),
