    ('2263', 'Canada Accessibility Design', 'This epic will capture work related to meeting the strict accessibility requirements imposed in Canada.聽*Strategy for User Research & Usability Testing:*With respect to validating the usability of Goal Bridge on the whole in the Canadian market, the commercial product management team has done some preliminary work in speaking to potential Canadian users. Attached is some feedback that was received. Additionally, there are plans for them to share the prototype with prospective users and put together a business case for going to the Canadian market. Any usability testing or further requirements specific to accessibility are to be determined by some of the tickets contained within this epic.*Information on this Epic''s Relation to Business Strategy:*As mentioned in the Advisor Workstation epic, GB-367, the users of Advisor Workstation are a good target market for Goal Bridge. Goal Bridge is intended to be an international tool and there are revenue targets that we can assist in hitting by expanding internationally. Canada is a nice test case for this because WFE already has a Canadian engine that is up to date. The proactivity of the commercial product management team has also validated up front that there is some interest in a tool like Goal Bridge.*Intended Outcome and Measurement:*The ultimate measure of success is if we are able to deploy to the Canadian market in 2020. Our initial target is by end of Q1 2020 (largely pending work placed higher in priority such as the US integration and how much we need to do in the realm of accessibility support, which will be uncovered by this epic). This specific epic will be successful if we are able to complete it in a manner that is timely enough to continue to be on pace for a Q1 2020 release. That would mean this epic should be complete by the end of 2019 (earlier is better due to an upcoming sabbatical).聽*Dependencies:* # Availability of in-house accessibility experts', -1, 2, 5