    ('2268', 'Delivery Method - Download with EMAIL notification', 'Data Services only support Morningstar File Server delivery currently. We would like to explore the possibility to delivery a scheduled feed to the user with email notification and download capability.聽User should be able to schedule the feed as normal and select Download as delivery mechanism. Once the feed is ready, email will be sent out to provided email(s) with download link for the purpose. Similar to what we have as Export functional. The download link should be expired after predetermined hours. User can setup up to 5 email accounts for delivery.聽Since email address is one of the security sensitive data, product shouldn''t save the actual email address in our database.聽We will be leveraging the AWS parameter store service for encrypting, decrypting and storing client email addresses.聽Components: * Design UX * Frontend UI * Backend API Service * DFD * SNS * Feed Messenger聽聽聽聽', -1, 5, 5, '#9faebf', null, null, null, 'Data Products - August-September 2019', '2019-08-23T00:00:00', '2019-10-03T00:00:00', 9, 9, '33', 'Support Velo Development', 'VELO-729'),
    ('2269', 'Data Set - Data Template Phase 1', 'Data Template is one of the Data Set Types selection in Data Point List. Data Template is a selection of a group of data pre-cooked as a group/template. Phase 1 for Data Template is focus on fundamental setup with certain level of limitation based on V2 capability from the data template services.聽*User can and cannot do:* * Create a data feed with one template only and available universe list * NO selection of the data points within the template. * Data column name is standard. No change.聽 * Data column order is standard. No change. * Be able to get either Current Data or Time Series of the Data Template. Time Series is based on availability of the data points. * Currency Conversion feature is based on availability of the Data Template and data point.聽Move to Phase 2 * -Be able to view the data points included in the template- * -Be able to view the description of the data template. However, description is an option display.-聽{color:#de350b}_*New endpoint from V2 to return data in Avro file for data template*_{color}*Workflow: Build Data Point List*Step 1: Enter the Data Point List NameStep 2: Select *"Data Template"* from the Data Set Type dropdown menuStep 3: Select one data template from the user entitled data template(s) from the list.Step 4: Select Criteria belong to the selected Data Template. Criteria is optional.聽 * Data Type (Current or Time Series) * Currency Conversion * Portfolio Breakdown Levels * Any possible criteria聽Step 5: Summary/Save*Workflow: Manage Data Point List*Step 1: Select the Data Point List to EditStep 2: Step 3 from Build Data Point ListStep 3: Step 4 from Build Data Point ListStep 4: Step 5 from Build Data Point List聽聽', -1, 5, 5, '#6ec762', null, null, null, 'Data Products - August-September 2019', '2019-08-23T00:00:00', '2019-10-03T00:00:00', 12, 12, '33', 'Support Velo Development', 'VELO-678'),
    ('2270', 'EAMS Data Roles', 'EAMS is currently working on supporting data roles which are like existing roles but are self-service and not curated internally.聽聽A role can only be one type, so the new data role are all empty in User API now.聽聽Per the info of EAMS, they already add a new聽node "dataRoles" into user json (${api-path}/v1/user) and a new claim "custom:data_role" into JWT. They are of type string array which is the same as "roles" and "custom:role".They also added a new separate endpoint "${api-path}/v1/user/dataroles" to retrieve user data roles only.Please find EAMS environments from the wiki page:[https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/M4/1.+How+to+use+EAMS]', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'VELO-670'),
    ('2271', 'Alert Feature', 'Alert Feature is to provide information that can be triggered by QA/Operation/Production process. The information of this feature can be provided for internal and/or external purpose. We need to have a database to house all the alerts for each feed and has a capability to provide the information for client in Basic Dashboard and Velo Admin site. Alert info should be overwritten by new alert information or NULL if there is nothing trigger.聽All of the alerts should be available to view from Velo Admin site but not only subset of the alerts should be display in Basic Dashboard in Data Services UI. There should be an indicator in the database to differentiate if the alert is available for Client Basic Dashboard.聽[https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/DWH/Alerts]聽', -1, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 4, 2, null, null, 'VELO-611'),
