    ('2274', 'Morningstar Fixed Income Index', 'Morningstar Index team would like to leverage Data Services platform to provide feed service for Morningstar Fixed Income Index for their clients. Morningstar Fixed Income Index are only using data from third party data vendor ICE. All the ICE data are available in Data API V2 with special entitlement and data definition. Based on this special entitlement requirement, Data Services might need to make slight modification to accommodate the situation.聽Data Services:聽 * -Data Point List - Data Template is introduced as part of the Data Point List. Data Template is a template with a group of defined data points. User must consume all the data points included in the template. User can select Current Data/Most Recent or Time Series for the data template if it is available.聽Entitlement is based on Data Template, not Data Bundle. Data Template entitlement in V2 and Authorization in EAMS. Same as Data Bundle.-聽 * -Universe List - *Morningstar Fixed Income Index Series*聽will be added. The entitlement is directly applied in Data API V2, not in EAMS. There will be a special API service to return entitled Index Series/Portfolio for the user that will be using in Universe List.-聽 * Data Feed - Due to entitlement model is different between Index Series and Investment Securities, we will introduce a concept of building data feed for Investment Securities and Morningstar Fixed-Income Index Series. New page will be added for the selection. If the user selected Investment Securities, it will follow the existing flow to select Universe List and Data Point List. If the user selected Morningstar Fixed-Income Index Series, new process flow will be introduced. It will start with select Data Template/Criteria then select Universe before Save Data Feed.聽 * Schedule - File Format availability will be based on Data Template * DFD - DFD for Data Template should be slightly different than DFD for Current Data because there is no individual data poi