    ('2302', 'Consolidate/streamline index entitlement framework', 'Currently we have two index entitlement frameworks: * The one used for Direct ** Multiple tables for each data set (IndexPerformanceAcl,聽IndexPortStatsAcl,聽IndexPortHoldingsAcl) ** No flexibility to add additional data sets, or update data points in each set ** No APIs to support access updates * The one used for Velo ** Simpler table structure ** Flexibility to add additional data sets or update data points in each set ** APIs to update access ** Not hooked up to traditional /securities SQL genThis epic is to consolidate the existing Direct index entitlement setup into the updated Velo framework.聽At a high level, I think this will involve: # Tech design task (June Sprint 2) # Redesign index tables (July Sprint 1) ## Remove tables:聽AmsIndexUuid,聽IndexAclAmsUuid ## Update table:聽IndexMFIAcl ### Rename to: ResourceObjectAcl ### Update columns to be: #### Resource Id (user GUID or product ID) #### Resource type (Product or User) #### Object Id (will reference new object table) #### Access Level (full, years history, no access, etc.) ## Create new table: EntitlementObject, colums will be: ### Object Id ### Object Definition #### We need to figure out what the structure of that will be #### At least it will include SeriesId+Data Point Group for index entitlement #### Also needs to handle the MQR case of universe criteria and data point # Update GET/POST /index-data APIs to use new tables (July Sprint 2) # Update /securities/data-template index entitlement to use new tables (July Sprint 2) # Update index entitlement ams > metadb ETL job to write to the new tables (August Sprint 1) ## Start updating both old and new tables # One-time data migration from existing Direct tables to Velo table structure (August Sprint 1) # Update to SQL gen to use the updated Velo table structure to enforce index entitlement (August Sprint 2) # Update to /holdings API to use updated Velo table structure to enforce index entitlement (August Sprint 2) # Turn off old tables in ETL (September Sprint 1)聽', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'DE-456'),
    ('2303', 'Income & Cash Flow Reports for Office Cloud', 'Between pdf reports and Presentation Studio, Office Cloud users can run or created most of the same reports they are accustom to running in Office Desktop.聽 One exception is聽 advisors ability to run reports that help them anaylsis cash flow/income related聽 information for their clients.聽 The most Presentation Studio can do is filter the Transaction component on transaction types, but advisors need more details than that when helping clients review their cash needs.Advisors typically want subtotals for different transaction types and/or security types when reviewing information like this.聽 Because of this gap, we would like to add the "Income Report" and "Portfolio Cash Flow" report to the pre-canned report options within Office Cloud. This will not only help migrate current users, but provide a more well rounded reporting option for new Office Cloud users.聽*Income Report:* This report lists the interests and dividends received for the account during the reporting period. * Income generation information is particular important for advisors who have聽 retired clients.聽 Retried clients depend on their accounts to replace the income they used to get working so like to carefully track that info (just like someone who is working would want to view their ''paycheck'')*Portfolio Cash Flow Report:*聽 This report displays all', 497, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-1312'),
