    ('2314', 'Model Portfolio Attribution', 'Risk Attribution&Decomposition API to accept model portfolio posted in Json format using secId as holding identifier.EC wants to be in a position to do a few things with this capability. Our primary users are Advisors or Individuals, however Asset Manager or Advisory Platforms (B/D or Wirehouses) are the buyers of the service.We can imagine an Asset Manager using this API on their website to demonstrate how their funds or models, standalone or in a portfolio, would perform in a up or down markets. Their target is an advisor or individual using their site to determine if the funds of that firm would be a good addition to their portfolio and needs to see both the fund and the fund in a portfolio to make the decision. This is just like our current Portfolio Xray/Hypo workflow.Additionally, on an Advisory platform this would be part of the proposal process to demonstrate the value of moving from a current to a proposed portfolio. Again, this for the same workflow as above. If we use the API, we assume the client will build their front end. However, we need the components too.聽', 564, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 16, 16, null, null, 'APG-4011'),
    ('2315', 'NA model', 'Release new *North America Regional Model*. It aims to accommodate North America region specific market conditions and build a multi factor risk model using the underlying Morningstar Global Risk Model methodology. This will help North America region asset managers to analyze their portfolios of local securities with more accuracy and help to forecast risk that is attributed to the local market factors. In Morningstar Database, we''ve seen the funds鈥?AUM of US and Canadian Equity Category sums up to over 16 Trillion dollars. This is a significant number of assets that our new Model will be provide better service for.', 585, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 2, 2, null, null, 'APG-4012'),
    ('2316', 'Corp Fin SIPC Report', 'h1. Business use caseMorningstar''s Corporate Finance team is required to file paperwork bi-annually during February and July/August for SIPC payment calculation. As inputs to this calculation, MIS needs to provide an Excel report with percentage breakdowns of the following types of investments per model:# Stock# ETF# Fundh1. Current stateThis request is fielded by Operations and passed to Zhigang, who is the only one that knows how to provide this report. h1. Future stateWe want to move towards a self-service model so that members of Corporate Finance can access the data inputs on-demand.', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'MPTHUNDER-186'),
    ('2317', 'Transition Email Distribution to AD Groups', 'For MIS express reports that we want to keep, we want to streamline how the reports are sent out to various stakeholders. That means sending emails to distribution lists rather than specific individuals and adopting a more flexible way to change recipients other than hardcoding in XML. _*Documentation*_* Link to documentation: https://morningstaronline-my.sharepoint.com/personal/frank_nezrick_morningstar_com/_layouts/15/guestaccess.aspx?guestaccesstoken=OI+p7jUFK2x8dib22EuZ6GOGRo542ewFs1XTo1iOgKw=&docid=2_1a37e007afc7f467a81e07c818d75cff9&rev=1* To get to the relevant info on the spreadsheet, go to the 2nd tab', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'MPTHUNDER-157'),
    ('2318', 'Compare Account Holdings', 'The problem we鈥檙e trying to solve is to ensure model performance is correct for month-end production. After discussion with Ruben and Ola, the root cause is determined to be the untimely reallocation updates to model holdings in our Models database. This causes the performance calculation to use incorrect holdings, resulting in incorrect model performance. (It is likely that other inputs can cause incorrect model performance but we will tackle the holdings issue first.)The approach is to compare our model holdings (in the Models database, modelHoldings table) to the source of truth. If a mismatch is found, then then notify appropriate parties to resolve the mismatch. What is the source of truth?Based on my understanding of our reallocation events, our Performance and Risk Management team (Paul/Sam) also use the reallocation data to update our models in Direct. They are tracking 93 models (base models + custodian variations) from inception in Direct鈥檚 Portfolio Management > Accounts database. All historical model reallocations are imported. These models are permission-based and can be shared with other Direct logins. Here鈥檚 a screenshot:!MPTHUNDER-92_Models_in_Direct.png!Each model鈥檚 holding detail can be accessed via right-click View Holdings > Detailed Holding Analysis. The Detailed Holding Analysis window will allow you to export model holdings and other holdings data to Excel or CSV. !MPTHUNDER-92_Detailed_Holding_Analysis.png!In my mind, here are the initial steps needed for setup:# Gain access (Read-Only should suffice) to these models in Direct 鈥?contact *Paul Gozali and Sam Yan*, copy me.# Learn how to navigate to these models and get holdings data; the above screen-shots are good starting points# Map the models from Direct to the model codes in our database. Sam and Paul have created Portfolio IDs for each model in Direct. Map these to modelHoldings.MISsymbol (model codes)', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'MPTHUNDER-92'),
    ('2319', 'Demo Change Tool migrate to OPs tool', 'The dealer change tool is currently working on the production environment however the same tool is not being able to function on the lower environment. The dealer change tool is currently not working on the STG envoriment. The tool is able to update the dealer on the QA and UAT environment. Also the request for providing access to the STG environments was rejected and hence the tool will not be able to work on all the lower environements.The requirement was to move the Dealer change tool to OPs tool so that the same can be used for updating the dealer number on the lower environments.聽', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'MPTHUNDER-724'),
