    ('2321', 'Consolidate the Account Related Events AUM Rollup Reports', '*Business Purpose*The AUM Summary information is utilized by the Regional Sales Directors (and some related team members) to obtain a snapshot of their regions AUM deltas on a daily basis.  The summary data provides a quick visual reference to each RSD on how their region is performing  at various intervals as well as seeing a pipeline asset.The main usage of the daily ARE report is understanding the log of events that have transpired during that business day.  This type of data will be addressed in a separate Epic User story.*Audience*# Peter Dugery / SVP of Sales and Distribution# RSDs# Sales Associates# Sales Consultants / Internal Sales Consultants# Internal Wholesalers#', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'MPTHUNDER-76'),
    ('2322', 'Provide a self-service Email List search and extraction online tool', '*Business Purpose*As a Marketing Team Member I need the ability to pull standard and ad hoc lists of advisors and emails to send required communications.  Currently there are ~16 - 22 reports that extract advisor (and advisor assistants) contact information that are then imported into our Elapse communication tool.  Ad hoc requests are created on demand by Zhigang as would be the case of following up with advisors that may have assets under management in a given model.  Key pieces of information are:# firstName (of advisor)# lastName# Company (full company name)# email address# phone number# state# RSD# RSD email# RSD phone number# Advisor ID# address1# address2# city# state# zip*Audience*# Sarah McClain, Marketing Manager# Alec Buchholtz, Marketing Associate# Regional Sales Directors', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'MPTHUNDER-67'),
    ('2323', 'Consolidate Investment Strategy Metrics and Portfolio Cashflow into a single report', 'Business Purpose:Different groups are actively monitoring sales and redemption activities as markers for potential trends that drive follow up activities or preparation for meetings driving interactions with partners.  A few of the key audiences at Morningstar are:* Investment Management Team (including MS Sr. Leadership)* Trade Desk* MIS Operations* Regional Sales Directors* etc.The two reports of consolidation opportunity are:# Investment Strategy Metrics (uses rp_reportPortfolioCashflow_new)# Portfolio Cashflow (uses rp_reportPortfolioCashflow)At a high-level, both of the reports cover the same data columns.  The coupled stored procedure and template used for Investment Strategy Metrics does not specifically identify any custodians; whereas the Portfolio Cashflow report  uses a template that names approximately 14 custodians.The opportunity exists to consolidate this report into a single report albeit with either updated filtering capabilities in a updated template.  Moreover, the opportunity exists to move this type of data into an online, self service model.  In cases where the Investment Team is looking for specialized queries (i.e. All custodians that possess a specific model or where specific securities are held by a given custodian), Zhigang is approached and creates these custom queries resulting in separate emailed attachments.', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'MPTHUNDER-64'),
    ('2324', 'Convert Confirmation Events into an Event Driven / API Interface', 'The Warehouse database is currently used to house a number of event types driven by account management activities by advisors / brokerDealers.  These activities are then "read" by a query through the MISExpress system that generate a number of email messages.  In the case of the Account Closing Feedback message, the email is sent to the advisor at a dealerBroker or Custodian involved in closing the account.There are six templates currently used to facilitate the construction of the email bound for the advisors:# ClosedAccount.xml# NewAccEmail.xml# StrategyChange.xml# TranPurchConfirmations.xml# TranRedConfirmations.xml and# Thank You_Email.xmlRather than having the construction of the reports/emails by the MISExpress, look to move the implementation to an API driven function.  It is possible other types of events need to be defined/recorded that could be handled by an API approach for these "reports."  In an ideal implementation the following would be true:* MS loader processes would be responsible for the mass and delta data uploads to commit account information into Morningstar''s databases (perhaps persisting in the current Warehouse)* An API/Web Service would be exposed allowing dealerBrokers and other appropriate partners to securely call when an event is encountered* In the case of a "new account opening," the API/Web Service could be used to record data in an appropriate database* In the case of redemptions, model changes, or purchases* In all cases, the API would facilitate pulling the right data and sending confirmation emails/communications.', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'MPTHUNDER-62'),
    ('2325', 'Consolidate Accounts Changed Reports', 'Currently three reports are maintained separately that capture different types of "changes".# Advisors Changed Dealer# Account Changed Advisor# Accounts Changed Model The data presented in these reports is used by MISOps to prepare for support fee calculations, statement production and other quarter end activities.The purpose of this Epic is to guide the consolidation of this data into a single report...with the ideal goal to move towards an online, self-service, and queryable tool.', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'MPTHUNDER-56'),
    ('2326', 'Consolidate 13F Total AUM for ETF StocketBasket Report', '*Business Purpose*The compliance team uses the 13F reports to support quarterly findings.  The file provides aggregate data that will be used to support filings to the SEC and FINRA.  Closely related, the MIS Core team would benefit be removing another report from being maintained.*Audience*# Compliance Team# Core / Legacy MIS Team# Zhigang Liang', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'MPTHUNDER-35'),
    ('2327', 'Deliver Account Related Events Log Level Detail', '*Business Purpose*As a Sales Team Member, I need to see a list of activities that have occurred in my Region that drive my daily sales/follow up actions.  Key pieces of information I require are:# TOA Summary Data such as TOA Counts# Alert Level Summary for activities within the region# Detailed breakout of specific events by the following categories:# Opened Accounts Pending# New Accounts Opened# Initial Account Funding# Additional Account Funding# New Proposals Created# Created first proposal# First Login# Withdrawal from Accounts# Withdrawal to close Account# New Applications Created*Audience*# SVP National Sales and Distribution# Regional Sales Director# Sales Associates# Sales Consultant / Internal Sales Consultant# Internal Wholesaler', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'MPTHUNDER-69'),
