    ('2396', 'Argus - Optimization', 'This Epic will track tasks connected with optimization function development, one of the most important new feature for APC 2.0.聽 Also in scope: a. Sweep Logic b. Portfolio stats c. Storing Portfolio d. Orchestration (Step Functions)Business Background -聽APC 1.0 process utilizes many qualitatively derived constraints that have accumulated over the years and periodically conflict with each other, thus necessitating consultant intervention. The new portfolio construction process will include an algorithm that dynamically loosens constraints on three different paths (loosening manager and misfit constraints by equal amounts and then two others where one is loosed more than the other) until a feasible region is found and then builds the alpha/tracking error frontier and selects the portfolio of each sweep with the highest Israelson Information Ratio.聽 A single portfolio is selected from the three portfolios by comparing a ratio of Information Ratio/Herfindahl.Morningstar has taken the qualitative definition of what a 鈥渟uitable portfolio鈥?is and used quantitative metrics to measure these characteristics.聽 The process is to find the portfolio that maximizes the unit of alpha per unit of tracking error subjected to the manager and asset class constraints based on trading off between manager specific risk and asset class misfit risk within a total tracking error budget while building within a constraint on the allowed nominal deviation from the equity target of the model, and diversified manager risk by measuring the concentration of holdings', -1, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 32, 21, null, null, 'MIMAPC-1335'),
