    ('2402', 'GECS change 10/31/2019', 'Morningstar鈥檚 Global Equity Classification structure is comprised of three super sectors based on economic sensitivity; Cyclical, Defensive, and Sensitive. Within these three super sectors there are 11 sectors, and within those numerous industry groups and individual industries.The current methodology was created nearly 8 years ago. Economic and technology changes since that time dictate that we revise our methodology to align more closely with industry standards and current economic realities. Equity Data team in consultation with Equity Research team, has reviewed our current classification schema and has come up with several changes in the classification structure.There are no changes on the Super Sector and Sector level. All the proposed changes are limited to Industry Group and Industries only.At the Industry group level, we are discontinuing聽*20*聽groups and introducing聽*6*聽new groups, resulting in an overall reduction from 69 to聽*55*.At the Industry level, we are discontinuing聽*29*聽current industries and will introduce聽*26*聽new industries, resulting in an overall reduction from 148 to聽*145*聽industries. Some industries are also moving out from one Sector to another sector.', -1, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 8, 8, null, null, 'DSSV-10123'),
