    ('2422', 'Argus - Fund Statistics', 'This Epic will track tasks connected with fund stats calculation function, having the matlab code translated that make each piece can be operated separately聽and combined.聽Also in scope:a. Translating each calc will be a story (from Matlab to Python) b. RBSA c. Peer Grouping d. calculating statistics b. Storing Statistics  c. Orchestration (Step Functions)Business Background:_The statistics used in the optimization are not from a consistent model._The alpha/tracking error framework uses an optimization that is based on the least squares regression approach.聽 It is generally accepted that when utilizing an optimization routine, the alphas and betas should be derived from the same model.However, in the APC 1.0 system, the alphas and tracking errors can be disjointed from the betas, which can be sourced using different lengths of time for RBSA, inconsistent HBSA rules, or an analyst.聽 Furthermore, the APC 1.0 portfolio construction process has several areas where different regression sets are use and a lot of points of analyst intervention鈥攆rom peer grouping overrides, to statistic overrides including R-squared overrides.聽 Because of that the optimization inputs are disjointed, hard to rationalize, and/or may be unjustifiable to clients.聽In the new era all stats are derived from the same model, the RBSA is to be聽ran on a monthly basis and the outputs will be warehoused to be used聽in following peer grouping, fund stats, main/select list, and optimization process._Returns Based Style Analysis (RBSA)_Argus will use Returns Based Style Analysis (RBSA) for all funds except stable value investments (funds and contracts). This calculation requires a common period of returns series for fund and the benchmarks.This solver聽in the current system/Advice Engine Web Service (AEWS) must be updated to include the option to incorporate a half-life. The alpha/tracking error framework requires three estimates all derived by using Returns Based Style Analysis (RBSA):1,Style Weights,聽2.聽Alpha, 3.Tracking Error.聽The proprietary APC fund selection process also considers a number of other calculations that includes: 1.R-Squares, 2.Peer Group, 3.聽Israelsen Information Ratio, 4.聽Style Drift ScorePeer Grouping (Each eligible Morningstar Category will be mapped to an APC peer groups, Custom funds are to be grouped with rules based of RBSA results)_Forward looking alpha(FLA),_ _Israelsen Information Ratio(__IR) and_聽_Style Drift Score (Replacing Consistency Score)_聽_Calculation_The FAL calculation is a proprietary calculation created by Ibbotson. The function currently exists but uses 36 months and 12 months; the months should be a configuration that can easily be changed.聽APC currently uses Israelsen method to calculate IR and should continue.The _Style Drift Score_ is a way to gauge the variances of the fund鈥檚 style analysis over a rolling analysis period;聽The score will be calculated using a selected subset of the 19 benchmarks and/or a set of composite benchmarks for each pe', -1, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 91, 58, null, null, 'MIMAPC-1336'),
