    ('2516', 'Design for Management Fee Customization', '{color:#ff0000}Design Due Date: September 30, 2019{color}_{color:#ff0000}*A.*{color} As an advisor who used Office to run my billing, I want to create separate fees for different securities types so that I can bill in a way that reflects the effort it takes to manage each different security type._*Background:*聽Typical client accounts are comprised of multiple different scrutiny types.聽 This is so the account is balanced in such a way to achieve the client''s investment goals. Different security types require different levels of work & review by the advisor.聽 聽Stocks may need a higher amount of monitoring compared to a CD聽 or to a bond that won''t come due in years.聽 Some advisors want a way to create bills that reflect the different work loads associated with different security types.聽*How it works in 3.x*: * user creates manage fee --&gt; Tiered (% of Account Value in OC) --&gt; Billing by Security Type.聽  !image-2019-08-23-13-27-27-477.png|width=633,height=162! * Which replaces the standard tier with this:聽  !image-2019-08-23-13-28-15-105.png|width=507,height=172! * User then creates different tier breakouts for one or more security types at a time:聽  !image-2019-08-23-13-36-30-908.png|width=458,height=445! * User can then view the breakouts they have created & CRUD them as needed:  !image-2019-08-23-14-47-42-119.png!*{color:#ff0000}B.{color}*聽As an advisor who used Office Cloud to bill my clients, I want the ability to created billing time periods that match my businesses finical calendar so that I can line up charging my clients with other firm financial activities.聽Additional info from the help section of 3.x:聽  !image-2019-08-26-14-10-35-966.png!*{color:#ff0000}C.{color}*聽As an advisor billing in Office Cloud, I want to ability to break a fee tier out by advisor & firm %s so that I can designate how much of the fee goes to my firm and how much gets paid out directly to me. The advisor.For example, The client may pay an annual fee of 1%, however of that 1% , 0.75% is the advisor portion and 0.25% is the firm鈥檚 portion.Advisor Fee + Firm Fee = Annual Rate%聽 !image-2019-08-26-16-10-15-650.png!聽聽*In Scope:* * content updates * rearranging the options/settings with in a fee as needed*Out of Scope:*聽 * complete overhaul of how fees are CRUD*Unknowns:* * Is there a use case for any security types to be fully left out of tier list? * what happens when a security type is left out? * will custom security types created by 3x users show up in security type list like in 3x', 35, 5, 2, null, '2019-08-22T00:00:00', '2019-10-02T00:00:00', null, 'Cloud - Aug-Sept 2019', '2019-08-22T00:00:00', '2019-10-02T00:00:00', 13, 12, '62', 'Office Cloud -  Billing Parity', 'OC-4925'),
