    ('2588', 'Argus - Data Loading', 'This Epic will track tasks connected with fund loading process including fetching, parsing, and storing.聽 The tasks including:a. Load (reach S3 Bucket)聽 聽 聽 聽 i. Client 聽 聽 聽 聽 聽 聽 聽a. plan 聽 聽 聽 聽 聽 聽 聽b. asset聽 聽 聽 聽 ii. Public (Data API v 2) b. Storing 聽 聽 聽 聽 i. parse 聽 聽 聽 聽 ii. put into DBBusiness Background for 2.0_Required Data points_For Argus, the data structure of funds does not need to change, however, the data sufficiency for use in a portfolio will change.聽Regardless of the source of the underlying data and fund type, all funds are required to have 48-month net returns as well as prospectus expense ratio to be considered for use.聽 For public index funds with less than 48 months, past performance will be calculated using the fund鈥檚 primary benchmark.聽 *A decision on whether clients will be able use the same process for custom funds marked as index needs to be decided.* To be mentioned,聽**聽for stable value funds, there''re a couple of data points that we won''t be using anymore but fund returns are newly聽required,聽the length of month returns is to be decided._Fund Types_APC supports a multitude of fund types, which can come from either the client or the Data api. 1. Pubic, 2.Public GIC, 3.Custom, 4.GIC, 5.Wrap, 6.Share, 7.Target Date.聽 Among them,聽Public and Public GIC are available to聽all clients聽by mapping identifiers to the fund. The client custom fund data聽are sent from the client. The Asset.XML file loading process should not change for clients from a mechanical aspect.The APC database only needs to load the fund information once from聽Data Api but allow clients to reference that data.聽 It is important to create a client-level universe as most clients have special identifiers for all funds.聽Custom funds and SVF are loaded via the Asset XML files and all the data is given by the client.聽 These funds are exclusively available to the client.聽聽Wrap funds are client specific funds that overlay an extra annualized fee amount over an existing fund (public or client fund).聽 The wrap fund must reference an existing fund in the client鈥檚 universe and will mirror the parent index fund flag, strategy fund flag, and peer group information but will calculate separate statistics.聽Target Date funds and聽Share funds are sent in by clients solely for use in the Master Style Table (MST).聽', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 54, 29, null, null, 'MIMAPC-1337'),
