    ('2638', 'IP API align with Morningstar API standards', 'We had review meeting with API guild on August 30th, and got some feedback. # camelCase must be applied across the board. We see title case and underscores, so they need to be addressed for all end-points. {color:#ff0000}[  # We need to update EMR script to mapping new camelCase name for table fields # Make sure all resources are camelCase, including swagger resource, path placefolder, input, output. ]{color} 2. Expand names so that they鈥檙e wholly readable, plus fix typos (鈥淣etAsset鈥?should be 鈥淣etAssets鈥? {color:#ff0000}[  # 鈥淣etAsset鈥?in exposure node can be removed. # In other nodes, update 鈥淣etAsset鈥?to be "NetAssets". ]{color} 3. The field 鈥淐umulative12MonthFlows:FundAge鈥?looks incorrect (鈥淐umulative12MonthFlows鈥?and 鈥淔undAge鈥?are separate flow factors, so it seems strange they鈥檙e combined in the end-point output). {color:#ff0000}[ # This can be done in item 1, just need [~pli1] to provide new mapping name. ]{color} {color:#4c9aff}Peanut: change to cumulative12MonthFlowsFundAgeInteraction{color} 4. 鈥淓QUTY鈥?looks a lot like a typo! It would be much better to see it spelled out. {color:#ff0000}[ # Update model config file to change the flow model id naming to be more readable. e.g. "usa-equity-shareclass-fundflow", "usa-allocation-shareclass-fundflow", "usa-fixedincome-shareclass-fundflow". ]{color} 5. Expand abbreviations 鈥?try to maximise clarity, especially from the perspective of a user that鈥檚 new to our services. {color:#ff0000}[ # Covered by other items ]{color} 6. Mandatory parameters should always appear in the path, not as query string params. {color:#ff0000}[ # Still using Get method # Put the mandatory parameters in the URL Path # Add limit of 50 ids to multiple values # e.g. /models/\{flow-model-id}/\{share-class-ids}/exposures ]{color} 7. Some fields are incorrectly nested. For example, NetAssets shouldn鈥檛 be in exposures as it鈥檚 a property of the share class, not a factor. 鈥淭imeIndex鈥?probably appears in the same category. {color:#ff0000}[ # Make sure correct nodes appear in correct parent node/category. e.g. date should be out of exposure node in endpoint /flow-attribution/calculate-ex-anti # Remove useless nodes, e.g. TimeIndex, lost_money, attract_money in exposure node in endpoint /models/\{flow-model-id}/\{share-class-ids}/exposures ]{color} 8. 鈥渋tems鈥?needs to be more descriptive. Again, it鈥檚 good to think about readability through the eyes of someone completely unfamiliar with our services. {color:#ff0000}[  # [~pli1] to provide a more readable name for "items" and any other parts.{color} {color:#4c9aff}Peanut: Let''s make it consistent as risk model. {color} {color:#4c9aff} change items to riskExposures, change the subnode "exposures" to "factors"{color}{color:#ff0000} ]{color} 9. The /exposures/ endpoint needs a re-think. Ican and Peanut agreed to work with Philip Z to confirm the use-case and to restructure the endpoints accordingly. {color:#ff0000}[ # /exposures/ endpoint can be removed. # [~pli1] to confirm whether the', 519, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 11, 11, null, null, 'APG-4084'),
