    ('2655', 'POC for migrate DWM import to leverage PAS API which connect to 3x storage', '[https://morningstaronline.sharepoint.com/:w:/r/sites/CloudDataStrategyPlans/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc=%7B9e8cbeb3-8b6a-4ae3-8930-922b6eebe0f4%7D&action=default&wdLOR=c86653274%2D805E%2D40E9%2D9015%2D71FA3371751B&cid=e7b5015f-6fba-4d04-9a52-229d8f2755fd]聽Summary聽聽Validate mapping process聽1) to use聽SecId聽as Morningstar security Id聽instead of GUID, 2) to use RDB as mapping source.聽聽聽Ensure聽the efficiency of ID service can support both 3X and Cloud users.聽.聽High-Level Explanation of Solution聽 * Currently 3X uses聽SecId聽as Morningstar security primary ID, while DWM uses Performance Id. We will change聽DWM import聽to use Sec Id, including security, holding and custom data points.聽 * We will change to use RDB as Morningstar security mapping source, verify the performance of RDB is fast enough.聽 * We will have performance test to validate ID service聽concurrency based on聽about 30,000 users.聽聽POC Task聽 * Pull account & security mapping data from Pas DB as test mocking data.聽 * Change Morningstar security mapping source to RDB聽 * Use Sec Id for Morningstar security ID in the following object: security, holding and custom data point.聽 * ID service performance test, focus on high concurrency.聽Out of scope聽 * 聽聽 Security / Account sync between PAS DB to ID service.聽聽 * 聽聽 Post account/security/custom data point to PAS API instead of sqlMart.聽聽Dependencies聽 * We need large number of test login for ID service performance test.聽Risks & issues聽聽Assumptions聽 * DWM and 3.x use same client security structure, that is,聽聽 * For security mapped to Morningstar Security, use聽Secid聽 * For user defined security, linked to Morningstar Security, use聽GUID聽 * For user defined security, NO Morningstar Security mapping, use GUID聽聽聽聽Measures of Success聽 * Use SecId as primary ID in security/holding/custom datapoint without impacting performance.聽 * Change to RDB as mapping source, verify the performance of RDB API.聽 * ID service performance聽based on:聽 * Average聽time cost聽of importing 10,000 accounts聽cover聽2,000,000聽securities and聽100,000 holdings聽 * Average聽time cost聽of importing聽10000 accounts cover 2,000聽securities with聽20,000 holdings聽 * Average聽time cost聽of importing 300 000 accounts聽cover聽2,000,000聽securities with聽20,000,000 holdings聽Resource & Estimation:聽 * Leaders: David Chen / Smart Li聽 * Working Team: Emma聽聽 * Estimation:聽 3 weeks聽聽Impact聽 * Quick account import for Office Cloud for 2-3聽weeks.聽', 637, 5, 5, '#ff9867', null, null, null, 'Cloud - Oct - Nov 2019', '2019-10-03T00:00:00', '2019-11-13T00:00:00', 23, 23, null, null, 'PBCIMPORT-5939'),
    ('2658', 'Argus Portfolio Stability Control', 'This Epic will track tasks connected with Portfolio Stability Control development, one of the most important new feature for APC 2.0. 1 MotivationWe re-optimize fund allocations on a quarterly basis. In virtually all cases, the updated portfolio (Pu) created at t0 will be different than the current portfolio (Pc) created at t..1. This is typically due to changes in fund parameter estimates though it could also be due to a change in asset class targets. In many cases, however, it is likely that the updated portfolio won''t be materially better than the current portfolio thus rendering trading unnecessary. While trading in a qualified setting is almost always cost less, it creates some degree of confusion for clients and participants. It can also place some burden on those record keepers who need to submit trades by selling the current portfolio to cash before implementing the new recommendations. As such we''ve used various forms of turnover control to minimize transactions we believe to be unnecessary. With the roll-out of APC 2.0, we''re aiming to simplify the current process.', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'MIMAPC-1583'),
