    ('2769', 'Canada Accessibility - Development', 'This epic will capture work related to meeting the strict accessibility requirements imposed in Canada.聽*Strategy for User Research & Usability Testing:*With respect to validating the usability of Goal Bridge on the whole in the Canadian market, the commercial product management team has done some preliminary work in speaking to potential Canadian users. Attached is some feedback that was received. Additionally, there are plans for them to share the prototype with prospective users and put together a business case for going to the Canadian market. Any usability testing or further requirements specific to accessibility are to be determined by some of the tickets contained within the GB-821 epic.*Information on this Epic''s Relation to Business Strategy:*As mentioned in the Advisor Workstation epic, GB-367, the users of Advisor Workstation are a good target market for Goal Bridge. Goal Bridge is intended to be an international tool and there are revenue targets that we can assist in hitting by expanding internationally. Canada is a nice test case for this because WFE already has a Canadian engine that is up to date. The proactivity of the commercial product management team has also validated up front that there is some interest in a tool like Goal Bridge.*Intended Outcome and Measurement:*The ultimate measure of success is if we are able to deploy to the Canadian market in 2020. Our initial target is by end of Q1 2020 (largely pending work placed higher in priority such as the US integration and how much we need to do in the realm of accessibility support, which will be uncovered by this epic). This specific epic will be successful if we are able to complete it in a manner that is timely enough to continue to be on pace for a Q1 2020 release.聽*Dependencies:* # GB-821', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, 'Financial Planning - Q1 2020', '2020-01-01T00:00:00', '2020-03-31T00:00:00', 0, 0, '82', 'Goal Bridge - Canada - Advisor Workstation', 'GB-1053'),
    ('2771', 'PPI-4659 New Liquidity Tools Part I', 'Bsiness case:Liquidity considerations are key when evaluating asset managers, investment strategies, and alpha potential, so it''s imperitive that we develop better tools around this. The liquidity tool protoype and resulting research paper have also received good feedback and interest from investors and clients.Benefit:New metrics--e.g., days to liquiditate, burndown rate--give investors a more comprehensive view of the capacity and liquidity risk they face, which is key to evaluating a strategy''s ability to generate alpha.Description:Project to productize the liquidity tool prototype created by data/methodology and manager research. Example of prototype''s output is included in the htm file, as is the research paper that uses the new metrics.聽', -1, 5, 2, null, '2019-09-25T00:00:00', '2019-11-05T00:00:00', null, 'Data Services - October-November 2019', '2019-09-25T00:00:00', '2019-11-05T00:00:00', 13, 13, '253', 'New Liquidity Tools PPI-4659', 'DTCMER-250'),
    ('2773', 'Improve messaging for situations when portfolios do not meet 50% data sufficiency threshold and calculated results are not available', '+Sufficiency Rule+:聽In order to produce a calculated聽result for a portfolio, >50% of the holdings of the portfolio must have the data required for calculation. Data required for calculation = coverage that is no older than 6mo old.So, for example, here is the criteria for the Average Effective Duration data point:Bond % with available Fixed-Income Survey Data Average Effective Duration in the underlying funds >=0.5 * Bond % within all the underlying funds+List of data points with sufficiency rule+:聽|Equity Sector Exposure||Equity Sector (GICS)||Equity Regional Exposure||Equity Style Box Breakdown||Market Cap Breakdown||Average Market Cap||Financial Health Grade||Average Economic Moat||Price Ratios||Profitability Ratios||Maturity Range breakdown (Yrs)||Fixed Inc Style Box (Long)||Credit Quality Breakdown||Average Credit Quality||Average Eff Duration||Average Eff Maturity||Average Coupon|Calculation specs for these data points can be found here:聽[https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/PFS/Calculation+Spec+Repository]+*Problem*+: Users don''t know when their portfolio is missing data because of a system issue or because of the sufficiency threshold. It is very hard for users and CSMs to diagnose this type of problem.*This ticket is to solve this problem.*There needs to be further analysis done to figure out exactly how to fix this problem, but here are some general thoughts: # For any components that use the data points listed above, display a specific message when sufficiency threshold is not met. Something like "XX portfolio does not meet our 50% data sufficiency threshold to perform the calculation." # We need to add more holding level views for the data points listed above, so that users and CSMs can review what data is available for holdings to identify holdings that are contributing to the <50% data. That way it will be easier to check if the holdings have enough data to meet the 50% threshold. We also need to be able to see the freshness of this data (i.e. does it meet the within 6mo old threshold) # Display a data point that shows the coverage % for the portfolio for each statistic. That way we can easily see if the portfolio meets the threshold.', 488, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-1340'),
