    ('2827', '[FSNext] Launch to Production', 'h3. User StoryAs an FSNext user, I want to be able to perform end-to-end testing prior to releasing to production, and then release to production to realize the enterprise value of the system.h3. Design OverviewLink to UX/Visual Design: N/ALink to Technical Design:聽[https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/WORK/Epic+WFIS-67%3A+Launch+FSNext+to+Production]h3. In ScopeThe scope is limited to preparing the following environments for the following purposes:(1) Staging (STG) for deploying code to a pre-production environment for end-to-end testing prior to release, including all system components, NFRs satisfied, and integrated with the Staging environments of both Traditional FS and MPA(2) User Acceptance Testing (UAT) for deploying code to a production-like environment with client access for acceptance and integration testing, including all system components, NFRs satisfied, and integrated with the UAT environments of both Traditional FS and MPA(3) Production (PRD) for day-to-day system operation and live business data processing,聽including all system components, NFRs satisfied, and integrated with the Production environments of both Traditional FS and MPAh3. Out of Scope(1) Disaster Recovery (DR) for a live standby of the Production (PRD) environment with up-to-date data and configuration to be activated in the event of a disaster,聽including all system components, NFRs satisfied, and integrated with the Production environments of both Traditional FS and MPAh3. Roll Out StrategyTimelines to get all 3 parts done before releasing will lead to a delay in bringing this feature to market. In the interest of getting a smaller version of this capability to market, the SSO capability will be released to production in the following phases.+Phase 1+: Presenting a modal to show benefit and penalty from ages 62 to 70 from a link on the dashboard+Phase 2+: Updating the Social Security card on the dashboard+Phase 3+: Presenting a modal to