    ('2879', 'Improve the portfolio analysis workflow for "master / sleeve" portfolio structure', 'Many clients have portfolios that are structured such that there is one master portfolio that is comprised of various sub-portfolios, or ''sleeves''.聽For example, each of the M* funds we recently launched have several sub-advior ''sleeves'' that are managed separately, but that all contribute to the overall fund.We can already support this type of portfolio structure by loading the master portfolio as a nested account, where the sleeves are holdings.The problem is that the analysis you can do with this type of nested account is limited. So, we''d like to make some improvements to that experience.Main goals are: * Give the user the ability to analyse the master account, and the allocation of the sleeves to that account * Give the user the ability to analyze the master account by drilling into underlying sleeve level holdingsFor example, here is a master account with 6 ''sleeves'' that we imported as a sample for Amerprise.You can see the allocation of each sleeve, but you can''t drill into it.!image-2019-09-19-11-14-14-250.png!In addition, you cannot view attribution based on the underlying holdings of the sleeves.!image-2019-09-19-11-15-11-519.png!', 493, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-1343'),
    ('2880', 'PFM EC Delivery [Q4 2019]', 'PFM MWC components will be produced in vue.Current repo: cwp-vue-componentsFor developing PFM components, we''ll continue using our own repository. We will bundle and ship the components to the same repo but since they are delivered through nexus they will be made available to other teams for consumption.We need to create a Jenkins job.We need to register for MSNexus.*Project Tasks:*Component Resolver- Work needs to be done to support nexus scopes 鈥楡fp鈥? - ecquickrqa - external -> client integration demo  - developer website ask them to resolve this issue on their end MWC Verification Tool - This currently does not working, waiting on Eric Wang to debug MWC authentication - Auth tokens for requesting data (once we no longer use mock data) - Bearer token from MaaS MaaS Authentication Docs Morningstar Developerhow to get, and refresh token should be responsibility of EC team for developer website Component Loader - Get component configuration working in a local environment using Morningstar Loader  - requires the Component Resolver work to be completed. Developer Site Reqs - Create a dev site markdown file that is pulled in by a Jenkins job to generate the demo page  - Will need Hazal to come up with the language here - Get a draft approvedDocumentation Criteria: [https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/CSG/Acceptance+Criteria%3A+Documentation]聽', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, 'Financial Planning - Q4 2019', '2019-10-01T00:00:00', '2019-12-31T00:00:00', 24, 5, '21', 'CWP: Personal Financial Management (PFM) v2', 'CP-2845'),
    ('2881', 'Real-Time Portfolio Construction', '*Realtime Portfolio Construction (RPC)* is a web service that provides portfolio construction capabilities to clients via a RESTful API that aligns with Morningstar鈥檚 portfolio construction methodology and best thinking.  The major difference between PRC and APC is that PRC leaves out the Qualitative checks and oversight, Data and operational support, and Consultant relations, ad hoc analysis, etc. By separating the manual heavy components within APC, we hope to create a more flexible and scalable portfolio construction service across Workplace clients and offering real-time service will allow for integration across the various strategic workflows.  Due to legacy reasons, Retirement Manager鈥檚 Online Advice service uses a different optimizer.  This web service will implement the latest alpha/tracking-error approach and allow the advice service to use the same algorithm.', -1, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 17, 14, null, null, 'MIMAPC-1627'),
