    ('2889', 'Show custom security returns in investment workbook grid', 'A few months back, we implemented a feature to be able to see custom security returns in portfolio workbook components (https://msjira.morningstar.com/browse/CLP-1053). This covers the important use case of when users have portfolios with securities that have custom returns.We now have a聽 new scenario. Users want to compare the custom performance of securities in the investment workbook grid.This has been requested by the Merrill AI team, so they can compare the custom performance of their hedge funds against each other.The way this would work would be: * In global settings, the user selects: "Security Custom Performance Source" = <custom return stream>. * Then, for any securities that have values for this custom return stream 鈥?you see values for custom return show up in grid view. Else M* returns are shown', 759, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-1344'),
