    ('2891', 'Account Aggregation MVP [Q4 2019]', 'Review and refine user flow, visuals, and聽interactions for production-fidelity account aggregation prototype, including coding refinements. Included in this flow are: # Account Addition # Account List # Account Edit to resolve connection issues*What do users need most right now?* * Be oriented in the聽flow and understand what they are about to do/currently聽doing * Trust the system as they are sharing personal credentials to financial institutions * Have a high level understanding of their net worth * Identify accounts with connection issues and have聽a resolution path when they encounter issues*What''s critical?*聽 * Users should have visibility of system status * Identify bumpers to keep users on the happy path and develop accompanying UI ** Goal is to encourage users to aggregate all of their accounts * When errors are encountered there should be a clear path to resolution*How does this fit into the service?* * Onboards the user * Creates a personalized net worth view * Is a prerequisite for the PFM workflow聽*Account list details*{color:#00875a}In scope for MVP:{color} * Empty state of account list * Categorize linked accounts ([~hsabah] let''s discuss what these should be) * Total $ amount for all linked accounts ([~hsabah] let''s work with Kirk to determine what this should be labeled) * Confirmation of successfully added/deleted accounts * Visualization for 1st time discovery/syncing (both one account and multiple simultaneously) * Visualization for ongoing syncing * General error cases: ** Problem with first time discovery/syncing *** user action required? *** user action not required ** Added account isn''t syncing *** user action required *** user action not required{color:#de350b}Out of scope for MVP:{color} * Alternative organization of account list by custodian * Inline error resolution where possible * New institution requests (will need to revisit this process with product and compliance) * A way to handle