    ('2899', 'On Demand Data for PFM [Q4 2019]', '[https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/SWDO/On+Demand+Update+Import+PFM]*PFM events that will impact user aggregation, budget, or on demand status:* * Login:聽CP-2777 ** If (1) a CWP user logs in/PFM component is instantiated, (2) their aggregation status is A4 or A5 and (3) their on demand O1 status time stamp is more than an hour ago, then switch their on demand status to O2. * Account Aggregation:聽CP-2346,聽CP-2664, CP-2760 ** If a user''s on demand status is O2, then trigger account aggregation. ** If (1) the BAA component triggers account aggregation and (2) the user''s aggregation status is A1, then switch their aggregation status to A2. ** If (1) account aggregation is successful and (2) the user''s on demand status is O2, then switch their on demand status to O3. If it''s unsuccessful, then switch their on demand status to O1. ** If (1) account aggregation is successful and (2) the user''s aggregation status is A2, then switch their aggregation status to A3.聽If it''s unsuccessful, then switch their aggregation status to A1. * Import:聽CP-2347, CP-2348 ** If a user''s on demand status is O3, then trigger import and calculations. ** If a user''s aggregation status is A3, then trigger import and calculations. ** If (1) import and calculations are successful and (2) the user''s on demand status is O3, then switch their on demand status to O1. If they''re unsuccessful, then switch their on demand status to O1. ** If (1) import and calculations are successful and (2) the user''s aggregation status is A3, then switch their on demand status to A5. If they''re unsuccessful, then switch their on demand status to A4. ** If import and calculations are successful, then refresh the data in Aggregated Account List and PFM components. * 聽Set a first time savings target/budget:聽CP-2778 ** If (1) a user''s budget status is B2 and (2) they click on the button that sets a savings target, then set their budget status to B3. ** If (1) a user''s budget status is B2, (2) they don''t have a savings gap but want to adjust their savings target and (3) they hit save in the Edit Savings Target/Budget component, then set their budget status to B3. ** If (1) a user''s budget status is B2, (2) they have a savings gap but want to adjust their budget and (3) they hit save in the Edit Savings Target/Budget component, then set their budget status to B3. * Delete an aggregated account:聽CP-2771 ** If (1) a user deletes an aggregated account and (2) they no longer have any aggregated accounts, then set their aggregation status to A1.*PFM UI components and their interaction with user statuses:* * Aggregated Account List: ** A1 - empty CTA state CP-2765 ([https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/d/main#/console/15244152/316934343/preview]) ** A2 - first time aggregation in progress聽CP-2766 ([https://morningstar.invisionapp.com/d/main#/console/15244152/316934339/preview]) ** A3 - first time import and calculations in progress (same as A2) ** A4/O1 - import/calculation failure (same as A5) ** A5/O1 - fu', -1, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, 'Financial Planning - Q4 2019', '2019-10-01T00:00:00', '2019-12-31T00:00:00', 39, 39, '55', 'CWP: Personal Financial Management (PFM) MVP', 'CP-2849'),
    ('2900', 'Design for Security Pricing Warnings', '*Issue:* When custodial data is imported into Morningstar Office, the product maps securities being imported to the corresponding security in the product鈥檚 security database. The mapping logic used is complex and securities mapped using a reused ticker may result in an incorrectly mapped security. For example, Box, Inc. uses the ticker BOX. The ticker BOX was previously used by SeaCube Container Leasing Ltd. SeaCube Container Leasing is delisted and no longer traded on public markets. Its ticker has been reused by Box, Inc. During the import process, custodian position files containing the ticker BOX map to SeaCube Container Leasing by default even though the account truly owns Box, Inc.聽Incorrect mapping then leads to incorrect security prices, and therefore incorrect account values.聽 This has a negative impact to performance reporting and billings on accounts.聽When this issues was first addressed in 2017/18, the import team did work to update/improve the mapping logic (CIS-3764)Along with import mapping improvements, desktop implemented a feature to allow warn users of any potential security pricing issues and allow them to review flagged instances.Below is the initial warning users receive immediately upon logging into Office 3.x.聽[^SecurityMapping.pdf]聽document attached to this ticket describe the current 3.x feature in great detail.聽 It should be used as a starting point to understand the current feature.聽聽!image-2019-09-20-09-52-20-658.png|width=322,height=247!聽*Dependencies:* Office Cloud, DOPA, Import/BOS?*Dev wiki from 2018 work in 3.x*聽:聽[https://mswiki.morningstar.com/pages/viewpage.action?spaceKey=PFS&title=Security+Price+Alert]聽*Unknowns:* * Office Cloud is designed around BOS users since the goal is to move everyone to Office Suite.聽 However, as user migrate, we will still have those importing on their own in desktop. ( and its possible the import tool will continue to stay active after the rest of desktop has been retired.)聽 do we need to consider that in this design? *', 69, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, 'Cloud - Nov-Dec 2019', '2019-11-14T00:00:00', '2019-12-25T00:00:00', 0, 0, '66', 'Office Cloud - Data Management', 'OC-5055'),
