    ('2947', 'Argus - Data Model for New APC Platform', 'This Epic will track tasks connected with new data table design, necessary bridging with the loading process, determine what old fashion are required to notify ops team of the changes,  schema file refresh and data migration if needed, having the table design documented and articulate the benefits for this change. Database a. Spin up PG DBb. Draft Table DesignBusiness Backgrounds:For Argus, the database does not need to change, however, the data tables could be refactored to adapt new data flow work.  In the APC1.0 system, caused by gaggle process and repetitive RBSA in crossing processes there are a lot of redundant tables.  In the new era giving off gaggles and all stats are derived from one-off RBSA, table structures could be re-designed to reflect the changes.  As the population of funds and plans grow, old fashioned tables are confronted with challenges of being too huge to be efficient.   APC 2.0 represents an opportunity to create a system with faster and lightweight db that is specifically designed to gain more efficiency.The algorithms in Argus are extremely flexible, but to ensure consistency in the measurements and the comparison,  Set windows/tables should be used when estimating statistic. These should be values that can be changed at the admin level of the system. As regulation and scrutiny in the automated advice space increases, clients are looking for more and more information and data for decisions and the inconsistencies in the system that cannot be provided.  The APC 2.0 system attempts to do this by creating a well-defined and transparent system that is fully replicable with data deliberately stored for intermediate steps for auditing purposes. For the new version APC platform, a data model is necessary. This Epic will include the design, creation, development of the data model.聽This Epic will cover: the Object model in scripts (mostly in Python and any other programming languages if neces