    ('3056', 'FP | Charts 4Q2019', 'h2. *Why are we doing this?*The Financial Planning designers would like to develop charts that satisfy the unique requirements of our service. We have a good foundation with聽[Morningstar Base Charts|http://designsystem.morningstar.com/charts/choosing-a-chart.html]聽(MBC), but custom work is often required to build the specific types of charts we need.These customizations can be time-consuming for individual squads to design and develop. By tackling this work together we will design, build, test, and iterate on our ideas more quickly. We''ll reduce visual inconsistencies, share code, improve accessibility and interaction (particularly for touch devices), and create a more cohesive service.h2. *How will we complete this work?*Designers, developers, and content strategists will hold聽*biweekly* meetings and *monthly*聽stakeholder reviews to share work and testing results.We will聽partner with FP developers and user researchers to build and validate our ideas.We will have a JIRA board to prioritize and track this work, and estimate allocating 1鈥? points per sprint to this effort. The AX-IX聽channel will be聽used to share files聽and record our decisions.聽*Designers*[~jculber][~lkessel][~jkim2][~jhalper][~knathan][~rshanno][~mgriff1][~bvarga]聽*Developers*TBD聽 *User researchers*TBD聽 *Design stakeholders*[~sbower]David WilliamsPhilip Burton[~mkim]Brian Bouril (MBC)Alexander Hayashi (MBC)Jonathan Healy (MBC)Adam Rowe (MBC)h2. *Plan*We will deliver a minimum of five charts for our first round of work. That work will be completed by聽[date?].Depending on the particular customization, we will contribute this work to either MBC or Enterprise Components. It should be built using a framework that is compatible with all of FP.聽{color:#4c9aff}*accessible*{color} * 聽improve color contrast * create patterns for increased contrast * improve screen reader experience{color:#4c9aff}*touch-friendly*{color} * create easy ways to interact with charts on small screens * use native gestures where possible (pinch, zoom, swipe){color:#4c9aff}*interactive*{color} * create animations to reinforce movement and help tell a story{color:#4c9aff}*work at all sizes*{color} * switch format where appropriate (i.e. chart > table) * improve small screen typography (i.e. legends, labels, axes) * create labels and markers for points of interest (i.e. today, goal amount, drawdown) * print friendly (color contrast, interaction, etc. have to be surfaced in static image){color:#4c9aff}*test well for comprehension*{color} * create labels and markers to identify聽points of interest (i.e. today, goal amount, drawdown) * focus on one thing at a time 鈥斅爑se multiple charts to communicate complex ideas rather than layeringh2. *Impact*This work directly supports our聽[Product Quality Initiative|https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/PRODSCSS/Product+Quality+Initiative]聽by making our charts functional, easy-to-use, memorable, and meaningful.', -1, 0, 5, '#a59e89', null, null, null, 'Financial Planning - Q4 2019', '2019-10-01T00:00:00', '2019-12-31T00:00:00', 16, 0, '317', 'IX | Goals-Based Risk MVP', 'IX-359'),
