    ('3063', 'Cloud Session State', 'Currently the platform allows as many concurrent sessions as UIM allows. This is 1000 for the UIM realm most of our users belong to. Direct 3.x allows only one concurrent login. They have data on how often one user logging in logs out another user, number of different pcs that login to an account, and number of windows login ids that login to a different account. Some of that data is attached to help demonstrate that issue.Shows number of times a user has kicked themselves out:L:\OneTeam\Usage Tracking\DirectUserProfileReport\Combined User Profile Report.xlsShows details on PC''s that have logged in for a specific account and what windows user names were used over last 13 weeks:L:\OneTeam\Usage Tracking\DirectMachineDetails (last 13 weeks)If we allow users authenticated with UIM to enter the platform without signing in that what is the user saying when they logout? Do they want their UIM session ended which would kick them out of other M* products or just the cloud session ended which would mean that if they came back they would login again automatically? Would a user expect that if they log out of another Morningstar product that their cloud session was ended as well?', 299, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLOUDPLT-275'),
