    ('3153', 'Migration off expiring server software', '*From Kostya''s email:*This topic came up again in a meeting yesterday and it is one of those 鈥渘ot fun鈥?emails about a project that we must undertake as a team that relies on physical servers in Chicago and Dallas. We can meet and discuss all of this in more detail, but in short, many of our servers (Application and DB) are running very outdated Windows Server software which will actually be sunset by Microsoft  in January 2020. Morningstar, along with most companies around the world, must ensure that we migrate off these servers as soon as possible. The good news is that we don鈥檛 have dozens of on-prem servers like RM or other teams, but we still have a few and I鈥檇 strongly recommend that we don鈥檛 leave this work for Q4. Obviously, having a dedicated DevOps person will help (and we鈥檙e interviewing numerous candidates to make it happen), however, it鈥檇 be prudent to start discussing timelines, dependencies, and which tasks must be done in preparation for this effort. *From intro meeting:*(ideally devops tasks once hired)- Create ticket with IT PPM for 10 machines - or fewer? can combine any?- Go to the team''s meeting every Weds- They will install Windows 2016 and proper security groups- Check firewall rules, IIS/DB, etc.', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 30, 0, null, null, 'MIMPSA-3577'),
