    ('3353', '[MPA] UBS Home Office Reporting', 'Morningstar will provide reporting to the UBS home office beginning after the initial launch. Reports will be delivered in a CSV file format and posted to an FTP site on a quarterly basis. Morningstar will work with UBS to build out the home office dashboard and requirements through a separate process. Reports will include:*Report Name:* Plan Exception Supervision*Description:* Excel report that will capture only funds out of compliance and asset category violations.聽 This should include all error codes associated with these out of compliance. The error codes included would be as follows: 1005, 1006, 1007, 1011, 3027, 3028, 3029, 3030. This exception report should start 120 days after violation begins.聽 Need this report to be "ready" to go directly to the supervision team.*Frequency:* Monthly*Report Name:* Plan Exception Detail*Description:* Excel report that contains list of all plans in the UBS RPA program across all providers that have unapproved funds and are not meeting asset category requirements. Plans should be displayed after 120 days of non-compliance.*Frequency:* Monthly*Report Name:* Plan Status Summary*Description:* Excel report that contains list of all plans in the UBS RPA program across all providers. The report will include the results of the compliance check, errors, along with other plan details like start/end dates.*Frequency:* Weekly*Report Name:* All Plans Summary*Description:* Excel report that will include a list of enrolled plans in the program by provider, lineup, assets, and as of date*Frequency:* Monthly*Report Name:* Plan Reconciliation*Description:* Excel file that will be generated monthly and will help reconcile the plans on both the UBS and Morningstar systems by identifying plans that exist for one entity but not the other.*Frequency:* Monthly*Report Name:* Stale Plan*Description:* Excel file that includes plans that the provider previously included in the eligible plans data but for which no data has been sent in at least 1 month. The stale plan report will be shared with UBS on a monthly basis.*Frequency:* Monthly*Report Name:* Emails Sent*Description:* UBS does not want to receive emails via BCC but does want to track which advisors were sent emails. We will provide UBS with a list of all emails that we have sent.*Frequency:* Monthly*Report Name:* Email Bounce Back*Description:* If any emails are undeliverable due to an invalid email address, the email system will track this information in a log file. On a monthly basis, Morningstar will provide an Excel file with the invalid email addresses to UBS. The file will be provided monthly even if there are no failed deliveries the prior month.*Frequency:* MonthlyIn addition to the external UBS reports above, Morningstar will also produce internal reports for its operations team. The internal reports have been included below.*Report Name:* FA Delta Change Report*Description:* Morningstar to report new FAs added for MPA access and FAs removed from MPA access since las', -1, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'WFIS-40'),
    ('3354', '[MPA] UBS Fi360 Reporting', 'UBS has indicated that they would like to use Fi360 for the quarterly plan reports. UBS advisors are familiar with the Fi360 reports and are using them today. The reports are used by advisors to share plan-level investment information with the plan sponsor client. When changes are needed, the UBS advisors will identify several proposed investment options that can be used as replacements. The proposed replacements are shared with the plan sponsor so a decision can be made on how to proceed. In addition to an advisor selecting multiple fund options, Morningstar will also indicate up to three preferred funds that may be used as proposed replacements. All preferred funds will be active funds, even when the unapproved fund they are slated to potentially replace is a passive fund.聽 Unidentified funds will not be included as part of the information sent to Fi360.Morningstar will integrate with Fi360 to share and receive information. Morningstar will share the following information with Fi360, in two files, so that they can create the plan level quarterly reports. Files will be delivered in .txt format, with a pipe delimitator used to separate the data points. Morningstar is not responsible or liable for how Fi360 uses or stores the data we are sending them.聽*Plan Data File to Fi360 from Morningstar*|*Field Name*|*Example*|*Comments*||UBS Account ID|NA12671|This information will be provided by UBS in the plan-ready file.||FA ID|NAJW|This information will be provided by UBS in the plan-ready file.||Plan Name|Sample Plan|Plan name displayed from the plan provider by default. Advisor can optionally update the plan name in the UI. If advisor updates the plan name, it will be used on all subsequent UI pages, included on reports, and sent to Fi360.||Include Assets?|Y|We will default to not send the investment assets for the plan, but the advisor will have the ability in MPA to include the plan assets in the Fi360 report. Default = No assets||As of Date|06-30-2019|This will be the quarter end date of the provider鈥檚 data. There are only 4 valid values. Format will be mm-dd-yyyyMorningstar has added a parameter to the API endpoint to allow providers to send quarter-end data. We will Fi360 with that quarter-end data. If providers have not sent Morningstar quarter-end data, we will follow up with them. ||Required Asset Class status|<Failure Reason > 聽|Will be populated when a plan has an asset class failure. If a plan has multiple failures, Morningstar will list all issues in one cell, separated by commas with the message in quotes. Morningstar to provide messages to cover the four asset class rules. If null, Fi360 can consider the plan in compliance.|聽*Fund Data File to Fi360 from Morningstar*|*Field Name*|*Example*|*Comments*||UBS Account ID|NA12671|This information will be provided by UBS in the plan-ready file.||Morningstar SecID|F00000N3WT|All funds will be identified by a secID value. For funds that do not have a known Morningstar secID value, a custom secID ', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'WFIS-4'),
    ('3355', '[MPA] Advisor Access', 'UBS advisors will access MPA through a direct login process for the initial launch. Single sign on SSO) will be evaluated at a later date. Advisors will be directed to MPA to first create an account. Account setup will ask advisor for full name, UUNAME, email address, and allow them to set a password. Once the account is created, advisor can sign in using their UUName/password. Upon successful sign in, the advisor will be taken to the advisor dashboard. The advisor will only see the plans that are assigned to them and are live within the RPA program.UBS will send Morningstar an advisor file, in CSV format, in order to track which advisors have an MPA account. The advisor file will be a complete file in that it will contain all UBS advisors that have access to MPA. Advisor file will be sent by UBS daily (Monday 鈥?Friday) as advisors can leave and be added at any time. Morningstar will use the UUNAME identifier to validate users as they create their account in MPA. An advisor will not be able to create an MPA account if we do not have the advisor鈥檚 UUNAME in our database. The advisor file will include the following information: * UUNAME * This is the UBS internal employee id * This field is used as the unique identifier in the user file * This field is also used for mapping to the Entitlement file * First Name * First Name of the user * Last Name * Last Name of the user * Email * This is the email of the user * Role Mapping * There are three roles options (UBS1, UBS2, and UBS3) for FirmPlus * These roles are assigned to a user granting the user with any permissions assigned to that role. Morningstar will allow home office users access to plans. Home office users will have the ability to enter an FAID upon login to view plans associated with the FAID. 聽 * UBS1 = UBS Fiduciary Pilot User * UBS2 = UBS FPE User * UBS3 = UBS Corporate UserSample Advisor File|UUNAME|test_2183||First Name|Robin||Last Name|Viper||Email Address|[RV@ubs.com|mailto:RV@ubs.com]||Role Mapping|UBS1, UBS2, or UBS3|聽UBS will also provide a separate entitlement file, in CSV format, that Morningstar will use to tie the advisor user information to the financial advisor ID (FAID). The entitlement file will be a complete file in that it will contain all UUNAME and FAID combinations at that point in time. The FAID will be used to link the advisor users to the retirement plans. One UUNAME will be associated with multiple FAIDs and multiple UUNAMES can be linked to the same FAID. UBS home office users will be assigned an FAID value of 鈥淎LL鈥? This will give them the ability to view all plans in the MPA UI associated with a particular FAID. Home office users will have the ability to enter other FAIDs as well in the same session. The entitlement file will contain the following information: * UUNAME * This is used to map the user to the appropriate FAID. * FAID * Split the UU has access to * Entity Name * This would be the "Name" of the FA ID group.Sample Entitlement File|UUNAME|test_2183||FA', -1, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'WFIS-2'),
