    ('3381', 'Move alerts to Data API V2 as data source', '+Current:+* alerts is currently using the legacy RDB database as the source to trigger our alert * Right now, we are only solving part of the user''s problem. Our alerts vision states: The modern investor is inundated with financial data and content 鈥?Morningstar Alerts helps filter out the noise and highlights what our clients should prioritize and care about today to help them make better investing decisions.That said, we are really only solving for part of their challenges 鈥?we aren''t really highlighting everything our clients care about, we are missing a BIG piece ** * ** * +*What will this allow us to do?*+ * *Portfolio alerting* - Need for portfolio alerts: need to quantify this 鈥?get them to buy-in and scope out the work 鈥?see what they say about business impact * *Central alerting service (that is triggering off of the central data source API V2) to the rest of M* and potentially* *clients* - Need so we can open up our alerts API to other teams instead of continuing to do work on our legacy system which we know is flawed and time consuming. 3 teams have requested to utilize our alerting service ** The fin planning team, .com, and ARC Australia have all come to me asking to hook up to our alerting system ** it is inefficient to build different alerting systems around Morningstar when we have invested a lot of time and money developing a brand-new solution. Other teams should be able to easily use this ** This supports Morningstar''s overall goal of moving towards MaaS - Morningstar as a service * *M**ore updated, consistent data with cloud and other teams* (RDB is a more complex data source to use and has been outdated and triggering faults) ** Problems we''ve seen with the Analyst Rating change and fund manager - Worried about misalignment between what''s in v2 and showing in cloud vs the data/values we''re triggering on  * *Retire* *our L**egacy system quicker* 鈥?legacy APIs trying to retire these * *Incorporate more of Morningstar''s IP* ** Allows us to utilize more of Morningstar''s IP that is only getting put into V2 and not other data sources ** We cannot trigger off of data points that are only available in API V2 ** Sustainability alerts - potential deal with PNC and they have specifically requested additional sustainability alerts *** Company level data (API V2 handling entitlement) *** Sustainanalytics rating (Sustainanalytics peer group classification) *** Fund product involvement : conditional *** Company product involvement (entitlement restrictions)  * *Conditional alerting* 鈥?this could be built into API v2 kafka process **please note this requires dependent teams to do work before NERTS can do anything - I have not had detailed discussions with the API teams about how to implement this yet, hoping to better understand priority from a business perspective - Adrian previously suggested I include it as a CLP epic this time around)', 575, 5, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 4, 0, null, null, 'CLP-590'),
