    ('3400', '2.0 Multicollinearity', 'There appear to be more problems in the sector and region regressions above those described in RISK-70.  1) This is a heatmap of the factor covariance matrix.  On the lower right hand side, an anomalous region is visible, with extreme inter-sector and inter-region correlation, and anti-correlation between the regions and sectors.2) Part of the cause is probably both of the collections of exposures being the results of regressions to the weekly returns.   This means that it''s easy to express regions as linear combinations of regions and sectors.3) The result is multicollinearity, where the reliability of the model premia are diminished.4) Impact - the forecast statistics (e.g. forecast vol/CVaR) should not be affected, the errors should net out.  Scenario analysis should not be affected for multi-day scenarios (the effect will wash out).    But for actual diagnostics the protfolios will not be too usable.', -1, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 21, 0, null, null, 'RISK-936'),
