    ('3406', '2.0 Equity Model', 'As a risk model user, I want the risk model to support essentially the same model features as risk model 1.0.聽 Key features in this epic include: * 34 of the 36 factors (all bar ownership lens) must be produced in substantially the same way.聽 Acceptance criteria are the construction of the exposures which are聽聽substantially equal to the 1.0 model. * The universe must be implemented and be substantially the same as 1.0.聽 Acceptance criteria is observing that the coverage and estimation universe on some particular dates is substantially identical. * Data filtering must be implemented, and a QA process against the 1.0 code performed. * The residuals and premia must be calculated from equity data snapshots provided by the AAI team - essentially the lift+shift 1.0 inputs. * It must be possible to populate a database with the complete model output in a schema suitable for the APG team to query. The full model must run in less than 3 hours, and the load must happen in less than 2.Additional acceptance criteria * We should see the same basic pattern in value-growth, size and momentum factors * The OL factors are small, so we should see approximately the same percentage of variance assigned to factors vs residuals as in the 1.0 modelOut of Scope: * ICA/forecast model * Ownership lens * Devops/production operations聽', -1, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 100, 29, null, null, 'RISK-821'),
