    ('3410', '2.0 Scenario Analysis', 'There are five APIs considered under Scenario Analysis: # Pre-defined scenario analysis (discussed in issues聽RISK-595聽and聽RISK-596) # Macroeconomic Shock Scenario Analysis (MSSA) API, which is broken down into nine separate issues ## Interactive UI (RISK-589) takes a user-defined list聽of macroeconomic variables, a user-defined sub-list of聽macroeconomic variables聽to be shocked, the total duration in months of the shocks, and the scale of the shock relative to the most recent value of the variable to be shocked for each month specified and produces the following output to be used in the MSSA API: *** A dataframe of raw macroeconomic data from Marketplace as shown in raw_data.csv attached to issue聽RISK-583 *** A dataframe of macroeconomic variables indexed to the shock duration in months along with the associated scales as shown in scale_table.csv attached to聽RISK-560 ## Cumulative monthly product of daily returns (RISK-558) ## MSSA data preparation (RISK-583) ## Shocked data preparation (RISK-560) ## Principal Components Analysis (PCA) (RISK-585) ## Linear regression from PCA to risk premia (RISK-584) ## Vector Autoregression (VAR) and Lagrange Multiplier Solution (RISK-603) ## Risk Factor Premia Mean Forecast (RISK-604) ## Risk Factor Premia VolatilityForecast (RISK-605) # Market-driven scenario analysis聽API (RISK-586) # Causal Scenario Analysis聽(RISK-587) # Capital Markets Assumptions (CMA) scenario analysis (RISK-588)聽', -1, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'RISK-465'),
