    ('3435', 'Cloud Technical Operations Scorecard Star Rating Improvement', '75 of the 76 open tickets aligning to the various Cloud team capabilities closed at end of December/Jan Planning Period. 22 new items have been opened per the TOI scans as of 1/10/19 linked below.聽This epic is to track ownership of the needed tickets to improve our scorecard star rating. This will be a cross platform all hands effort that rolls up to the sustainability star measurement for Cloud Platform Improvement Plan.Click here to view all open issues for the DIRECTPLPer [Rachel Nartatez|https://msjira-sf.morningstar.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rnartat] update from September copied below. More background can also be obtained from viewing Stephen and Sharon''s [update here|https://morningstaronline.sharepoint.com/portals/hub/_layouts/15/PointPublishing.aspx?app=video&p=p&chid=18d70363-5324-4475-9021-9757b8d5e277&vid=9c1152df-0a1e-4d68-a24a-bd29ddbe91c0&from=1]------On *Monday 9/10* we are rolling out the NEW Technical Operation Scorecard Star Rating to measure our systems data transparency, track and report on key operational elements and metrics which will be reviewed monthly by the senior leadership team. You will receive an email containing your Technical Operations Scorecard Star Rating along with links to Jira Tickets specifically indicating outstanding data you are required to provide in order for your team to reach 5 STAR status. This is the process we have put in place in order to ensure the operational readiness of our products![How the Rating Works|https://mswiki.morningstar.com/display/technology/Technical+Operations+Scorecard] (Click Here)*+OH NO! You don鈥檛 have a 5 star!?+*If you don鈥檛 have 5 stars yet鈥ot ideal, but the good news is we are here to help you get there! Below are a few helpful steps and we will also be holding *OFFICE HOURS every Tuesday from 3-4PM (CT).* Please reach out to me, [@Rachel Nartatez|mailto:Rachel.Nartatez@morningstar.com] , indicating which