    ('3563', 'CLP - Performance Reports Liquid Objects Migration (Phase 1 Read Only)', '聽聽*Phase 1*聽聽*- Performance Report Liquid Object Read Only Requirements*聽Viewing/Adding/Deleting Performance Reports between 3X/Cloud: # A user can see all of their 3x Performance Reports in Cloud. # A user''s 3X reports will be exist in a separate section of the main hamburger menu (similar to Workbooks, Lists & Screens, etc) under "3X Performance Reports".聽 # When a user goes into hamburger menu and opens "3X Performance Reports", they will see all of the same 3X Performance Reports that are available in their Direct 3X Performance Report folder.聽 # In the "3x Performance Reports" section, at a minimum the user will see the 3X Performance Report name, the owner, and last calculated date/time (regardless of where it was calculated).聽 # If a user creates/deletes performance reports in 3X, the user will see those updates in the "3x Performance Reports" section of the hamburger menu in Cloud. This will be reflected immediately upon refresh in the Cloud folder.聽 # All 3X Performance Reports opened in Cloud will be "read only". # Users cannot create any NEW performance reports in Cloud. They can only view any already created and saved 3x performance reports from Direct 3X in Cloud. # The performance reports displayed in 3X and in cloud will always match.聽Opening/Calculating Performance Reports in Cloud: # When the user clicks on the 3X Performance Report from the "3X Performance Reports" folder in Cloud to open it, the "3x report" will appear within the Cloud 鈥済rid".聽聽 # If the report was previously calculated (regardless of where it was calculated), the last calculated data will show within the grid.聽 # Users can open any 3x Performance Report and see exactly same rows, same columns, same values in cells, same format on cells as in 3X. # The report will be the 3X performance report with a Cloud Grid facelift. The UI will be the Cloud grid.聽 # The user can kick off the calculation for the report either from the file management "3X Performance Reports" Folder or by opening the 3X performance report and clicking "calculate" while the report is open.聽 # Once the user begins calculating the report, if it is open the report will close and the user will be taken back to the "3X Performance Reports" folder. # If the user tries to open the 3x performance report in Cloud before it has finished calculating, the user will receive a notification that their calculation will be cancelled if they proceed. If they continue to open the report, the calculation will cancel and the user can see the grid with no calculated data.聽 # While the report is calculating the user can see the estimated percentage in the "last calculated" column in the "3X Performance Reports" folder. # When a 3X performance report in Cloud has finished calculating, the user will receive some type of notification (in Cloud notification, email, etc.). 3X provides a notification to the user wherever they are in Direct once the report has been completed. It gives the user the option to go to the calcu', 332, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CLP-1088'),
