    ('3849', '[MPA] UBS - Advisor Dashboard', 'We will display the following fields in the advisor鈥檚 live plan dashboard: Plan Name, UBS Account Number, Program Type, Provider, Assets, Contract Date, Status.|Field|Description||Plan Name|Plan name displayed from the plan provider||UBS Account Number|This is the UBS account number||Program Type|Will be RPA at launch||Provider|Will include the plan provider||Assets|This is the total sum of the plan assets as sent to us by the plan provider.||Contract Date|Date the advisor added the plan in the prospecting flow||Status|Should be Live and Terminated|聽UBS has indicated that they would like terminated plans to be set to inactive and remain in the UI for filtering.UBS and Morningstar agree to remove the to-do list from the advisor dashboard for launch. UBS and Morningstar will evaluate incorporating a UBS messaging capability which will allow the UBS home office to surface relevant program notifications in MPA. Since this has not been scoped, it will not be included for the initial launch. 聽UBS has also indicated that they would like an as of date included next to the asset distribution for each provider. This is needed because the providers may send the asset information in the eligible plans API call on the same day.', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'WFIS-77'),
    ('3850', '[MPA] Create Account flow for UBS', 'UBS will send Morningstar a plan-ready file, daily, as the retirement plans work through the contract process. UBS confirmed that full files will be sent on a daily basis. The initial file may be empty until plans are sold but going forward full files will be sent. Morningstar will use the plan-ready file to load plan information to the MPA plan profile section of the user interface as well as to begin checking compliance. The plan-ready file will also indicate to Morningstar when a plan should be terminated. The plan-ready file will contain the following information: * Contract ID聽 * Client Name聽 * Plan Name聽 * Contract聽Type聽 * Date Executed聽 * Contract FAID聽 * CAI Account No.聽 * Inception AUM聽 * Flat BPS Fee Rate聽 * Plan TAX ID聽 * Provider聽聽 * Status (will be Executed or Terminated per UBS)Sample Plan-Ready File|Contract ID|FD1008||Client Name|ABBA Co.||Plan Name|ABBA Plan||Contract Type UBS confirmed that only the contract type of 鈥淔AN鈥?should be considered a live plan at launch.|FAD||Contract Date|11/8/2018||Contract FAID|NAJW||UBS Account Number|NA12671||Inception AUM|$556,859||Flat BPS Fee Rate|0.0075||Plan TAX IDUBS confirmed that this will be sent without dashes. Morningstar will save without the dash but show with the dash in the UI.|222222222||Provider|paychex||Contract Status|Executed|聽Using the advisor file, entitlement file, and plan ready file, Morningstar will know which advisors have access to the MPA UI as well as to which plans they have access. UBS will send all files above as CSV and send them via FTP server. Morningstar will work with UBS to finalize timing of the file transfer. When an FA leaves UBS, the FA should be removed from MPA.If an FA drops from an FAID, the FA should no longer have access to those plans associated with the FAID. in the entitlement file, Morningstar will immediately work to delink the advisor from the plan in the MPA interface and cease all corresponding processes like notifications. If FA is dropped from the advisor file, Morningstar will remove access to MPA. UBS has confirmed that for shared advisor access (multiple advisors sharing one FAID on a given account) Morningstar will give those shared advisors equal read/write access to those associated plans.Morningstar will modify the MPA UI so that Advisor ID is replaced with the UBS UUNAME on the account setup page. Once the advisor creates an account, they will be able to login using their UUName and password combination going forward.聽聽', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'WFIS-90'),
    ('3851', '[MPA] UBS Prospecting Flow', '*Prospects*Advisors want to create a sample lineup for plan sponsor prospects. Upon accessing MPA, advisors can select the prospect link and will be taken to the prospect dashboard. Advisors will be able to view a list of prospects, along with the provider selected, the lineup type, date added, as well as status. Advisors can create a new prospect by selecting the 鈥淎dd New Prospect鈥?link. They will then enter the prospect name, select a provider, and can optionally include a plan tax ID. We will then display information on each of the providers products. The product information will be sent to us by the plan provider. Upon selecting a provider and product, advisors can optionally add in the prospect鈥檚 current lineup. They will have two options for adding in the current lineup: 1.) upload the fund data through a csv file or 2.) manually add in each investment by either entering the fund name, ticker, or Morningstar SecID. We would then allow the advisor to view the plans current lineup for evaluation against the approved fund options for each menu (Standard, Expanded, and Custom). Morningstar will also display the following metrics: INCLUDE UP TO 7 METRICS HERE. The advisor will have the ability to download and print a PDF of the current lineup and proposed lineup for the plan to evaluate.', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'WFIS-76'),
