    ('4056', 'Liquidity Tool in Cloud', 'Background: The liquidity project is the highest priority Manager Research Analyst team request for 2019. It involves analyzing an existing internal analyst tool they''ve created and converting the ideas to a cloud component(s). \n\nWhat Is Liquidity Risk?\nLiquidity is a term used to refer to how easily an asset or security can be bought or sold in the market. It basically describes how quickly something can be converted to cash. There are two different types of liquidity risk. The first is funding liquidity or cash flow risk, while the second is market liquidity risk, also referred to as asset/product risk.', -1, 0, 5, '#ff4e4d', null, null, null, 'Cloud_Q1 2020', '2019-12-26T00:00:00', '2020-03-18T00:00:00', 0, 0, null, null, 'RSMR-4555'),
