    ('4058', 'Retiring RM Edition', 'We are going to retire the Risk Model Edition (Risk Model playground) in Direct Web. This is a edition that we use for testing new risk models and features, in some cases gathering client feedback. That''s why it need to be in PROD environment, so that it is accessible from outside of Morningstar office. Now that Risk Model 2.0 has been running in PROD for over a year. We''ll be keep adding new features. But the existing features should be enough to demo to clients that we won''t need this testing Edition.聽In the case when we need to roll-out new Risk Models for internal testing purpose. We can use QA/STG for testing. If it need to be on PROD, we are also technical ready for permission control on features/models using EAMS system. With that we grant access to the features/models by user login.聽Note, we''ll still keep the "Risk Model Analysis" workbook, which is used as landing workbook for Direct Desktop version.聽', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'APG-4402'),
