    ('4076', 'UIS Office global error messages', 'As a PO, I want to get more information on how Error Messages are applied globally to transactions, so that I can make informed updates to the criteria.聽Business need:The BOS import team has noted transactions with the comment "Cash in Lieu" which are not being automatically flagged with the warning message "Cash In Lieu Transaction." and therefore auto posting. They believe there are a set of global rules (not interface specific) which are used to add warning messages to transactions based on Comments, so we would like to get more information on what these general rules are, so that we can better manage them.聽We are unaware on what general rules exist to apply errors that are not Interface specific, so any information that exists would be very helpful, not limited only to transactions.', -1, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CIS-3921'),
    ('4077', 'Client Mapping Update', 'As a user of Morningstar Office, I want to have more strict Account to Client Mapping rules, so that Accounts are not associated with incorrect personal information, or mapped to Clients incorrectly.聽Business need:We have identified scenarios where New Accounts are being associated with Existing Members that contain personal information different than what the New Account should have. For example, a New Account can map to an Existing Client record the same name, even if those two individuals have different SSN''s (In these scenarios, the SSN is NOT provided on the New Account). We want to prevent this incorrect mapping.聽Planned Acceptance Criteria: AC 1:Given a New Account is imported, it will attempt to map based on personal information on all existing Member records in Office.AC 2:Given a New Account is imported, it will attempt to map on multiple personal identifiers of each existing member. A positive match will only be made if: * SSN/TIN Matches (If Available) {color:#d04437}AND{color} * Member First Name and Last Name Matches (If Available) {color:#d04437}AND{color} * Two additional data points match: ** Number of Street Address (Starting numeric characters only) ** Birth Date ** Email Address ** Cell Phone ** Home Phone ** Phone ** Work Phone ** Fax NumberBelow are the only valid Matches: * {color:#14892c}(SSN/TIN) and (Two additional data points from list){color} * {color:#14892c}(Member First Name and Last Name) and (Two additional data points from list){color} * {color:#14892c}(SSN/TIN) and (Member First Name and Last Name) and (Two additional data points from list){color}Below are NOT valid Matches: * {color:#d04437}Only (SSN/TIN){color} * {color:#d04437}Only (Member First Name and Last Name){color} * {color:#d04437}Only (Two additional data points from list){color} * {color:#d04437}(SSN/TIN) and (Member First Name and Last Name){color}AC 3:Given a new account is imported, and a match to an existing member cannot be made based on AC 2, a new client will be created.', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'CIS-3919'),
