    ('4082', 'UIS Import of PFM Data', 'Modify the UIS BAA import to identify ''other'' accounts to that holdings and transactions for those accounts can be passed through to Kafka.聽 This allows Office BOS customers to leverage personal financial data in these ''other'' accounts for planning, client port, or other purposes outside of Office.聽 Basically, ''other'' accounts are those which the user does not wish to reconcile and are typically NOT investment accounts.聽 聽This project will require coordination and possibly development from BAA, DOPA and DBA (Kafka) teams.', -1, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 2, 2, null, null, 'CIS-3655'),
    ('4083', 'TDA Job Scheduler: Required files for TDA', 'BOS has recently found out that TDA will not generate a SEC or PRI file for a Rep that does not have a legitimate holding with a ticker symbol or cusip number.Based on the information listed above for TDA only:聽 1) For the *Non-Tax Lot Job Scheduler *- Is there a way that we can have the SEC and PRI files omitted from being a Required file?2) For the *Tax Lot and Cost Basis Job Schedulers *- Can we have additional logic included to read. If there is a SEC or PRI file in the Sub-folder then we need a CBL file for the Job to Finish. If there is no CBL file the job will Fail.I have made this issue critical because currently DMA''s have to manually import Offices that fall under this scenario causing additional time not only importing, reconciling but also reviewing their blotter.Could you please provide me with an estimate on how long it will take to make this changes?聽[Interface that apply the new source helper logic]: TDA office, TDA EDM,聽 BPS, Heldaway, heldaway annuity', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 8, 0, null, null, 'CIS-3653'),
    ('4084', 'Enable mapping with existed UD Security in new UD Security Blotter', 'As an user, I would like to # able to map the new user defined security with existed one in new user defined security blotter聽and the new user defined security can be replaced by the existed one # user has option to re-run reconciliation or not when replace # Once the new user defined security was replaced by the existed one,next time, given the same new user defined security was brought in, it can be recognized as the existed one.-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Currently, in new user defined security blotter, user only can select Morningstar Security to do mapping. This story is asking for allow user to map new user defined security with existing user defined security.', -1, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 11, 0, null, null, 'CIS-3049'),
