    ('4090', 'CAN UI Updates/Configurations', 'This work will capture the configuring of screens to be appropriate for a Canadian audience (ie "province" instead of "state" in personal information).*Strategy for User Research & Usability Testing:*With respect to validating the usability of Goal Bridge on the whole in the Canadian market, the commercial product management team has done some preliminary work in speaking to potential Canadian users. Attached is some feedback that was received.聽*Information on this Epic''s Relation to Business Strategy:*As mentioned in the Advisor Workstation epic,聽GB-367, the users of Advisor Workstation are a good target market for Goal Bridge. Goal Bridge is intended to be an international tool and there are revenue targets that we can assist in hitting by expanding internationally. Canada is a nice test case for this because WFE already has a Canadian engine that is up to date. The proactivity of the commercial product management team has also validated up front that there is some interest in a tool like Goal Bridge.*Intended Outcome and Measurement:*The ultimate measure of success is if we are able to deploy to the Canadian market in 2020. Our initial target is by end of Q1 2020 (largely pending work placed higher in priority such as the US integration and how much we need to do in the realm of accessibility support, which will be uncovered by this epic). This specific epic will be successful if we are able to complete it in a manner that is timely enough to continue to be on pace for a Q1 2020 release.', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 1, 0, null, null, 'GB-2269'),
    ('4091', 'Share Class Level Flag', '* Direct Cloud implemented alerts with assumption that non-report collections are share class specific like MR reports. * Due to this incorrect assumption, alerts do not include all share classes for a fund in an RPS document. * Alerts team and Direct Cloud has asked RPS tech resources to change a number of collections such that all active share classes for a fund are automatically populated. This way, the alerts team doesn''t need to change its implementation or use its own tech resources for its own product. * RPS has offered to create a share class tag in the tagging UI to flag rare exceptions to the fund-level assumption. * RPS API already provides the fund ID to allow products to get all share classes for the fund. * M* Magazine collection had the same type of share class mapping until a special request was made to change this collection by Adam Holzer in 2017. See attached email.聽[^RE Morningstar Magazine Collection Fund Tagging Bug 2017-11-8 Request to Enhance Magazine Securities Mapping.msg] * ^Wiki created December 2018:聽[https://mswiki.morningstar.com/pages/viewpage.action?spaceKey=RP&title=Manager+Research+Alerts+-+Thematic+Content+for+Related+Share+Classes]^ * ^RPS to explore effort and impact for thematic collections in scope: 662,691,760,761,762,763,764,770,789.^ ## (1 developer - 2 sprints) Option 1: Modifying UI security mapping to populate all fund share classes for a given fund. ## (1 developer - 3 sprints) Option 2: New data point or tag that flags thematic content with a share class specific exception. ## (1 developer - 1 sprint) Option 3: New tag * Tech Notes 11/21/2019: ** Either option 1 or option 2 are Large (8-13 pts) ** Tech team prefers option 2 if necessary to rewrite component for share class level flag, but is it really worth the resources? ** Easiest and quickest way to get a share class level flag is to create a tag. Tech team prefers this over option 2.', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null,