    ('4115', '[MPA] Sign In flow for UBS', 'UBS will send Morningstar a plan-ready file, daily, as the retirement plans work through the contract process. UBS confirmed that full files will be sent on a daily basis. The initial file may be empty until plans are sold but going forward full files will be sent. Morningstar will use the plan-ready file to load plan information to the MPA plan profile section of the user interface as well as to begin checking compliance. The plan-ready file will also indicate to Morningstar when a plan should be terminated. The plan-ready file will contain the following information: * Contract ID聽 * Client Name聽 * Plan Name聽 * Contract聽Type聽 * Date Executed聽 * Contract FAID聽 * CAI Account No.聽 * Inception AUM聽 * Flat BPS Fee Rate聽 * Plan TAX ID聽 * Provider聽聽 * Status (will be Executed or Terminated per UBS)Sample Plan-Ready File|Contract ID|FD1008||Client Name|ABBA Co.||Plan Name|ABBA Plan||Contract Type UBS confirmed that only the contract type of 鈥淔AN鈥?should be considered a live plan at launch.|FAD||Contract Date|11/8/2018||Contract FAID|NAJW||UBS Account Number|NA12671||Inception AUM|$556,859||Flat BPS Fee Rate|0.0075||Plan TAX IDUBS confirmed that this will be sent without dashes. Morningstar will save without the dash but show with the dash in the UI.|222222222||Provider|paychex||Contract Status|Executed|聽Using the advisor file, entitlement file, and plan ready file, Morningstar will know which advisors have access to the MPA UI as well as to which plans they have access. UBS will send all files above as CSV and send them via FTP server. Morningstar will work with UBS to finalize timing of the file transfer. When an FA leaves UBS, the FA should be removed from MPA.If an FA drops from an FAID, the FA should no longer have access to those plans associated with the FAID. in the entitlement file, Morningstar will immediately work to delink the advisor from the plan in the MPA interface and cease all corresponding processes like notifications. If FA is dropped from the advisor file, Morningstar will remove access to MPA. UBS has confirmed that for shared advisor access (multiple advisors sharing one FAID on a given account) Morningstar will give those shared advisors equal read/write access to those associated plans.Morningstar will modify the MPA UI so that Advisor ID is replaced with the UBS UUNAME on the account setup page. Once the advisor creates an account, they will be able to login using their UUName and password combination going forward.聽聽', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'WFIS-98'),
