    ('4228', 'Add-In Cloud', 'Business Story:This Epic is for enabling Excel Add-In in Office 365. As of now, the Add-In works in desktop Excel for PCs only and there聽are couple issues compromising user experience. One is that Mac users cannot access the Add-In. Even though the majority of Add-In users are corporate users with PCs, this does limit the possibility of Add-In usage on personal computers or on Mac for some users. Second is the inconvenience of upgrading. Since聽most users are from corporates, software upgrades need to be approved and conducted by their IT department, which is time consuming, resulting in clients being on outdated versions and are reluctant to upgrade. Due to security requirements, sometimes the software is incompatible after upgrades, and involvement of IT is required for testing, quickly causing fatigue for both our Support team as well as clients. By adding Add-In to Office Cloud, upgrading will be automatic and will no longer require IT sanction. Additionally, as Cloud has become a more prominent solution for businesses, Office 365 and Google Cloud has been incorporated by more and more companies. Making sure our Add-In solutions are available on Cloud is beneficial to long-term business growth and sustainability. Since Office 365 and Google Cloud are two entirely different ecosystems, and our Add-In is already available in Microsoft environment, we would work on Add-In Office 365 first.聽聽Product Structure * Global聽 ** Profile ** Refresh Options ** Templates ** Help * C&E MP ** Series聽 ** Curve ** Element ** Upload聽 * Direct聽 ** Investment ** Economic Data ** Key Indicators聽Project Process: # Global features聽 # C&E Add-In features # Direct Add-In features聽聽Challenges:聽 * Challenge 1: Requirement of excellent feature performance since upgrading is automatic * Solution 1: Enable version control that allow users to decide if they want to upgrade, or if they want to downgrade to previous version聽 * Challenge 2: Local <> Cloud compatibility. Formulas of a file created on desktop Excel should work when the file is opened up in Office 365, and vice versa.聽 * Solution 2: Ensure consistent API usage of the same formulas in both local and Cloud聽聽聽聽', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 6, 2, null, null, 'NEA-2582'),
