    ('4276', 'Shutdown Forecast Phase 2', 'In phase 1, we build Shutdown Forecast table with Tableau to provide shutdown forecast probability for US Equity funds in the next 2 years.聽The forecast data is great info for users to see serious alert on funds they''re managing or distributing. This table also provides filtering function based on Branding, Firm, Global Category and Shutdown Forecast Probability Category. This table also provides sorting function on the table.聽However, this table also has limitation on below needs: 1) no easy way to see more detail info on a certain fund or underlying share class if a fund is in alert; 2) no easy way to bring a selected list of funds from here to Direct Cloud to do further analysis and share research insight. These limitations are partly caused by Tableau table limitation.We would like to address these limitations by building a Shutdown Forecast table based on M* Web Component, so that expand options for further actions and connection with other features.Below features are considered to be supported: * Add As of Date to indicate forecast time period starting point * Allow users to select some of funds in the table, see how many funds are selected * My funds and my competitors can be a filter * Show this in Lists & Screens Dashboard * Connect the fund level or share-class level forecast from Shutdown tab to SWOT analyzerWhat data do we have at different levels: * Data at level higher than fund:聽 ** Branding Name ** Firm Name * Data at fund level: ** Fund Name, FundID ** Fund Forecast Growth Rate into future 12 months ** Fund SWOT Score into future 12 months ** Fund Size, Fund-level Net Flow, fund growth rate ** Global Category ** Manager Name ** Morningstar Analyst Rating * Data at level (share class) lower than fund: ** Share Class Name, SecID ** Share Class flow attribution, forecast growth rate, SWOT Score and what-if analysis ** Net Assets - Share Class, Share Class Net Flow ** Expense ** Return ** Morningstar Category, Morningstar Rating ** SAL report', -1, 2, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 2, 0, null, null, 'INPU-1858'),
