    ('4278', 'Fund Level Forecast', '*+User problem we are trying to solve+*As a product manager for a fund, he or she wants to understand how a fund overall stacks up against the competitors or peers within the same category from a flow perspective so they can conclusively determine what products to focus on.聽 Sometimes money is moving within or between share classes and that movement creates a lot of noise on the SWOT chart.聽 Multiple share classes can appear on different quadrants of the SWOT.聽 By consolidating the share classes, they can remove a lot of the noise and have a more precise view of the fund and the actions that can be taken.聽', -1, 0, 5, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 2, 0, null, null, 'INPU-1823'),
